 (II)--the son of भूमिमित्र. {{F}}1:  वा. ९९. ३१७.{{/F}} His reign lasted for २५ (२७?) years. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ७४. १३१; M. २७२. १०.{{/F}}

अजामुख|ajaamukha
--one of Danu's sons. वा. ६८. 5.

अजामुखस्|ajaamukhas
 (also अधोमुखस्)--a group of पिशाचस्. Br. III. 7. ३८१; वा. ६९. २६३, २६७.

अजामिल|ajaamila
--an old इतिहास of. A ब्राह्मण of कन्या- kubja, versed in शास्त्रस् and celebrated in आचार। Once when out to get कुश grass, he saw a दासी and fell in love. Then he abandoned all his duties and discarded his wedded wife. The दासी became his wife. She bore him ten sons. The last was named नारायण best loved of his parents. At [page१-032+ ३२] the time of his death, when the messengers of Yama were waiting to remove him to hell, he called out his last son by his name नारायण. On this, the messengers of वीष्णु were on the scene and prevented Yama's men from taking the ब्राह्मन् to hell. It was argued that pronouncing the name of Hari at his death redeemed him of all his sins, and that alone was the secret of Dharma. Yama heard this and approved it. अजामिल, thus rescued from Death, felt peni- tent, and while making तपस् at गङ्गाद्वार, he cast off his body and reached विष्णुलोक। भा. VI. 1. २०. to the end; Ib. VI. ch. 2 & 3.

अजित|ajita
 (I)--a manifestation of Hari during the epoch of Manu चाक्षुष. In this period the क्षीरोद was churned and nectar was secured. {{F}}1:  भा. II. 2. 5; VIII. 5. 9-१०.{{/F}} Praised by ब्रह्मा. {{F}}2:  Ib. VIII. 5. २५-50.{{/F}} Advised gods to befriend Asuras and then get अमृत by churning the ocean, with their co-operation, to be able ultimately to prevail against them; {{F}}3:  Ib. VIII. 6. १८-25.{{/F}} began to take part in अमृतमथन when the efforts of others produced no results. {{F}}4:  Ib. VIII. 7. १६; X. 2. २०; X. ५१. ४८.{{/F}}

अजित|ajita
 (II)--a पृथुक god. Br. II. ३६. ७४.

अजित|ajita
 (III)--the name of Hari born in स्वारोचिष epoch from तुषिता. Br. III. 3. ११४.

अजिता|ajitaa
 (I)--the goddess following भवमालिनी. M. १७९. ७१.

