--५०००+980 according to ऋषिस् like अङ्गीरस. वा. ६१. ७२.

अदर्शना|adarshanaa
--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. २७. [page१-044+ ५०]

अदिति|aditi
 (I)--a daughter of दक्ष and a wife of कश्यप. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 1. १०; VI. 6. २५; Br. II. ३३. १७; III. 3. ५६, ११७; ७१. २००; Vi. I. १५. १२४; III. 1. ४२.{{/F}} Mother of वामन-Hari and other gods. {{F}}2:  भा. VIII. १३. 6; VI. 6. ३८-39; VI. १८. 9; X. 3. ४२; M. १७२. 5; १७८. २०; वा., ९६. १९६; ९७, २३.{{/F}} Was much con- cerned at the evacuation of अमरावति by gods, and informed her husband of her grief. कश्यप consoled her saying that it was all Hari's माया and everything would be rectified by His aid. Asked to the means of approaching Hari, कश्यप taught her the पयोव्रत। Observed the व्रत for twelve days as directed. Hari heard her prayers, promised to be born in her womb to protect her sons, and desired that she should keep it a secret. She soon waited on कश्यप and became pregnant with Hari. Then Hari was praised by ब्रह्मा. {{F}}3:  भा. VIII. ch. १६ & १७.{{/F}} Birth of the Lord described. {{F}}4:  भा. VIII. १८. 1-११; Br. III. ७२. २२; ७३. ७५.{{/F}} Changed before her into a boy-ब्रह्मचारिन्. {{F}}5:  भा. VIII. १८. १२.{{/F}} Worshipped for food and other things, while her sons the आदित्यस् are prayed to for attainment of heaven. {{F}}6:  Ib. VIII. १८. १३-19; II. 3. 4; M. १७१. ५५-8.{{/F}} Her desire was fulfilled by वामन. Pleased with his anointing, gods sent their praises to Aditi on the exploits of वामन. {{F}}7:  Ib. VIII. २३. 4, २१, २७; M. २४४. 9-४८; २४५. ६३; २४६. ५८.{{/F}} कृष्न took back the कुण्डलस् which had been taken away by Naraka, and सत्यभामा in her Lord's company bowed to Aditi and handed over the कुण्डलस्। At this Aditi embraced her daughter-in-law. {{F}}8:  भा. X. ५९. ३८; Ib. [६५ (v) 6-१०]; Vi. V. २९. ११, ३५; ३० (whole).{{/F}} प्रजापति caused the तेजस् of the अण्डम् in her गर्भ, and removing it at the request of gods, made it into two pieces, and finding it weak, placed it on the lap of the Sun- god (मार्ताण्ड): given to dharma. {{F}}9:  Br. III. 7. २७७-94, ४६५.{{/F}} A part of Mother Earth. {{F}}१०:  Br. III. ७१. २३८; M. 6. 1. 5; ११. 2; ४७. 9; १४६. १८; १५४. ३५१; १७१. २९.{{/F}} A mother goddess. {{F}}११:  M. १७९. १५.{{/F}} Worshipped in housebuilding. {{F}}१२:  M. २५३. २७.{{/F}} Mother of the १२ A1dityas the former Jayadevas. {{F}}१३:  Br. III. 4. ३४; वा. ६६. ५५; ६०. ६५.{{/F}} Known for strength. {{F}}१४:  वा. ६९. ९२. Br. II. १३. ७९.{{/F}} [page१-045+ ३०]

