 (II)--nectar arising out of the churning of milk ocean by gods and Asuras. Others that came out of it were curds, liquor, Soma, लक्ष्मी, horse, Kaustubha, पारिजात, and lastly कालकूट. Then appeared Dhanvantari. Distri- bution of अमृतम् by मोहिनी, the form assumed by Hari to delude the Asuras. When राहु was seen, partaking of it, [page१-086+ २८] had his head cut off. Finding themselves deceived, the Asuras began war. M. 1. 9; २४९. १४ to the end; cha. २५० and २५१ (whole); वा. २३. ९०; ५२. ३७; ९२. 9; Vi. I. 9. ८०-111.

अमृतप्रभस्|amRtaprabhas
--gods of सावर्णि epoch. भा. VIII. १३. १२.

अमृतमन्थन|amRtamanthana
--the fourth देवासुर battle, in which Indra defeated प्रःलाद. {{F}}1:  Br. III. ७२. ७३ and ७९; IV. 6. 7.{{/F}} Also the fourth of twelve incarna- tions of Hari by name Indra; with details of the battle. {{F}}2:  M. ४७. ४३ and ४८; २४९. ५१; वा. ९७. ७४. ७९.{{/F}}

