अश्वमेध|ashvamedha
--Thrice performed by युधिष्ठिर. {{F}}1:  भा. I. 8. 6; १०. 2. [1]; १२. ३४.{{/F}} One hundred performed by Bali; {{F}}2:  Ib. VIII. १५. ३४.{{/F}} of अम्बरीष where वसिष्ठ and Gautama were present. {{F}}3:  Ib. IX. 4. २२.{{/F}} Thrice performed by परीक्षित्. {{F}}4:  Ib. I. १६. 3.{{/F}} Performed by अङ्ग when gods did not respond to his call. {{F}}5:  Ib. IV. १३. २५.{{/F}} A hundred were performed by पृथु. But in the last Indra stole away the horse. {{F}}6:  Ib. IV. १६. २४; १९, 1.{{/F}} Performed by Indra. {{F}}7:  Ib. VI. १३. १८-20; Br. II. ३०. १०; M. १४३. 6-२६.{{/F}} Per- formed by कृष्ण at द्वारका. The sacrificial horse was sent out with a number of warriors to watch its course. All [page१-128+ ४०] kings including the पाण्डवस् attended the sacrifice. In the course of the sacrifice a ब्राह्मण complained of the death of his children immediately after birth. At this Arjuna (s.v.) offered to give succour and recovered them with कृष्ण's aid, from नारायण's abode. नारायण said that he took the children as a means to see कृष्ण and Arjuna in their human form. The अवभृत of the sacrifice was cele- brated in the यमुना. {{F}}8:  भा. X. ८९. २२-64.{{/F}} A remedy for brahmicide. {{F}}9:  Ib. VI. १३. 6-9.{{/F}} Per- formed by शूद्र kings in Kali age; {{F}}१०:  Br. II. ३१. ६७; M. १४४. ४३.{{/F}} of other kings; {{F}}११:  Br. II. ३४. २४; III. 5. 7; 7. २६८; ११. १३-16; ६४. १७; ६८. २६; ७०. २४ and २७; ७१. ११९; ७२. २८; IV. १२. ३१.{{/F}} of इक्ष्वाकु, of दक्ष, of सुयज्ञ, of Nala, of शतानीक of पुरू- ravas; {{F}}१२:  M. १२. १०; १२. १५; ४४, २३ and ६४; २४. १०; वा. १०५. १०. ३२; १११. १७, ५१; ११२. ३१-2.{{/F}} equal to going to गया, bath in the प्रयाग and Ganges, कोटिहोम, ग्रहबलि, etc. {{F}}१३:  M. २२. 6; २८. 6; ५३. १५; ५८. ५४; १०६. २९; १८३. ७१ and ८०.{{/F}} १०० of them performed by Somadatta; {{F}}१४:  Vi. IV. 1. ५६.{{/F}} as efficacious as reading the विष्णु पुराण; {{F}}१५:  Vi. VI. 8. २८ & ३४.{{/F}} performed by other sages. {{F}}१६:  वा. २०. १६; ३२. ५२; ३०. २९१; ५०. २२१; ५७. ५२; ६०. २३; ६७. ५०, ५३-8; ७१. ७७; ७५. ६०, ७५; ९९. ४५६; १०४. ८४; भा. IX. २२. ३९.{{/F}}

