अश्विन्स्|ashvins
--the gods of Vaivasvata epoch; sons of बदवा (सम्ज्ञा) and Vivasvat born through the nose and hence नासत्यस्; {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. १३. 4, १०; Br. III. ५९. ७४-76; M. 9. २९; ११. ३५-7; २५. ४३; Vi. I. 9. ६४; III. 2. 7; वा. ८४. २३-24,{{/F}} fought with वृषपर्व in देवासुर war. {{F}}2:  भा. VIII. १०. ३०.{{/F}} Were taught the अश्वसिरस् मन्त्र by the sage दध्यङ्ग. {{F}}3:  Ib. VI. 9. ५२; १०. १७.{{/F}} Called on Cyavana. Being physicians they could not parti- cipate in सोम। Cyavana offered a share in सोम to them if they could give him a youthful form. He was made to look exactly like themselves so much so that सुकन्या was not able to distinguish her husband. On a prayer the [page१-131+ ५७] अश्विन्स् showed सुकन्या her lord and departed. {{F}}4:  भा. IX. 3. ११-17. वा. १०. ७१; ३०. ८४; ३९. ४९.{{/F}} In the यज्ञ of शर्याति, were allowed to partake of सोम juice. {{F}}5:  भा. IX. 3. २४-26.{{/F}} Parents of Nakula and Sahadeva through पाण्डु's queen माद्री. {{F}}6:  Ib. IX. २२. २८; M. ४६. १०; ५०. ५०; Vi. IV. २०. ४०.{{/F}} Came to द्वारका to ask कृष्ण to go to वैकुण्ठ; {{F}}7:  भा. XI. 6. 2; वा. ९६. १५४; ९९. २४५.{{/F}} wor- shipped for long life; {{F}}8:  भा. II. 3. 5.{{/F}} form the nose of पुरुष; {{F}}9:  भा. II. 1. २९.{{/F}} guard medi- cinal herbs in Candra hill of प्लक्ष for nectar; {{F}}१०:  Br. II. १९. 8; वा. ४९. 9.{{/F}} born from the nostrils of प्रजापति; vanquished by रावण; {{F}}११:  Br. III. 1. ५७; 7. २५४.{{/F}} present in the चन्द्रशाल of देवी. {{F}}१२:  Ib. III. ३५. ५७.{{/F}} Fought with Devas against कालनेमि, being experts in चित्रयुद्धम्। {{F}}१३:  M. १४८. ८६, ९७.{{/F}} Also अश्वि- कुमारकौ; worship of, in the ग्रहबलि। {{F}}१४:  M. ९३. १६; २४७. १०.{{/F}} Born of ब्रह्मा; {{F}}१५:  वा. ६५. ५७.{{/F}} the two forefeet of the शिशुमार (porpoise); {{F}}१६:  वा. II. १२. ३२; वा. ५२. ९३; Br. II. २३. १०३; M. १२७. २३.{{/F}} inhabit the भुवर्लोक; {{F}}१७:  वा. १०१. २९; Br. IV. 2. २७.{{/F}} stood on गयासुर, along with other gods; {{F}}१८:  वा. १०६. ५९.{{/F}} presented their weapons on the occasion of the marriage of शिव with ललिता to the divine couple; {{F}}१९:  Br. IV. १५. २४.{{/F}} came with other gods to pray to goddess ललिता for her victory against भण्ड; {{F}}२०:  Ib. IV. २०. ५२.{{/F}} the ears of वामन अवतार {{F}}२१:  M. २४६. ५६.{{/F}}

