इक्ष्वाकु|ixvaaku
--one of the ten (nine-ब्र्। प्।) sons of Vaiva- svata Manu. Born of his sneezing. {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. १३. 2; IX. 1. 3 and १२; 2. 2; वा. ६४. २९; ८५. 4; ८८. 9; Vi. IV. 1. 7; Br. II. ३८. ३०; III. ६०. 2 and २०; ६३. 8; M. 9. ३०; ११. ४१.{{/F}} Father of a hundred sons--विकुक्षि, Nimi, दण्ड and others. २५ of these sons ruled आर्यावर्त, २५, the western territory, three, the middle country and the rest all other provinces. Once in connec- tion with an अष्टक ritual, विकुक्षि was asked to secure some flesh. Accordingly he did. But feeling hungry he partook a part of hare's flesh. When the remainder was presented, the पुरोहित refused to take it on the ground that it was remain- der of that already tasted. विकुक्षि was therefore punished with banishment. It is said that he became a yogin and attained salvation. {{F}}2:  भा. IX. 6. 4-१०; Vi. IV. 2. १५-18.{{/F}} A king known for his exemplary pro- tection of his subjects. परीक्षित् compared to him. {{F}}3:  भा. I. १२. १९.{{/F}} Promi- nent kings of his line. {{F}}4:  M. १२. १५-56; वा. ९९. २८०-290.{{/F}} Knew the power of Hari's योग, and in his line Hari incarnated. {{F}}5:  भा. II. 7. २३ and ४४; XII. 2. ३७;{{/F}} Sumitra was the last क्षत्रिय king of this line. {{F}}6:  Br. III. ७४. २४४; M. २७३. ५३; वा. ९९. २६६ and ४३१.{{/F}} Originator of the solar race; the genea- logy given down to शन्तायु of the भारत war. {{F}}7:  M. १२. १५-56.{{/F}} Heard from वसिष्ठ of Ila's conversion to the other sex in the शर- वण forest and performed अश्वमेध by which Ila was [page१-184+ २७] turned into a किम्पुरुष. {{F}}8:  M. १२. 1-१५.{{/F}} Was addressed by the पितृस् in कलाप forest on the effect of offering श्राद्ध at गया. {{F}}१०:  Vi. III. 1. ३३; १६. १७-18.{{/F}} The line of. {{F}}११:  वा. 1. १४२; ८८. १७५-184; Vi. IV. २२. 1-१३.{{/F}} Had १०० branches. {{F}}१२:  वा. ९९. ४५१.{{/F}}

