कर्ण|karNa
 (I)--born of कुन्ती as a virgin and abandoned by her; brought up by Adhiratha; became a king and father of वृषसेन. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २३. १३-14; X. ४९. 2; Vi. IV. १४. ३६; १८. २८-9; V. ३५. 5 and 7; ३८. १६.{{/F}} पाण्डवस् defeated his army. Arjuna was saved from कर्ण's arrows by कृष्ण. Joined Duryodhana in insulting Vidura, and was his evil adviser. {{F}}2:  भा. I. १५. १५-16; III. 1. १४; 3. १३.{{/F}} Resented साम्ब's action in carrying away लक्ष्मणा but vanquished by साम्ब. In charge of gifts in युधिष्तिर's राजसूय। Joined Duryodhana's army and succeeded द्रोण as com- mander for two days, but was killed by Arjuna. {{F}}3:  भा. X. ६८. 5 and 9; ७५. 5; ७८ [९५ (v) १६] & [३७].{{/F}} Failed to hit the mark in the स्वयम्वर of लक्ष्मणा. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ८३. २३.{{/F}} Identified with Cakravarman, the son of Bala. {{F}}5:  Br. III. 6. ३२.{{/F}} Was called son of सूत as he was brought up by Adhiratha the सूत. {{F}}6:  वा. ९९. ११८.{{/F}} [page१-326+ २१]

कर्ण|karNa
 (II)--a son of आण्डिर. M. ४८. 5.

कर्ण|karNa
 (III)--born in after-birth as Cakravarma, the son of Bali. वा. ६८. ३२; Br. III. 6. ३३.

कर्ण|karNa
 (IV)--the son of अङ्ग. M. ४८. १०२-4; वा. ९९. ११२.

कर्णक|karNaka
--a मन्त्रकृत्। M. १४५. १०८.

कर्णजिह्व|karNajihva
--an आत्रेय gotrakara. M. १९७. 3.

कर्णप्रावर्णस्|karNapraavarNas
--country of, watered by नलिनी. Br. II. १८. ६०; M. १२१. ५८; वा. ४७. ५७.

कर्णमोटि|karNamoTi
--a mindborn mother. M. १७९. १५.

कर्णाटकस् (दक्षिण)|karNaaTakas (daxiNa)
--Inhabitants of south कर्णा- टक. भा. V. 6. 7.

कर्णिका|karNikaa
 (I)--wife of कङ्क and mother of ऋतधा- man and Jaya. भा. IX. २४. ४४. [page१-327+ ३२]

कर्णिका|karNikaa
 (II)--the tendril of the world lotus; Atri regards it as १०० cornered, भृगु as १००० cornered, भा- guri, square, वार्षायणि Sa1mudra, गालव, tray-shaped, गार्- gya like braided hair and क्रोष्तुकि circle-like. Each had only partial knowledge; ब्रह्मा alone knows it entire. वा. ३४. ५८-69.

कर्णिकार|karNikaara
--a son of जटायु. M. 6. ३६.

कर्णीर|karNiira
--a नाग. वा. ६९. ६९.

कर्दम|kardama
 (I)--father of कपील. Married देवहूति. {{F}}1:  भा. II. 7. 3; IV. 1. १०.{{/F}} A son of ब्रह्मा born of his shadow. A progenitor and a योगि; {{F}}2:  Ib. III. १२. २७ & ५६; chap. २१ to २४.{{/F}} performed in कृतयुग austerities on the banks of सरस्वती for १०,000 years; when Hari appeared before him, he praised Him and asked for a suitable wife. देवहूति was suggested and the Lord disappeared. Manu came with his wife and daughter to his hermitage, and was suitably received. Kardama agreed to marry his daughter and lead a householder's life until the birth of children. After wed- ding, Manu and his wife returned home. Pleased at his wife's devotion, created an aerial car artistically built and furnished. Took his wife after her bath and dress round the earth for a hundred years. Nine daughters were born when according to original contract he was anxious to leave her for woods to practise योग। Noticing her anxiety at his departure, he consoled her that she would give birth to Hari who would bring solace to her. On the birth of Kapila, ब्रह्मा and other seers called on him; gave his daughters in marriage, took leave of his son and retired to a life of penance. [page१-328+ ३१]

कर्दम|kardama
 (II)--a son of Pulaha and क्षमा; married Sruti; son शङ्खपद and daughter काम्या; a प्रजापति; a sage by तपस् and a देवऋषि; {{F}}1:  Br. I. 1. ६५; II. ११. २३ and ३१; ३२. ९९; ३५. ९४; III. 8. १८; १०. ९३; M. १४५. ९३; वा. 1. ८०; 3. 3; २८. २५-29; ३३. 7; ३८. 7; ५९. ९१; ६१. ८४; ६५. ५३; Vi. I. १०. १०.{{/F}} a pravara. {{F}}2:  M. १९९. १६.{{/F}}

कर्दम|kardama
 (III)--a प्रजापति: wife of सिनीवली; had two daughters सम्राट् and कुक्षि, besides ten sons. {{F}}1:  Br. II. १४. 7; III. 1. ५३.{{/F}} His wife left him for Soma. His world that of आज्य पितृस्। {{F}}2:  M. १५. २०; २३. २४.{{/F}}

कर्दम|kardama
 (IV)--also शम्खप; a लोकपाल. Br. II. २१. १५७; M. १२४. ९५; वा. ५०. २०६.

कर्दमायन|kardamaayana
--a gotrakara of Atri family. M. १९७. 1.

कर्दमाल|kardamaala
--in the navel portion of गया; bath and श्राद्ध here to get rid of the debt to पितृस्. वा. ११२. ५७.

कर्दमालम्|kardamaalam
--a तीर्थम् sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ७७.

कर्पटस्|karpaTas
--पाषण्डस् who live by sheer prowess. वा. ७८. ३०.

कर्म|karma
 (I)--two-fold; प्रवृत्ति and निवृत्ति; {{F}}1:  Vi. I. 1. २७; VI. 4. ४१.{{/F}} importance of; {{F}}2:  Vi. I. १८. ३२.{{/F}} that which consists of यज्ञ is best. {{F}}3:  Vi. II. १४. १४.{{/F}}

कर्म|karma
 (II)--(Vedic) two-fold; प्रवृत्त and निवृत्त। {{F}}1:  भा. VII. १५. ४७-49.{{/F}} There is another classification of Karma: वैदिक, तान्त्रिक, [page१-329+ ३६] and मिश्र (mixed). {{F}}2:  Ib. XI. २७. 7.{{/F}} कृष्ण advised Uddhava to pursue निवृत्त and abandon प्रवृत्त path. {{F}}3:  Ib. XI. १०. 4.{{/F}} Karma exalted as the source of all good and evil, and appropriate to four castes: is done due to मायामोहन्; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. २३. ५०; २४. १३-14 & १८-20.{{/F}} does not lead to final destruc- tion of कर्मन्। {{F}}5:  Ib. VI. 1. ११.{{/F}} Seven-fold: तपस्, ब्रह्मचर्य, यज्ञ, प्रजा, श्राद्ध, विद्या and दान। Bad कर्मस्--five-fold: killing, theft, in- jury, drinking and lust. {{F}}6:  Br. II. २८. ७५; III. 4. 5 & २४; २८. 9; IV. 5. २५; 6. ३७; वा. ५६. ७०.{{/F}}

कर्म|karma
 with Agni is काम्य, नैमित्तिक and अजस्र; should be done with detachment. {{F}}7:  वा. २९. ४४; १०४. ८६-96.{{/F}} Rebirth after death is dependent on. {{F}}8:  वा. १४. 2-3, ३१-42; ६१. १०६.{{/F}}

कर्मजित्|karmajit
--son of बृहत्सेन and father of सृतञ्जय. भा. IX. २२. ४७.

कर्मज्ञानम्|karmaJNaanam
--initiated according to अधिकार। वा. १०४. ८६, ९४.

कर्मदण्ड|karmadaNDa
--restraint of worldly duties. वा. १७. 6.

कर्मधर्मवती|karmadharmavatii
--a daughter of Ugrasena. वा. ९६. १३३.

कर्मभूमि|karmabhuumi
--the earth as distinguished from Heaven. {{F}}1:  Br. IV. 9. १०.{{/F}} भारतवर्ष as compared with others which are भोगभूमिस्। {{F}}2:  Vi. II. 3. २२.{{/F}}

कर्मयोग|karmayoga
--Three-fold. Scriptural and not लौकिक। Intended for the attached and householders. आचार preli- minary to कर्म। कर्मकाण्ड an ocean. Three kinds of [page१-330+ ३४] worship--vedic, तान्त्रिच्, and mixed. Worship of image through a guru and according to established rules. {{F}}1:  भा. XI. 3. ४१-55; २०. 6-7; २१. १४-15; २७. 1 & 6-9.{{/F}} Preach- ed by जनार्दन to Manu; greater than ज्ञान योग; as ज्ञा- नम् is the result of कर्म; origin of ब्रह्मा from: also क्रिया योग; five यज्ञस् and ३० सम्स्कारस् come under this. {{F}}2:  M. ५२. 3-११; २५८. 2.{{/F}} Four of Karma category--अग्निहोत्र, silence, study and sacrifice, when not performed properly give fear. {{F}}3:  M. ३९. २५-7.{{/F}}

कर्मश्रेष्ठ|karmashreShTha
--a son of Pulaha and गती. भा. IV. 1. ३८.

कर्मसम्न्यास|karmasamnyaasa
--leads to ब्रह्मण्यम्। वा. ५७. ११८.

कर्मारनाग|karmaaranaaga
--the Fifth tala or महातल. वा. ५०. ३६.

कलन|kalana
--a door-keeper of महाकाल. Br. IV. ३२. १८.

कलश|kalasha
--a राक्षस; his city in the Atalam. वा. ५०. १८.

कलशीकण्ठ|kalashiikaNTha
--a sage. M. १९६. २७.

कलहम्सस्|kalahamsas
--sons of धृतराष्ट्रि and गरुड. Br. III. 7. ४५७.

कलस्|kalas
 (I)--sixty in number: {{F}}1:  Br. IV. ३४. ७०.{{/F}} a period of time; {{F}}2:  वा. ३०. १३; ७०. १५; M. ३४. 9.{{/F}} ३० लवस् according to a calculation; {{F}}3:  वा. १००. २१६.{{/F}} ३३ काठस्; {{F}}4:  वा. ५७. 6; १००. २१८; Vi. I. 3. 8; II. 8. ५९; VI. 3. 6.{{/F}} ३० कलस् make a मुहूर्त or १६० मात्रस्। {{F}}5:  वा. ५०. १७९; ९३. ७२; Br. II. 7. १९; १३. १४.{{/F}} [page१-331+ ३२]

कलस्|kalas
 (II)--a Janapada of the केतुमाल country. वा. ४४. १५.

कलस्|kalas
 (III)--Digits of Soma recovered by propitiating दक्ष: {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. २४; M. ३४. 9; १४२. 4.{{/F}} one-sixteenth part.

कला|kalaa
 (I)--a स्वर शक्ति। Br. IV. ४४. ५७.

कला|kalaa
 (II)--a daughter of Kardama married to मरीचि; bore two sons, कश्यप and पूर्णिमन्. भा. III. २४. २२; IV. 1. १३.

कलाप|kalaapa
 (I)--a deva-gandharva. वा. ६८. ३८.

कलाप|kalaapa
 (II)--a forest where इक्ष्वाकु was addressed by पितृस्. Vi. III. १६. १७.

कलापग्राम|kalaapagraama
--on the East slopes of the Himalayas {{F}}1:  वा. 1. १८९; ४१. ४३-6; ४७, ४७.{{/F}} noted for great sages. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ८७. 7.{{/F}} Residence of Manu. Here देवापि [and Puru (Manu) वि। प्।] continued their योग practice. These yogins would start the course of वर्णाश्रम धर्म again at the end of Kali; {{F}}3:  IX. १२. 6; २२. १७; XII. 2. ३७-38; Br. I. 1. १६४; III. ६३. २१०; ६६. 7; M. १२१. ४९; २७३. ५६.{{/F}} watered by the Ganges. {{F}}4:  Br. II. १८. ५०.{{/F}} देवापि and Manu originate क्षत्रिय clans in कृत युग at; the race of Manu responsible for rulers throughout the three ages, कृत, त्रेता and द्वापर। {{F}}5:  वा. ८८. २१०: ९१. 7: ९९. ४३७; Vi. IV. २४. ११८-121.{{/F}} Manu stands rooted to योग at. {{F}}6:  Vi. IV. 4. १०९.{{/F}} [page१-332+ ३८]

कलि|kali
 (I)--born of Krodha and हीम्सा. Married Durukti who gave birth to Bhaya and मृत्यु. {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 8. 3.{{/F}} Personified as king but शूद्र by birth, kicking a cow and bull. Vanquished by परीक्षित्. Kali fell at his feet when परीक्षित् asked him to leave ब्रह्मावर्त. Asked for a place to reside, परीक्- षित् appointed him to five unrighteous spheres--wine, dice, gold, women and slaughter. Father of अधर्म, heroic in the midst of children and cowardly before the valiant. {{F}}2:  Ib. I. १६. 4; १७. २९-40; १८. 6-8.{{/F}} His rule in युगान्तर described. {{F}}3:  Ib. II. 7. ३८.{{/F}}

कलि|kali
 (II)--a Mauneya Gandharva; a son of Brahma- dhana. Br. III. 7. 4; वा. ६९. 3, १३३.

कलि|kali
 (III)--a son of वरुण and शुनादेवी (सामुद्रि- वा। प्।); father of Jaya and Vijaya; one wife of Kali, सुरा, mother of Mada; other wives, त्वाष्ट्रि, हिम्सा and निकृति; other sons of Kali, all cannibals, नाक, Vighna, शद्रम and Vidhama. Br. III. ५९. 6; वा. ८४. 6-१०.

कलि|kali
 (IV)--a door-keeper of महाकाल. Br. IV. ३२. १८.

कलिङ्ग|kalinga
 (I)--a क्षेत्रज son of Bali; after him came कलिङ्गस् (s.v.); {{F}}1:  Br. III. ७४. २८ & ८७; M. ४८. २५; वा. ९९. २८; Vi. IV. १८. १३-14.{{/F}} a राक्षस in the Atalam. (Tatvalam- ब्र्। प्।). {{F}}2:  वा. ५०. १७; Br. II. १९. १८.{{/F}}

कलिङ्ग|kalinga
 (II)--(Mt.) a hill on the south of the मानस. वा. ३६. २२; ४२. २८.

कलिङ्ग|kalinga
 (III)--a southern kingdom of मध्यदेश unfit for श्राद्ध; a Janapada of the दक्षिणापथ. Its king was stationed by जरासन्ध on the east gate of मथुरा, and on the same direction during the siege of Gomanta; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १६. ४२ & ५७; III. १३. १३; १४. ३३ & ८०; ७४. १९८ & २१३; M. १६३. ७२; वा. ७७. १३; ७८. २३; ९९. ३२४, ३८६, ४०२.{{/F}} present at [page१-333+ ४६] Pradyumna's marriage. Advised Rukmin to vanquish बलराम in dice, and laughed at the latter when he was defeated. His teeth were broken by राम. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ५०. ११[2]; ५२. ११[5]; ६१. २७-29; ३२[1] & ३७; IV. 5. २१; Vi. V. २८. १०, १५, २४.{{/F}} Its ३२ kings. {{F}}3:  M. २७२. १६.{{/F}} On its south flows the नर्मदा where the hill अमरकण्- टक is. {{F}}4:  M. १८६. १२.{{/F}} In the कृतयुग, the first man appeared in this country {{F}}5:  वा. ५८. ११०.{{/F}} under Guhas. {{F}}6:  Vi. III. 7. ३६.{{/F}}

कलिङ्गस्|kalingas
--a tribe born of दीर्घतमस् and Bali's wife; enlisted by जरासन्ध against the Yadus; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २३. 5; X. [५० (V) 3]; M. ११४. ३६ and ४७; वा. ४५. १२५.{{/F}} people of the दक्षिणापथ. {{F}}2:  वा. ४५. १२५; Vi. II. 3. १६.{{/F}}

कालिन्दी|kaalindii
--the daughter of सम्ज्ञा. वा. ८४. ३६.

कलियुग|kaliyuga
--the features of the युग, and its discontents. Removed by hearing the story of कृष्ण, as the ऋषिस् did in the नैमिष forest. The source of unrighteousness. {{F}}1:  भा. I. 1. १०, १६ & २१; १२. २६; १५. ३६-7; XI. 5. २०, ३१-42; वा. ५८. ३०-73.{{/F}} Form of Hari worshipped in. {{F}}2:  M. १४२. १७-27; २७३. ४९; वा. ९९. ४२९.{{/F}} Reflections on the conduct of castes and observance of धर्म by persons. कलि becomes कृत after the अवतार् of Kalki. When the सप्तऋषिस् traverse Maghas, and on the day when कृष्ण left the earth for Heaven then began Kali of १२०० divine years. Grows in strength commencing with Nanda. The actual beginning was when कृष्ण left for वैकुण्ठ; a description of the युग। Worship of Hari by कीर्तन। {{F}}3:  भा. XII. chap. 2 & 3.{{/F}} Its advent was recognised by Mucukunda from the smallness of the men, plants, trees, etc., which he saw after he woke up from his long sleep. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ५२. 2.{{/F}} Deterioration of Vedic धर्म and rise of पाखण्डस्. Incarnation of Pramati in the form of a horse who puts down all heretics and the unrighteous. {{F}}5:  Br. II. २९. २३-34; ३१. 5-१०२; III. १४. ४६. ७४. २०७-241; M. १४४. ३०-88.{{/F}} Predominance of here- [page१-334+ ३८] tics and शूद्रस् in; {{F}}6:  वा. ७८. ३६.{{/F}} १०६,000 or ३६०,000-duration of; its सन्- ध्याम्श 1,००० years. {{F}}7:  वा. ३२. ६३; ९९. २६४; १०२. 4. M. २७३. २७-33, ४५. ५०.{{/F}} Noted for theft; see तृष्यम्; {{F}}8:  Br. II. 7. ५९.{{/F}} दानम् the chief act and तमस् the chief quality. {{F}}9:  वा. 8. ६६.{{/F}} descrip- tion of the evils of: bad rule and decay of civilization and morality; age of man २३ years; began with परीक्षित् when the two first stars of seven ऋषिस् were in Magha; its duration according to the calculation of men ३६०,800. Then comes कृत। {{F}}१०:  Vi. IV. २४. ७१-96, ९७, १०९. ११४-15.{{/F}}

