कश्यप|kashyapa
 (I)--(सवितुः विद्वान्, मारीचि) son of मरीचि and कला, and husband of Diti. {{F}}1:  भा. III. १४. 7; IV. 1. १३; Br. II. ३७. ४४; III. 2. ३१; 3. ५५; IV. 1. २०; 2. ३३. ४७; M. १४६. १६ & २५; १७१. ३०; १९९. 1, १४, १९; वा. ६३. ४१.{{/F}} Married twelve (thirteen मत्स्य प्।) daughters of दक्ष, who were ब्रह्मवादिनीस् and लोक-मातस्। Married also पुलोमा and कालका on the advice of ब्रह्मा. Their sons were दानवस् distinguished for warlike qualities. ६०,000 of these were killed by Arjuna while in Heaven to please Indra. {{F}}2:  भा. VI. 6. 2, २५, ३४-36; M. 4. ५५; 5. १३; 6. 1-2, ४४; वा. ६५. ११५-116, १५७-158.{{/F}} Aditi was another wife of कश्यप, and was the mother of वामन-Hari. On an appeal from her on behalf of gods exiled from अमरावती, कश्यप taught her the पयोव्रत to please Hari. {{F}}3:  भा. VIII. १३. 6; १६. 2-२५; १७. २२-3: X. 3. ४२; Br. II. १३. ७९.{{/F}} Pleased with the anointing of वामन. {{F}}4:  भा. VIII. २३. २१; M. २४४. ४१; २४५. ८२.{{/F}} His तेजस्। {{F}}5:  भा. III. १६. ३५-36; १७. 2.{{/F}} Pleased with Diti's मदनद्वादशिव्रतम् but did not relish her request for a son to slay Indra but granted it under certain condi- tions. {{F}}6:  भा. VI. १८. ४४-54: III. chap. १४ (whole); M. 7. ३०-49.{{/F}} A sage of the Vaivasvata epoch. His descendants. {{F}}7:  भा. VIII. 8. ३१; १३. 5; M. 9. २७.{{/F}} Father of Vivasvat. {{F}}8:  भा. IX. 1. १०; M. ११. 2.{{/F}} Awarded मध्यदेशा by परशु- राम. {{F}}9:  भा. IX. १६. २२.{{/F}} Visited with pupils भीष्म on his death-bed; {{F}}१०:  Ib. I. 9. 8.{{/F}} goes round Dhruva. {{F}}११:  भा. IV. 9. २१; M. १२७. २४;{{/F}} See दिति, इन्द्र। A ब्रह्मवादिन् and a प्रजापति. A देवऋषि. His sons were नारद and Parvata, as also आदित्यस्, Maruts and Rudras. {{F}}१२:  Br. II. २७. १०४; ३२. ९८, ११२; ३५. ९२-95: ३८. 3; III. 1. ५३; 4. ३४; 8. 1 and २७; M. १४५. ९२; वा. 1. १३८; 3. 2: ६५. ५३; ८४. २६ and ३१.{{/F}} An अम्श of ब्रह्मा. {{F}}१३:  M. ४७. 9; Br. III. 2. १०५; ७१. २३८; वा. 1. १३८; 3. 2; ६५. ११४.{{/F}} When दक्ष grew angry on account of his daughter कश्यप drank कश्य, a kind of wine; {{F}}१४:  वा. ६५. ११५-17.{{/F}} hence his name; hid योग in a cave; {{F}}१५:  Br. I. 1. ११७; वा. ८३. ८३; Br. III. १९. ५३.{{/F}} आश्रम of; {{F}}१६:  वा. ३७. २२.{{/F}} a sage by ज्ञान; {{F}}१७:  Ib. ५९. ९०.{{/F}} place in the विश्वचक्र दान। {{F}}१८:  M. २८५. 6.{{/F}} With the sun during the months सह and सहस्य, {{F}}१९:  Ib. १२७. १७.{{/F}} a sage of चाक्षुष epoch. {{F}}२०:  वा. ६२. ६६.{{/F}} [page१-342+ ३१]

