कात्यायनी व्रतम्|kaatyaayanii vratam
--was observed by the girls of the व्रज early in the season of हेमन्त। After bathing in the यमुना, they made a figure of the देवी with sand, and worshipped it as the representation of the देवी for a month. Their object was to win कृष्ण as their husband. Prayers were also sent to भद्रकाली by rising early and bathing in the यमुना. To test their sincerity कृष्ण saw them one day playing in the river naked leaving their clothes on the banks. He removed these to the top of a नीप tree near by. The girls asked for the return of their clothes, and threatened to report to the king. कृष्ण asked them to receive their clothes from him. He said that their vow was fruitless as they bathed naked, and he returned their clothes on their saluting him with both their arms. He then blessed them and asked them to go back to the व्रज which they did. भा. X. २२. 1-२७.

