कालिय|kaaliya
 (I)--a chief of the क्रोधवश group of ser- pents. Got into a pool of the यमुना, causing the death of people who drank of the waters. कृष्ण subjugated it and ordered it to go to the sea, thus making the waters drinkable. He assured कालीय of freedom from गरुड's hostility. Son of Kadru, कालिय originally lived in Rama- णक, and refused to give Bali to गरुड according to an agreement with him. In the fight that ensued, कालिय was vanquished, and he resorted to the कालिन्दि pool where गरुड could not come. But he was expelled by कृष्ण. {{F}}1:  भा. V. २४. २९; X. ch. १६ (whole); १७. 1-१२; X. ४३. २६.{{/F}} In the Atalam region; {{F}}2:  वा. ५०. १८; ६९. ७२.{{/F}} in Talvalam ? {{F}}3:  Br. II. २०. १९; M. १६३. ५६.{{/F}} [page१-368+ २९]

