कुन्ती|kuntii
--daughter of शूर and adopted by Kuntibhoja as he was childless. दुर्वासस् taught her a मन्त्र by which she invoked the sun who returned after blessing her with a child. Being an unmarried girl, she abandoned her son in a box, and this was discovered by Adhiratha who [page१-392+ ४६] brought him up. This child was कर्ण; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २३. १३-14; २४. ३१-36; Br. III. ७१. १५२-5; M. ४६. 7.{{/F}} queen of पाण्डु: gave birth to युधिष्ठिर and four other sons by the favour of gods--Dharma, वायु and Indra and the अश्विन्स्; outlived her husband for the sake of their welfare. {{F}}2:  भा. IX. २२. २७; M. ५०. ४८-50. Br. III. 1. ४०. Vi. V. १२. २४.{{/F}} Seen by अक्रूर: Narrated to Vidura her troubles after पाण्डु's death. Her affection and love for कृष्ण; addressed him on the difficulties encountered by the पाण्डवस्. कृष्ण comforted her and explained how it was not possible for him to go to हास्तिनापुर earlier. {{F}}3:  भा. X. ५८. 7. १०; X. ४९. 1-१५; I. 8. 3: 9. १३.{{/F}} Her स्तोत्र of कृष्ण; {{F}}4:  Ib. I. 8. १७-43.{{/F}} grieved at his departure from हास्तिनापुर. Her thoughts on the other world. {{F}}5:  Ib. I. १०. 9; १३. 3; १५. ३३; X. ८२ 24.{{/F}} Heard of Drupada's defeat by her sons. Was met by कृतवर्मन् at हास्तिनापुर. At the news of the alleged burning of (पाण्डवस्, etc.), कुन्ती went to the Kurus accompanied by राम and कृष्ण, though the latter was aware of the fact of their living. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ५२. [५६ (V) 2], [5], १०; ५७. 1.{{/F}} Heard the story of the marriage of कृष्ण from his wives and was lost in wonder. {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ८४. 1.{{/F}} Left for स्यमन्तपञ्चक, and complained to Vasudeva of his neglect of her sons. Vasudeva consoled her saying that oppression from कम्सा had scattered them in different directions. {{F}}8:  Ib. X. ८२. १८-22; ८४. ५७ and ६९ [3].{{/F}} Joy at कृष्ण's visit to हास्तिनापुर. Taking leave of her कृष्ण went to द्वारका. {{F}}9:  Ib. X. 7 1. ३९; ७७. 7; १०. M. १०३. १२.{{/F}} (See पृथा) Regret- ted with her sons the loss of Duryodhana and others.^10

कुन्ती|kuntii
--a R. from the पारियत्र hill. M. ११४. २४.

कुन्तिस्|kuntis
--a Yadu tribe who took part in the marriage festivities of कृष्ण and रुक्मिनी. {{F}}1:  भा. X. ५४. ५८.{{/F}} They went to Syamanta- पञ्चक for solar eclipse. {{F}}2:  Ib. X. ८२. १३.{{/F}} Heard of कृष्ण going to मिथिला and met him with presents. {{F}}3:  Ib. ८६. २०.{{/F}} Fought with their kinsmen and ended their lives. {{F}}4:  Ib. XI. ३०. १८.{{/F}} [page१-393+ ३८]

कुन्द|kunda
--a Mt. of शाल्मलिद्वीप. भा. V. २०. १०.

कुपथ|kupatha
--a दानव. Br. III. 6. १०; वा. ६८. १०.

कुपथस्|kupathas
--a hill tribe; a mountain kingdom of the south. Br. II. १६. ६७; M. ११४. ४७. ५५; १२१. ३५.

कुपथप्रावरणस्|kupathapraavaraNas
--the kingdom of. M. १२१. ५६.

कुबलाश्व|kubalaashva
--Killed Dundhu, the son of अरूरु, on the advice of Uttanka. वा. ६८. ३१.

कुबेर|kubera
 (I)--the son of विश्रवस् (वैश्रावण) and इडविडा. His father initiated him into a great विद्या। Father of three sons--विशाल and others. Lord of यक्षस्, and brother of शिव; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 2. ३२-33; IV. 1. ३७; ११. ३३. वा. ४०. 8; ४७. 1; ७०. ३८. ९७. 2.{{/F}} was pleased with Dhruva and blessed him though he killed his followers. {{F}}2:  भा. IV. १२. 1-9.{{/F}} Presented a golden throne to पृथु. {{F}}3:  Ib. १५. १४.{{/F}} With his नरवाहन attacked कृष्ण taking पारिजात, but defeated by सत्यभामा, retreated in fear. Presented to कृष्ण eight treasures and his new city. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. [६५ (V) ४५], [६६ (V) 4-२१]; ५०. ५६.{{/F}} Attended by Guhyakas, he is compared to युधिष्ठिर attended by पाण्डवस्, कृष्ण and sages. {{F}}5:  Ib. I. 9. 3.{{/F}} Lord of Alaka and son of Pulastya and resident of Kai- लास; {{F}}6:  Br. II. १८. 1-2; ३५. ९४; ३६. २१८; M. १२१. 2-3; १३७. ३२; वा. ६९. १९६.{{/F}} vanquished by रावण; wife ऋद्धि and son Nala- कूबेर. {{F}}7:  Br. III. 7. २५४ and ३३१; 8. ४४; ७२. 2; IV. १५. २२; वा. ७०. ४१.{{/F}} Man as his riding animal: followed by यक्षस् and राक्- षसस् with respective standards--उलूक and गृध्र; [page१-394+ ३५] fought with Jambha and Kujambha and was overwhelmed; fled to Indra helpless; beaten by तारक. {{F}}8:  M. १४८. ८४; १५०. ५०-108; १५३. १७९.{{/F}} By residing in Benares, attained the status of a गणेश; {{F}}9:  M. १८०. ६२.{{/F}} observed the आदित्यशयनवृअतम्; {{F}}१०:  Ib. ४७. ३०; ५५. ३२.{{/F}} penance at the conflu- ence of the नर्मदा and the कावेरी and was blessed by शिव to be the Lord of यक्षस्; {{F}}११:  Ib. १८९. 4-११; १९१. ८५.{{/F}} icon of; {{F}}१२:  Ib. २६१. २०-2.{{/F}} defended the chariot of त्रिपुरारि. {{F}}१३:  Ib. १३३. ६३; १३८. २५; १४०. ४१.{{/F}}

कुबेर|kubera
 (II)--(Dhanada): the guardian of the north; {{F}}1:  M. ६७. १५; Vi. V. ३६. १२.{{/F}} presents of, at उमा's marriage; {{F}}2:  M. १५४. ४८९.{{/F}} in the army of deva's at तारकामय; riding animal of, man; {{F}}3:  M. १७४. १७-18.{{/F}} हरिकेश got this status at Benares; became अन्नद and क्षेत्रपाल; Udbhrama and Sambhrama, two गणस् in his service. {{F}}4:  M. १८०. ९४-99.{{/F}}

कुबेरणि|kuberaNi
--Tripravara. M. १९६. ३३.

कुबेरतुङ्ग|kuberatunga
--a sacred place fit for श्राद्ध; near नन्दा in the N. E. direction; a सिद्धक्षेत्र; a temple of महादेव; the lord performed austerities standing on one leg in the देवी's temple for a युग (दिव्य)। Br. III. १३. ८०; वा. ७७. ७८-81.

कुबेर भवनम्|kubera bhavanam
--in the पिशाचक hill. वा. ३९. ५७.

कुबेरस् (च्)|kuberas (ch)
--a Janapada of the केतुमाल. वा. ४४. १४. [page१-395+ ४०]

कुब्ज|kubja
--got final release by सत्सङ्ग। भा. XI. १२. 6.

कुब्जाभ्रम्|kubjaabhram
--a तीर्थम् sacred to पितृस्. M. २२. ६६.

कुमनस्|kumanas
--a people of the दक्षिनापथ। वा. ४५. १२५.

कुमार|kumaara
 (I) (सुब्रह्मण्य)--born in शरकानन or शरवन and was nursed by the six कृत्तिकस्, hence कार्त्ति- keya: Sucking milk with six mouths, the child came to be known as षण्मुख. Appointed commander of the celes- tial army in the तारकासुर war and killed तारक. {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 7. ६४-5; Vi. I. १५. ११५. M. 5. २६-7; १६० (whole): २२५. १८; वा. ६६. २४.{{/F}} शाख, विशाख and Naigameya were brothers. {{F}}2:  Ib. ६६. २४; M. 5. २६१७.{{/F}} An अवतार् of Hari. {{F}}3:  भा. XI. 4. १७.{{/F}} A son of Agni through स्वाहा, and the son of गन्गा by taking Agni's गर्भ due to Uma's curse. Hence son of शिव. {{F}}4:  M. १३५. ७९.{{/F}} His birth was heralded by divine musicians, siddhas, चारणस्, यक्षस्, kinnaras and others. Fed with milk by the wives of the seven sages except अरुन्धती. Hari presented him two birds--fowl and peacock, सरस्वती the lute, ब्राह्मी a goat, and शिव a ram. {{F}}5:  Br. III. 3. २४; १०. ३५. -४८; M. २०३. 6; वा. ७२. ३५-46.{{/F}} Married देवसेना, the daughter of Indra: also known as Skanda, Guha, and Deva- सेनापति. {{F}}6:  Br. IV. ३०. ३९, ९९ to the end; वा. ७२. ४८-50; Br. III. १०. ४८-51.{{/F}} मयूर as the riding animal of. {{F}}7:  M. १३५. ७६.{{/F}} Wounded by Maya in the battle of Tripuram. {{F}}8:  M. १९२. ३३.{{/F}}

कुमार (सनत्)|kumaara (sanat)
 (II)--a सिद्ध who could not com- prehend the supreme Being and who would not find fault with Hara for violating धर्म। {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 3. २०; १५. १२; १७. १२ and ३२; VIII. २३. २०.{{/F}} Learnt the भागवत from सन्कर्षण and imparted it to सान्ख्यायन. {{F}}2:  भा. III. 8. 3 and 7.{{/F}} [page१-396+ २५]

कुमार|kumaara
 (III)--a son of Havya, after whom कुमार- वर्ष was called. Br. II. १४. १७-18; वा. ३३. १६.

कुमार|kumaara
 (IV)--see भौम। Br. II. २३. ८५; २८. ९२.

कुमार|kumaara
 (V)--a प्रजापति. Br. III. 1. ५४; वा. ६५. ५३.

कुमार|kumaara
 (VI)--an author of Architecture. M. २५२. 3.

कुमार|kumaara
 (VII)--rose out of the contemplation of ब्रह्मा in the २९थ् कल्प; with white complexion and a resplendant fearful countenance and mouth; ब्रह्मा wor- shipped him as the Gods of Gods, पुराणपुरुष, the best of yogins and laughed a hearty laugh in wonder; also of red colour. वा. २२. १०-23.

कुमार|kumaara
 (VIII)--at the commencement of the eighth कल्प ब्रह्मा got a son (नीललोहित) who was weeping; he asked ब्रह्मा to give him a name for which ब्रह्मा said रुद्र; again he cried for a second name and ब्रह्मा said, भव; the other names given in order were शिव, पशुपति, ईश, भीम, उग्र and महादेव। वा. २७. 4-१६.

कुमार|kumaara
 (IX)--a नाग. वा. ६९. ७१. [page१-397+ २५]

कुमार|kumaara
 (X)--a son of Bhavya of शाकद्वीप. Vi. II. 4. ६०.

कुमार (च्)|kumaara (ch)
--a kingdom watered by ह्लादिनी; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १८. ५५.{{/F}} a tribe. {{F}}2:  वा. ४७. ५२.{{/F}}

कुमारस्|kumaaras
--a celestial group. वा. ४७. ५२.

कुमारक|kumaaraka
--the first offspring of ब्रह्मा when he was engaged in thinking of creation devoid of शब्द, स्पर्श, रूप, रस and गन्ध। ब्रह्मा pondered over a form which would be neither male nor female but with colours. Then अक्षर came out of ‘his neck; it was ओम्कार with one मात्र, then two मात्राक्षर, three अक्षरस्, then fourteen- faced deva and १४ Manus. वा. २६. 8-२८.

कुमारकोशल|kumaarakoshala
--a तीर्थ in the पालपञ्जर hill; sacred for श्राद्ध। वा. ७७. ३७.

कुमारनिलय|kumaaranilaya
--sages of, visited द्वारक. भा. X. ९०. २८[4].

कुमारवनम्|kumaaravanam
--Here पुरूरवस् got separated from उर्वशी. M. २४. १९.

कुमारवम्श|kumaaravamsha
--the son of Madhu, and father of Anu. Vi. IV. १२. ४२. [page१-398+ २६]

कुमारसम्भव|kumaarasambhava
--see तारकामय।

कुमारा|kumaaraa
--a R. from the शुक्तिमत् hill. Vi. II. 3. १४.

कुमारी|kumaarii
 (I)--a daughter of ललिता aged nine, and train- ed in military art. Attacked and slew all the sons of भण्ड to the joy of the शक्ति troops; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. २६. ७३-117.{{/F}} goddess enshrined at माया- पुरी. {{F}}2:  M. १३. ३४.{{/F}}

कुमारि|kumaari
 (II)--Cape Comorin, fit for श्राद्ध offerings. Br. II. १६. ११; III. १३. २८.

कुमारी|kumaarii
 (III)--a R. from the शुक्तिमत् hill. Br. II. १६. ३८; M. १६३. ८६.

कुमारी|kumaarii
 (IV) (सिद्धा)--a R. of शाकद्वीप. Br. II. १९. ९६; वा. ४५. ८१; ४९. ९२; Vi. II. 4. ६५.

कुमारी|kumaarii
 (V)--noted for चन्द्रतीर्थ. वा. ७७. २८.

कुमारीपुरम्|kumaariipuram
--a part of an artificial fortress (कृत्- रिम)। Br. II. 7. १०३-4.

कुमुञ्ज|kumunja
--Mt. king of hills, to the east of अरुणोद; {{F}}1:  वा. ३६. १८; ३७. 1.{{/F}} eight cities of the दानवस् located in. {{F}}2:  Ib. ३९. २८-9.{{/F}}

कुमुथि|kumuthi
--a ऋत्विक् at ब्रह्मा's sacrifice. वा. १०६. ३४. [page१-399+ २९]

कुमुद|kumuda
 (I)--an attendant on Hari. {{F}}1:  भा. VII. 8. ३८-39; XI. २७. २८.{{/F}} Attacked Asura followers of Bali. {{F}}2:  Ib. VIII. २१. १६.{{/F}}

कुमुद|kumuda
 (II)--a disciple of Pathya. भा. XII. 7. 2.

कुमुद|kumuda
 (III)--a chief वानर. Br. III. 7. २४२.

कुमुद|kumuda
 (IV)--a son of इरावती. Br. III. 7. २९२.

कुमुद|kumuda
 (V)--a नाग from चान्द्रमस Sa1ma. Br. III. 7. ३४५.

कुमुद|kumuda
 (VI)--a son of मणिवर. वा. ६९. १६०.

कुमुद|kumuda
 (VII)--a son of बृहती. वा. ९६. २४७.

कुमुद|kumuda
 (VIII)--a Mt. on one side of Meru west of शितोद. Here is the celestial Banian Tree शतबलू's from which flow rivers to निलावृत. The tree would yield what- ever was desired of it. {{F}}1:  भा. V. १६. ११ and २४; वा. ३६. २८; ३८. ४५; ४२. ५१.{{/F}} One of the seven hills of शाल्मलद्वीप. {{F}}2:  Br. II. १९. ३५; वा. ४९. ३२-3; Vi. II. 4. २६.{{/F}} Residence of the Kinnaras. {{F}}3:  Vi. ३९. ५९.{{/F}}

कुमुद|kumuda
 (IX)--a Mt. in कुशद्वीप. M. १२२. ५२.

कुमुद|kumuda
 (X)--a Mt. in Gomedaka. M. १२३. 3. [page१-400+ २५]

कुमुद|kumuda
 (XI)--a चक्रवाक in मानस; a son of Kau- शिक in previous birth. M. २०. १८.

कुमुद|kumuda
 (XII)--one of the eight निधिस् of Kubera. वा. ४१. १०.

कुमुदस्|kumudas
--a Janapada of the Bhadra continent. वा. ४३. २१.

कुमुदद्युति|kumudadyuti
--a नाग from चान्द्रमस साम। Br. III. 7. ३४५.

कुमुदद्वीप|kumudadviipa
--a region of भारतवर्ष; (कुश) described. वा. ४८. १४. ३४-5.

कुमुदा|kumudaa
 (I)--a name of योगमाय; the goddess enshrined in मानस. भा. X. 2. १२; M. १३. २७.

कुमुदा|kumudaa
 (II)--the wily sister of महादेव in the isle of Kumuda. वा. ४८. ३५.

कुमुदाक्ष|kumudaaxa
 (I)--an attendant on Hari. Attacked Asura followers of Bali. See कुमुदाक्षण. भा. VIII. २१. १६; XI. २७. २८.

कुमुदाक्ष|kumudaaxa
 (II)--an यक्ष and a son of देवयानि. Br. III. 7. १२९.

कुमुदादि|kumudaadi
--a pupil of Pathya. Br. II. ३५. ५९; वा. ६१. ५२; Vi. III. 6. ११. [page१-401+ २६]

कुमुदाभस्|kumudaabhas
--a Janapada of the केतुमाल country. वा. ४४. १२.

कुमुदिनी|kumudinii
--one of the four queens of भण्ड. Br. IV. १२. १३.

कुमुदेक्षन|kumudexana
--see कुम्दाक्ष।

कुमुद्वती|kumudvatii
 (I)--a R. in क्रौञ्चद्वीप. Br. II. १९. ७५; M. १२२. ८८; वा. ४९. ६९; Vi. II. 4. ५५.

कुमुद्वती|kumudvatii
 (II)--a R. from the Vindhyas. Br. II. १६. ३३; M. ११४. २७; वा. ४५. १०२; ४७. 2.

कुमुन्द|kumunda
--(Mt.) a hill range on the east of Meru. Vi. II. 2. २७.

कुम्भ|kumbha
