--founded by Kuru and sacred to हरी. {{F}}1:  भा III. 3. १२; VII. १४. ३०; Vi. VI. 8. २९.{{/F}} Watered by the river सरस्वती. {{F}}2:  भा. IX. १४. ३३.{{/F}} Capital city of the Kurus. {{F}}3:  Ib. IX. २२. 4.{{/F}} Sages of कुरुक्षेत्र visited द्वारक. At कुरुक्षेत्र Kr2s2n2a performed sacrifices for twelve years. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ९०. २८[3], ४६[1].{{/F}} The battlefield where the पाण्डवस् fought with the Kurus led by Duryo- dhana. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ७८. [९५ (V) 9], [१८].{{/F}} Here परशुराम dug a lake called स्यमन्तपञ्- caka. {{F}}6:  Br. III. ४७. 2.{{/F}} On the occasion of a sacrifice सूत narrated the ब्र्। पुराण here. {{F}}7:  भा. I. 1. १७.{{/F}} पुरूरवस् met उर्वशी after their separa- tion at; the residence of सनत्कुमार and धर्मराज fit for श्राद्ध offerings, and sacred to पितृस्. Founded by Kuru, son of सम्वरण; {{F}}8:  III. १३. ६५ and ६८; ६६. १८; M. २२. १८; वा. ७७. ६४; ९१. ३१; ९९. २१५, २५९.{{/F}} residence of sage कौशिक, and sacrifice of अधिसीमकृष्ण for 2 years at; sacred in द्वा- para; {{F}}9:  M. २०. 2; ५०. २० and ६७; १०६. ४९ and ५७; १०९. 3; १८०. ५५; १८४. १६.{{/F}} धर्मक्षेत्र where a great sacrifice was per- [page१-407+ ३०] formed. {{F}}१०:  वा. 1. १४; ५९. १०७.{{/F}} Residence at, leads to मुक्ति; no shaving or उप- वास required here. {{F}}११:  Ib. १०५. १६ and २५.{{/F}} Noted for अम्भोजसरस् or lotus tank. {{F}}१२:  Vi. IV-१९. ७७.{{/F}} R. सरस्वती flows here: noted for a temple of वामन. {{F}}१३:  M. १८६. १०; १९२. १२; २४४. 3.{{/F}}

