गन्गा|gangaa
 (I)--a R. source of, sacred to Hari; {{F}}1:  भा. VII. १४. २९, VIII. 4. २३, Br. II. १६. ११, २४.{{/F}} brought to the earth from Heaven; a महानदी from the Himalayas. {{F}}2:  वा. ४२. ३९-49: ७१. 5.{{/F}} Originating from the foot of विष्णु and watering the region of the moon falls from heaven into ब्रह्मा's city; issuing from the nail of the great toe of Hari's left foot; Dhruva holds her in his crown; the seven sages perform austerities with her waters; issuing again from the moon she falls on Sumeru and thence to the four quarters of the earth; hearing of her, the desire to go to गन्गा, see, touch, bathe in her waters--all purify a person; falling in four directions, takes the names of शीता, अलकनन्दा, चक्षु and भद्रा. {{F}}3:  वी. I. 9. १०३: II, 2. ३३४: 8. १०८-13, १२०-2: III. १४. १८ IV. 4. २६-30: १८-28.{{/F}} Effort made by अम्शुमान्, दिलीप and भगीरथ and hence her name भागीरथी. Held up by Hara and then let; flowed in seven streams through several territories in the four directions, sanctifying the regions and the people there. {{F}}4:  भा. IX. 9. 1-१३: Br. III. १३. ११८: ५५. ५१: ५६. ३८-54.{{/F}} Its waters drunk by Janhu, and let out by his ears and hence called जान्हवी. {{F}}5:  भा. IX. १५. 3: Br. III. ६६. २५-6: ७३. ११७: M. १२. ४४: १२१. २६.{{/F}} The seed cast off by शिव in the [page१-502+ ४८] sky was borne by गन्गा and was swallowed by Agni; phoetus left on the Himalayan slopes became gold, which was utilised in building the यग्ञशाल at नैमिष. At her confluence with यमुना (s.v.) was the अवभृत of the sacri- fice of प्रजापतिस्. On its banks Bharata performed horse- sacrifice. {{F}}6:  भा. IV. 7. ६३-4: वा. 2. १७-18: ७२. २८-32. Br. II. १६. ११ and २४. भा. VII. १४. २९; VIII. 4. २३ Va1. ४२. ३९-40: ७१. 5. भा. IX. 9. 1-१३. Br. III. १३. ११८: ५५.51: ५६. ३८-54. M. १५. 3. Br. III. ६६. २५. 6: ७३. ११७: M. १२. ४४: १२१. २६. भा. IV. 7. ६३-64. वा. 2. १७-18: ७२. २८-32. भा. IV. 2. ३५. IX. २०-25: २२. १९: X. १०. 4.{{/F}} Here युधिष्ठिर had his अवभृत bath after राजसूय. {{F}}7:  भा. X. ७५. १९.{{/F}} Here were done funeral rites of the dead children of द्रौपदी. {{F}}8:  Ib. I. 8. 1.{{/F}} Here again परीक्षित् observed vow of fasting unto death. {{F}}9:  Ib. 3. ४३; 4. १०; १२. २८; १८. 3.{{/F}} Visited by बलराम. {{F}}१०:  Ib. X. ७८. २०.{{/F}} The Sagaras sent to heaven by the Ganges waters. {{F}}११:  Ib. IX. 9. १४.{{/F}} गन्गा as देवी. {{F}}१२:  Ib. I. १९. १५.{{/F}} Originally of three-fold path, the छायापथा being in the नक्षत्रमण्डल; {{F}}१३:  Br. II. १८. २६-42, ५०-52:{{/F}} addressed by Agni to bear Rudra's गर्भ, गन्गा accepted the task and gave birth to कुमार. {{F}}१४:  Br. III. 7. ३५५: 9. 4: १०. ३०-5: १४. ८४: ३७. 5: ५४. ४९: IV. 9. ७८.{{/F}} गन्गा refilled the ocean, after Agastya drank it dry. {{F}}१५:  Br. III. ६३. १६७.{{/F}} Manu put the growing fish in; washed off the city of हस्तिनापुरम्; contains 3(1/2) crores of तीर्थस्; forms the cure for all ills; released in seven streams by शन्कर, three to the west, three to the north and one भगीरथी, sacred in Kanakhala. {{F}}१६:  M. 1. २३: १३. २५: ३६. 5: ५०. ७८: १०२. 5-6: १०६. ५७-8; ११४. २०: १२१. ३८-41; १३३. २३: १८३. १०७: १८६. १०; १९२. ११; २३९-18.{{/F}} Wife of the ocean; {{F}}१७:  वा. १३. ३५: ३०. ३२ and ९२: ४५. ९५:{{/F}} त्रिपथगा; {{F}}१८:  वा. 2. 7; ५१. २१, ४६; ५८. ८८.{{/F}} a consort of शिव, served by Trayambaka and other gods. {{F}}१९:  वा. ४२. ३९-40: ७१. 5.{{/F}} Fit for श्राद्ध; {{F}}२०:  वा. ७७. ६८.{{/F}} the right side of the Veda; {{F}}२१:  वा. ९८. ११७: ९९. ६३: १०४. १३, २७, ७७: १०६. ६७: १११. १६.{{/F}} particularly sacred at three spots--गन्गाद्वार, प्रयाग and गन्गा sa1gara-sangama. {{F}}२२:  M. १०६. ५३.{{/F}} [page१-503+ २५]

