 (IV)--a son of Nakta and Druti: A राजऋषि and an अम्श of Hari; a महापुरुष who ruled his kingdom righteously and with devotion to Hari. His name is sung in an ancient गाथा, as the upholder of धर्म, Vedas, ब्रह्मणस् and यज्ञस्. His queen was गायन्ती who was mother of three sons Citraratha and others. At the end of [page१-515+ २७] his rule, he renounced the throne and sought refuge with Hari. भा. V. १५. 6-१४: X. ६०. ४१: Br. II. १४. ६८: वा. ३३. ५७. Vi. II. 1. ३८.

गय|gaya
 (V)--though lord of seven द्वीपस्, he was not content. He wanted more territory. भा. VIII. १९. २३; XII. 3. १०.

गय|gaya
 (VI)--a son of (इला) Sudyumna and Lord of Dak- षिणापथ; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 1. ४१. M. १२. १७.{{/F}} king of the eastern kingdom with its capital Gaya; {{F}}2:  Br. III. ६०. १८.{{/F}} a राजऋषि. {{F}}3:  वा. ८५. १९.{{/F}} Performed a big sacrifice and gave lavish gifts to all ब्रह्मणस्; even gods were pleased and granted a boon perpetuating his name by a city गयापुरि; attained विष्णुलोक. {{F}}4:  वा. ११२. 1-6.{{/F}}

गय|gaya
 (VII)--a son of Angirasa and ऊरु. M. 4. ४३.

गय|gaya
 (VIII)--a son of बलकाश्व. वा. ९१. ६१.

गयन्ती|gayantii
--(गायन्ती-ब्र्। प्।), wife of Gaya (s.v.) and mother of three sons. भा. V. १५. १४.

गयशिरस्|gayashiras
--sacred to Hari. भा. VII. १४. ३०.

गया|gayaa
 (I)--a R. visited by बलराम. भा. X. ७९. ११. [page१-516+ ३५]

गया|gayaa
 (II)--(च्) the kingdom of; sacred for श्राद्ध offering. धर्मपृष्ट, Brahmasaras, and गृध्रवट are chief places here; capital of Gaya; परशुरान performed श्राद्ध here. {{F}}1:  M. १२. १७. Br. III. १३. १०४: १९-11: ४७. १७: ६०. १९: वा. ८५. १९.{{/F}} A पितृतीर्थम् being the residence of पितामह; a गाथा says that any one son may visit गया and satisfy all पितृस्. {{F}}2:  M. २२. 4-6 and २६: ११०. 2; १९२. ११: २०४. 8: २०७. ४०.{{/F}} Fit for श्राद्ध; a man devoted to गयाश्राद्ध must dress himself in beggar's garments, circumambulate the ग्राम, and the next one with shaving and begging money; श्राद्ध in ब्रह्मकुण्ड and other places; going to Dhar- maranya after worshipping गदाधर; feed the Brahmans there without enquiring into their family, conduct or learn- ing; offer पिण्डस् in गयारूप, even for unknown cognates and names; पिण्ड for one's own self with तिल; by this even heinous crimes are mitigated; a superior तीर्थ; best in Makara, eclipses of the sun and moon, and Caitra and Preta- पक्ष (महालय); others are अधीमास, birthday, the even- ing of Guru and शुक्र, the stay of बृहस्पति in Simha which is once in twelve years. {{F}}3:  वा. ७७. ९७: ८०. ४५: ८३. १२-44.{{/F}} The face of the Veda; {{F}}4:  Ib. १०४. ७७.{{/F}} शम्भु, विष्णु and Ravi; sacred to Gaya. {{F}}5:  Ib. ११२. २०.{{/F}}

गया|gayaa
 (III)--six in number, गायागय, गयादित्य, गायत्री, गदाधर, गया, गयासुर, all tending to salva- tion. वा. ११२. ६०.

गयाकूट|gayaakuuTa
--in गया. वा. ११२. ५२.

गयाख्यानम्|gayaakhyaanam
--the legend about गया. वा. ११२. ६२, ६७. [page१-517+ ३५]

गयातीर्थम्|gayaatiirtham
--origin of; the austerities of गयासूर here bearing a stone on his head. Here गदाधर stood steadfast lest he should move; on this ब्रह्मा performed a sacrifice; shaving and fasting are prescribed in तीर्थस् but not for this place; measurement 2(1/2) क्रोश; गयाक्षेत्रम् 5 क्रोशस् and गयाशिर 1 क्रोश, the best of all तीर्थस्. वा. १०५. 4-४६.

गयादित्य|gayaaditya
--the north sun. वा. १०९. २१.

गयापुरि|gayaapuri
--after the name of king Gaya. वा. ११२. 5.

गयायात्रा|gayaayaatraa
--pilgrimage to गया; preliminaries; per- formance of श्राद्ध, going round the village, travel to another village and so on, every day without begging food, etc.: purity and selflessness to be maintained; reaching गया, bathing and performance of श्राद्ध according to his Veda शाख; the next day visit to Pretaparvata, bath in ब्रह्मकुण्ड and the offer of पिण्डस् in other places. See गय। वा. ११०. 1-9.

गयाशिर|gayaashira
--one क्रोश in extent; {{F}}1:  वा. १०५. २९.{{/F}} श्राद्ध there lifts १०० generations. {{F}}2:  Ib. १०५. ३१.{{/F}}

गयाश्राद्धम्|gayaashraaddham
--one of the four means to mukti; {{F}}1:  वा. १०५. १६.{{/F}} special वर्ण to mother; {{F}}2:  Ib. १०८. ३५: ११०. १७.{{/F}} for पिण्ड; {{F}}3:  Ib. २३. ५९.{{/F}} suitable occasions for. {{F}}4:  Ib. १०५. ४७-8.{{/F}}

गयासुर|gayaasura
--had a stone over his head on which ब्रह्मा performed sacrifices; Gaya perforhmed याग in श्वेतकल्प- वाराह; after him the name for the place; the son who goes to गया, he who resides at गया for three पक्षस् [page१-518+ ४२] purifies seven descendants; or residence at least for १५, 7 or 3 days; one offers पिण्ड with तिल to forefathers and to oneself; the four heinous offences are expiated with the ritual at गया. Out of the navel of विष्णु came ब्रह्मा who created Asuras one of whom was Gaya, १२५ yojanas in length and ६० in breadth; a वैष्नव; performed तपस् at कोलाहल hill for १००० of years; {{F}}1:  {{/F}} all gods went to विष्णु. गयासुर with whom विष्णु was pleased was granted his request, to be the best of all; Yamapuri became vacant; all went to ब्रह्मा and he went to विष्णु; on the latter's advice ब्रह्मा went to गया and wanted to perform याग on his body; a true devotee, Gaya agreed readily. But finding him un- stable ब्रह्मा ordered Dharma to place a stone on his head and the devas to stand to maintain balance; विष्नु was again approached who gave his मूर्ति and finding Gaya still un- stable गदाधर himself took his stand and made the stone motionless. Pleased, विष्णु gave him what he desired. It was that they should all live there and that the people who did rites there must reach Brahmaloka. See गया ti1rtham. वा. १०५. 5-१३. ch. १०६. (whole): १०८. 8: १०९. १३.

गरिमा|garimaa
--a सिद्धिदेवी. Br. IV. १९. 4: ३६. ५१.

गरिष्ट|gariShTa
--a दानव. Br. III. 6. १६.

गरुड (गरुत्मत्)|garuDa (garutmat)
 (I)--a son of तार्क्ष्य (काश्यप) and विनता (सुपर्णा), and vehicle of Hari. {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. २२: III. १९. ११. Br. III. 7. २९: 8. ११. M. 6. ३४: १४६. २२. वा. ४९. १०; ६९. ६६: ७०. ११: ७२. ४५. Vi. I. २१. १८.{{/F}} Has abode in शाल्मलिद्वीप. {{F}}2:  भा. V. २०. 8.{{/F}} Took कृष्ण to Madhuvana; {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. 9. 1.{{/F}} Identified with Hari, and regarded as the embodiment of the Vedas. {{F}}4:  Ib. VI 8. २९. VIII. 3. ३१.{{/F}} Attacked Asura followers of Bali, and knowing Hari's mind, he bound Bali with cords of वरुण. {{F}}5:  Ib. VIII. २१. १६ and २६.{{/F}} Serves as a watch for क्षीरोद. When he saw Bali carrying away Hari's crown-jewel, he pursued him and recovered it after a fight. When he saw on his return from Gomanta, he placed it on His [page१-519+ ४६] head and belauded him, requesting him for opportunities of service to Him, who ordered him to go back and come whenever He thought of him. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ५३ (V) १०-19.{{/F}} His winning nectar is com- pared to कृष्ण winning वैदर्भी in स्वयम्वर। {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ५२. १७.{{/F}} कालीय, the enemy of snakes, freed from fear of; entered into an agreement with snakes of रमणक to give him बलि every fortnight. कालीय failed to do this, and after a fight escaped to the river कालिन्दी where गरुड could not go, as he was under a curse. It happened once that गरुड took a king- fish from the river against the wish of the sage Saubhari who cursed that गरुड's coming again there would mean the end of his life. {{F}}8:  Ib. १६. ६३; १७. 1-११. Vi. V. 7. ७८.{{/F}} Attacked by Mura, {{F}}9:  भा. X. ५९. 7-8.{{/F}} killed all elephants of Naraka, {{F}}१०:  Ib. ५९. १९. Vi. V. २९. १४.{{/F}} carried कृष्ण to Indra's city. Defeated वरुण attacking कृष्ण, flung शिव and his bull to a distance of a hundred धनुस्। Discomfited ऐरावत of Indra, and took कृष्ण and सत्यभामा safely to द्वारका. {{F}}११:  भा. ६५ (V) 1: ६६ (V) २२-25, ४८; ६७ (V) ११-14, ३८-39, M. १५०. २१९ Vi. V. ३०. ६४-70. XI. ३०. ४४.{{/F}} गरुड standard of Hari. {{F}}१२:  Br. III. ७१. २४८.{{/F}} Praise of Hari. {{F}}१३:  भा. IV. ३०. 6. XI. २७. २८.{{/F}} Took nectar for mother's sake to Somaka hill of प्लक्ष; married five daughters of ताम्र and became father of birds in all the world. {{F}}१४:  Br. II. १९. ११-12: III. 7. ४४८-51: M. १२२. १५.{{/F}} Younger brother of अरुण. {{F}}१५:  M. १५०-53.{{/F}} Worship of, on the भी- मद्वादशि, and in the लक्ष homa of Grahabali. Icon of. {{F}}१६:  M. ५३. ४१; ६९. २६; ९३. ९९: २५८. ११ and १२.{{/F}} In the तारकामय: in the war with कालनेमी: performed tapas at Kanakhala. {{F}}१७:  M. १५२. 6-7, ३६: १५३. १८१: १७१. ५०: १७८. ३२ and ५०: १९३. ७०: २४९. ३५{{/F}} had a number of wives, sons and grandsons; the eater of all cruel snakes--his descendants spread over largely the whole of शाल्मलिद्वीप, and the mountains देवकूट, मणिमन्त, सहस्रशिखर, Parna- mala, सुकेश, and सतश्रुग, the five-peaked Kauraja, हेमकूट etc. {{F}}१८:  वा. ६९. ३२८-335.{{/F}} [page१-520+ ३०]

गरुड|garuDa
 (II)--a son of विश्वेशा. M. १७१. ५०.

