 (I)--a son of (Bhuva) Manyu and father of शिनि, (Chini). M. ४९. ३६: Vi. IV. १९. २१-23.

गर्ग|garga
 (II)--the Purohita of यादवस्. Urged by Vasudeva, he went to the Vraja of Nanda who welcomed him as befitted a Guru, praising him as the great author of ज्योतिष s4a1stra. Requested by Nanda to do नाम सम्स्कार to कृष्ण and राम without कंश's knowledge, he did so and returned to his place. {{F}}1:  भा. X. 8. 1-२०. Vi. II. 5. २६: V. 6. 8. 9.{{/F}} He held कृष्ण and राम to be divine incarnations. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ४६. २३.{{/F}} He informed Nanda that कृष्ण was the son of Vasudeva and an अम्श of नारायण. {{F}}3:  Ib. २६. १५-23.{{/F}} He officiated at उपनयन सम्स्कारस् of the two brothers. {{F}}4:  Ib. ४५. २६-29.{{/F}} He had also informed Mucukunda that नारायण was to be born on [page१-521+ २६] the earth as कृष्ण. {{F}}5:  Ib. ५१. ४५.{{/F}} He was invited for the राजसूय of युधिष्ठिर. {{F}}6:  Ib. ७४. 8.{{/F}}

