गर्भ|garbha
 (II)--the child in embryo; {{F}}1:  भा. III. ३१. 1-१०. वा. ९७. ४६-57.{{/F}} a union of शुक्र-- springing from मज्ज which is from bone which is due to मेदस्, which again results from flesh, that is due to शोणितम्, emerging from Rasa or waters, शुक्र constitutes of Soma and सोणितम् of अग्नी. The former resides in Kaphavarga and the latter in Pittavarga. The place of कफ is heart, and that of पित्त is the navel region. Stages in the गर्भ and formation described. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ७२. ४५-57. वा. १४. १८-26.{{/F}} [page१-523+ २७]

