जनमेजय|janamejaya
 (I)--the first of the four sons of परीक्षित् and इरावती. {{F}}1:  भा. I. १६. 2; Br. III. ६८. २०.{{/F}} Father of शतानीक. {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. २०. 1; २१. 2-3.{{/F}} Finding that the death of his father was predicted to be by the snake तक्षक, he per- formed a सर्प याग to destroy all snakes. All except Tak- [page१-624+ ३२] षक came, the latter being sheltered by Indra. At this Tak- षक and Indra were invoked together. Advised by बृहस्- pati to refrain from the cruel याग, Janamejaya agreed; with the aid of Tura, the priest, he performed अश्वमेध and other sacrifices; {{F}}3:  भा. IX. २२. ३५-38; XII. 6. १६-28; M. 6. ४२.{{/F}} cursed by वैशम्पायन he made याज्ञ- valkya his ब्रह्मा in a sacrifice. {{F}}4:  M. ५०. ५७-60.{{/F}} Introduced वाजसने- yaka and became known as Trikharvi. {{F}}5:  वा. ९९. २२९, २५०-4.{{/F}} Put to trouble Loha- gandha, the son of गार्ग्य out for mischief and was cursed by गार्ग्य. {{F}}6:  Ib. ९३. २१.{{/F}} King of सुदेश and a Kaurava; highly righte- ous. After anointing his son on the throne he went into the woods for penance. {{F}}7:  M. ५०. ६१-5.{{/F}}

