जम्कारिणि|jamkaariNi
--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ४४. ८७.

जम्ब|jamba
--a सुधर्मान God. Br. IV. 1. ६०.

जम्बु|jambu
--the tree at इलावृतम् in the हिमालयस्. Br. II. १७. १२; १९. २९; III. २२. ३७; २७. १७; IV. ४३. १७.

जम्बुक|jambuka
--a son of आप. वा. ६९. ३०.

जम्बुकाक्ष|jambukaaxa
--a commander of भण्ड to aid विषङ्ग; was killed by नीलपताका. Br. IV. २१. ८०; २५. २९, ९८.

जम्बुला|jambulaa
--a R. of the भारतवर्ष. वा. ४५. १००.

जम्बू|jambuu
--(जाम्बूनदम्) a river of juice of celestial roseapple tree flowing from the top of Merumandara into इलावृत. The earth on its two banks yields fine gold जाम्बू- nada from which jewels are made in heaven; source of जम्बु; {{F}}1:  भा. V. १६. १९-20; वा. ३५. २६-30.{{/F}} R. from Candraprabha {{F}}2:  Br. II. १८. ६९.{{/F}} in colour like a butterfly. {{F}}3:  वा. ४६. ३०.{{/F}}

जम्बू (जम्बूद्वीप)|jambuu (jambuudviipa)
--occupies the central position of the globe in the form of a lotus leaf, in extent a १००,000 yojanas. There are nine continents demarcated by moun- tain ranges. In the middle is situated इलावृत, at whose middle portion stands Meru. Some say that eight extra [page१-630+ ३८] countries were attached to it by the sons of Sagara who dug into the earth on all sides in search of sacrificial horse. This द्वीप is surrounded by salt sea. {{F}}1:  भा. I. १२. 5; V. 1. ३२; १६. 5-7; १९. २९-30; २०. 2; M. ८३. ३२; ११३. 7; १२२. 2; २८४. 2; वा. ११. ८४; ३३. ११ and ४५; ch. ३४. Vi. II. 3. २८.{{/F}} Contains many जनपदस्, cities, mountains, rivers, nine भुवनस्, salt ocean, six वर्षपर्वतस् and two oceans--east and west. Divided into nine parts among the sons of आग्नीध्र; {{F}}2:  Br. II. १७. २४, ३०; १५. 8 to the end; १४. ११, ४३ and ५२; Vi. II. 1. १२; 2. २३-25.{{/F}} from the जम्बु tree. {{F}}3:  वा. ४६. २५.{{/F}}

जम्बूद्वीप|jambuudviipa
--people of, described. See जम्बू. वा. ४६. २५-37.

जम्बूनदी|jambuunadii
