जम्भ(क)|jambha(ka)
 (I)--father of कयाधू, and chief of Asuras. Took part in the 6th देवासुर war between Bali and Indra. Fought with वृषा-Kapi. Hearing that Bali had fallen dead Jambha riding on a lion attacked Indra and dis- abled his elephant. He then turned towards मातलि who brought a chariot to Indra's aid. But his head was cut off by Indra's वज्र। {{F}}1:  भा. VI. १८. १२; VIII. १०. २१-32; ११. १३-18; Br. III. 6. १०; ७२. ८१ and १०५; वा. ९७. १०३.{{/F}} Led तारक's army in a chariot of १०० lions; fought with Yama, Kubera, जनार्दन and others but was finally killed. {{F}}2:  M. ४७. ७२; १४८. ४२-54; chh १५०-53; २४५. १२. Vi. IV. 6. १४; V. १४. १४.{{/F}} [page१-631+ २७]

जम्भ|jambha
