त्वरितायु|tvaritaayu
--a son of Bhauma. M. ५०. ३६.

त्वष्ट (त्वष्ट्रि)|tvaShTa (tvaShTri)
--a son of Aditi, and an आदित्य. {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. ३९; III. 6. १५; M. 6. 4; १७१. ५६; वा. ६६. ६६; Vi. I. १५. १३०.{{/F}} Presented पृथु with a good chariot. {{F}}2:  भा. IV. १५. १७.{{/F}} His wife was रचना, [page२-056+ ४९] and sons were Sannivasa and विश्वरूप (s.v.); {{F}}3: Ib. VI. 6. ४४.{{/F}} when the latter was lost, he offered a sacrifice to destroy Indra. From the fire rose a dreadful figure known as वृत्र. The Gods were frightened and prayed to Hari. The lord revealed Him- self and asked them to meet the sage दध्यञ्ज with whose support वृत्र could be vanquished. दध्यञ्ज initiated them into नारायणवर्म; {{F}}4: Ib. VI. 9. (whole).{{/F}} was propitiated by An- giras for blessing चित्राक्ष with a son. {{F}}5: Ib. VI. १४. २७.{{/F}} His con- templation. {{F}}6: Ib. XI. १५. २०.{{/F}} The name of the Sun in the month of इष (आश्विन). {{F}}7:  Ib. XII. ११. ४३. वा. ५२. २०; Vi. II. 1. ४०; १०. १६.{{/F}} (माघ and फाल्गुन) (वा। प्। and वि। प्।) Fought with शम्बर in the देवासुर war. {{F}}8: Ib. XI. १२. 5; VIII. १०. २९.{{/F}} Out of the तेजस् came विष्णु's cakra, Indra's vajra, and Rudra's शूलम्; all limbs except the feet of Vivasvan were operated upon, and hence feet अमन्गल and not to be worshipped; pre- sented कुमार with a hen that could assume any form at will. {{F}}9: M. ११. 3. २२-32; १५९. १०.{{/F}}

त्वष्टा|tvaShTaa
 (I)--one of the four sons of शुक्र; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 1. ७८, ८६; वा. ६५. ७७, ८५; Vi. I. १५. १२१.{{/F}} married यशोधरा--वैरोचिनी, daughter of Virocana; father of त्रिशिर, विश्वरूप and विश्वकर्म; {{F}}2:  Br. III. १४. 6; ५९. १७.{{/F}} प्रह्रादी, another wife; सम्ज्ञा, a daughter of his, was given in marriage to the Sun God; {{F}}3:  Ib. II. २४. ३४, ३९.{{/F}} an आदित्य in the month of कार्त्तिक having ८००० rays; {{F}}4:  Ib. II. २३. २०.{{/F}} with the शिशिर Sun; {{F}}4:  Ib. II. २३. २०.{{/F}} reduced the Sun's तेजस्; {{F}}5:  Ib. III. ५९. ४४ and ६५.{{/F}} made विष्णु's discus; {{F}}6:  Ib. III. ५९. ७१, ८२.{{/F}} fell down on the earth for having drunk the Soma of शचिपति. {{F}}7:  वा. ७८. 6; ९४. ५६.{{/F}}

त्वष्टा|tvaShTaa
 (II)--a son of Manasyu. Vi. II. 1. ४०.

त्वष्टा|tvaShTaa
 (III)--the son of Bhauvana and दूषणा. His queen was विरोचना, and their son विरजा. भा. V. १५. १५. Br. II. १४. ७०. वा. ३३. ५९. [page२-057+ २१]

