दुर्वास|durvaasa
 (I)--a son of Atri and an younger brother of दत्तात्रेय; {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 1. १५; Br. III. 8. ८२; वा. ७०. ७६.{{/F}} an अम्श of शिव; {{F}}2:  भा. IV. 1. ३३.{{/F}} appeared before अम्बरीष who was about to break his द्वादसि fast; agreed to accept his hospitality, went to the river for bath and tarried there; finding the मुहूर्त for पारण (break-fast) drawing to a close, the king broke his fast with some water. Coming to know of this on his return, the sage produced a flaming spirit to attack him. But Hari's चक्र burnt it down and turned towards the sage, who ran for succour to ब्रह्मा, शिव and विष्णु. All of them were unable to help; but Hari advised him to meet अम्बरीष and apologise to him. {{F}}3:  Ib. IX. 4. ३५-71.{{/F}} This he did and was set at liberty. After partaking the meals with him, he returned to Brahmaloka; {{F}}4:  Ib. IX. 5. 1-२२.{{/F}} blessed पृथ with secret मन्त्रस् to summon gods. {{F}}5:  Ib. IX. २४. ३२; XI. 1. १२.{{/F}} Through him Duryodhana planned to destroy the पाण्डवस् by inciting him to go to them and ask for a feast. But कृष्ण protected them on the occasion. {{F}}6:  Ib. I. १५. ११.{{/F}} In the course of his sojourn he met a विद्या- [page२-106+ २३] dhara maid with a garland given to her by the देवी; took it from her and presented it to Indra who put it on his elephant, who in turn threw it on the ground and trampled upon it. Enraged at this, the sage cursed him to be lost to all fortune. {{F}}7:  Ib. VIII. 5. १६; Br. IV. 5. १६-20; 9. ३१; ४०. १२०.{{/F}}

