 (I)--(देवकभोजपुत्री Suna1ma1) a Bhoja princess; a daughter of Devaka, one of the wives of Vasu- deva and mother of eight sons of whom कृष्ण was one, all of them comparable to the eight Vasus; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 1. १२; III. 1. ३३; 2. २५; IX. २४. २३, ४५, ५३; X. 1. 8 and २९; ३६. १७; Br. I. 1. १२५; M. ४४. ७३; ४६. १३-15; ४७. 2; वा. 1. १४८; ९६. १६३, १७२-4; Vi. IV. १४. १८; १५. १८. २६-30.{{/F}} oppressed by Kamsa and relieved by कृष्ण; was about to be murdered by Kamsa who heard a divine voice that her eighth child would be the cause of his end; on Vasudeva's assurance to give up the babies as they were born she was allowed to go. Her first child कीर्तिमत् was taken to Kamsa who returned the baby. She was imprisoned with Vasudeva to watch over the birth of her sons. During her seventh pregnancy the धाम of Hari in her womb was transferred by योगमाया to that of रोहिणी and it was said that देवकी aborted. Then the अम्श of Hari entered her womb and she grew beautiful every day. ब्रह्मा, शिव and other Gods waited on her on the eve of कृष्ण's birth and said that her son was to kill [page२-114+ ३८] Kamsa: addressed the new-born कृष्ण. In the स्वायम्- bhuva epoch she was पृश्नि and Vasudeva was Sutapa. In another epoch she was Aditi and Vasudeva was कश्यप. यशोदा's daughter exchanged for देवकी's son and Kamsa was told of the birth of a girl; was released from prison along with Vasudeva; forgave and advised Kamsa; was saluted by कृष्ण and राम. {{F}}2:  भा. X. Chh. 1-4; ४४. ५०-51; ४५. 1-१२; भा. I. 8. २३. ३३; ११. २८; X. ३६. २०; ४३. २४. Vi. V. 2. 2; 4. १४; १८. 7-8.{{/F}} युधिष्ठिर asked Arjuna about her welfare. {{F}}3:  भा. I. १४. २७.{{/F}} कृष्ण's respects to, after his return from Indra's abode. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. [६७ (V) ४८].{{/F}} देवकी came to रुक्मिणी's palace with Vasudeva and कृष्ण; {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ५५. ३५.{{/F}} felt concerned at कृष्ण not returning from the cave of जाम्ब- वान् and aided by others prayed to दुर्गा for कृष्ण's return; {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ५६. ३४-5.{{/F}} wondered at the discourses between Nimi and the sages, sons of ऋषभ; {{F}}7:  Ib. XI. 5. ५१.{{/F}} embraced यशोदा at स्यमन्तपञ्चक and enquired after her welfare; {{F}}8:  Ib. X. ८२. ३७.{{/F}} praised कृष्ण and राम and desired to see her sons who had been killed by Kamsa; saw them with joy when taken back from Sutala by कृष्ण; in her presence they left for heaven. {{F}}9:  Ib. X. ८५. २७-33, ५२, ५६-70.{{/F}} Her grief at the decease of राम, कृष्ण and others; entered fire. {{F}}१०:  Ib. XI. ३१. १८; Vi. V. ३८. 4.{{/F}}

