नन्द(गोप)|nanda(gopa)
 (IV)--In previous birth the Vasu, द्रोण; {{F}}1:  भा. X. 8. ४८-50; Br. III. ७१. २३९.{{/F}} connected with the Devas, married यशोदा; {{F}}2:  भा. I. 8. २१; X. 1. ६२; 2. 9; Vi. IV. १५. ३१.{{/F}} celebrated the birth of कृष्ण as his son by inviting Brahmanas, Gopas and गोपीस् and making rich presents to them, the Gopas and गोपीस् threw balls of turmeric on the baby and sprinkled butter, curds and milk on one another, a folk custom; {{F}}3:  भा. X. 5. 1-१६; chh. 5. 6, 7 and 8 (whole),{{/F}} went to मथुरा to pay the annual tribute to Kamsa; was met by Vasudeva who advised him to leave at once for his place as he expected some उत्पातस् there: Nanda thinking Vasu- deva's words to be true turned his thoughts on the way to Hari; heard of पूतना, the demon killed by कृष्ण and felt greatly surprised; embraced कृष्ण in joy; performed शान्ति for कृष्ण for kicking the cart; was surprised at कृष्ण's taking the lap of तृणावर्त and believed more and more in Vasudeva's words; welcomed Garga and had नामकरण done to his sons; became pleased at Garga's service; {{F}}3:  भा. X. 5. 1-१६; chh. 5. 6, 7 and 8 (whole),{{/F}} Nanda and his friends bewildered at the fall of the Arjuna trees and released कृष्ण from his fetters; planned to leave Vraja for ब्रिन्दावन; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ११. 1-2; Vi. V. 5. 1-२१; 6. 6 and २१; 7. २२ and ३४; १०. १८ and २५.{{/F}} his fortune in enjoying Hari at close quarters; {{F}}5:  भा. X. १४. ३२.{{/F}} was much concerned at the bad omens at कृष्ण's fight with कालिय; was stopped by बलराम from entering the port of कालिय; joy at कृष्ण's escape from कालिय; gave presents of gold and cows to Brahmanas on the occasion. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. १६. १२-22; १७. १५-18.{{/F}} [page२-195+ ४३] Prepared for the इन्द्रयाग; but gave it up and prayed to the mountains instead, as advised by कृष्ण; Indra's anger towards Nanda; was surprised at कृष्ण holding the Govar- dhana; when the Gopas wondered at the exploits of the boy, कृष्ण, Nanda said that he heard from Garga that he was Vasudeva's son and an अम्श of नारायण; after fasting on एकादशि, Nanda went to यमुना for bath for the द्वादशि; it was आसुर time and not the time for bath; so an Asura follower of वरुण took hold of him and placed him before वरुण; seeing Nanda missing, the Gopas got frightened and appealed to कृष्ण who went to वरुण; pleased at seeing him वरुण said that it was a mistake committed by his servants in ignorance and set Nanda free; then he returned to Vraja to the great joy of all the Gopas; taken to Brahmah- rada; {{F}}7:  Ib. X. chh. २४, २५, २६, २७ and २८ (whole).{{/F}} when once he went to अम्बिकावन he was seized by a reptile and was released with कृष्ण's help. {{F}}8:  Ib. X. ३४. 4-१८; ३६. २४. (३१).{{/F}} Extended a hearty welcome to अक्रूर and enquired of Kamsa; became afraid of अक्रूर's message; got ready with all the Gopas to start for मथुरा with presents to Kamsa; followed अक्रूर's chariot with all his carts and men; came in advance and waited for कृष्ण's arrival; took his seat along with the other Gopas in the gallery of the wrestling ground; Kamsa desired to imprison him; duly honoured by कृष्ण, Nanda and the Gopas returned to Vraja after Kamsa's death; {{F}}9:  Ib. X. ३८. ४१-43; ३९. १०-12, ३५; ४१. 8; ४२. ३८; ४४. ३२; ४५. २०-25; Vi. V. ११. 3; १५. १८; २०. २८ and ८३.{{/F}} welcomed Uddhava with due honour; exhibited his deep love for कृष्ण; Uddhava revealed the real nature of कृष्ण to him. {{F}}१०:  भा. X. ४६. १४ to the end.{{/F}} Came to स्यमन्तपञ्चक and met कृष्ण and others; embraced and enquired after by Vasudeva and others; {{F}}११:  Ib. X. ५२. ३२-35.{{/F}} was honoured by कृष्ण, राम, Ugrasena and Vasudeva; spent three months unwilling to be away from the Yadus, left for मथुरा; {{F}}१२:  Ib. X. ८४. ५९-69.{{/F}} chief of सात्वतस् and vassal of कृष्ण: went with वृष्णिस् to बाण's city. {{F}}१३:  Ib. I. १४. ३२; II. 7. ३१; X. १३. 3.{{/F}} [page२-196+ २५]

