 (VI)--the son of उदासि, and a शैसु- नाग ruled for ४० years. (४२ years ब्र्। प्।). M. २७२. ११; वा. ९९. ३२०.

नन्दिवर्धन|nandivardhana
 (VII)--a son of Manivara; a यक्ष and a Guhyaka. वा. ६९. १५८.

नन्दिवर्धन|nandivardhana
 (VIII)--a son of Janaka and father of Nandi of the Pradyota dynasty. Vi. IV. २४. 6-7.

नन्दिवर्धन|nandivardhana
 (IX)--a son of Udayana and father of महानन्दि of the शैसनाभ dynasty. Vi. IV. २४. १७-8.

नन्दीश|nandiisha
--one of the eighteen authors on architecture. M. २५२. 3.

नन्दीश्वर|nandiishvara
--the god attendant on शिव; {{F}}1:  वा. ७७. ६३.{{/F}} the vehicle of Rudra; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ६३. 6.{{/F}} भगवान् with सूल; {{F}}3:  वा. ३०. ९१, ३१५.{{/F}} cursed दक्ष for his hatred of शिव; {{F}}4:  भा. IV. 2. २०-26.{{/F}} caught hold of Bhaga on the occasion of the destruction of Daksa's sacrifice; {{F}}5:  Ib. IV. 5. १७.{{/F}} his permission to see [page२-202+ २९] शिव; temple of, at स्वर्गमार्ग Prasa1da. {{F}}6:  Br. III. ३२. २३; १३. ६३-4; IV. ३०. ७५; ३४. ८९; ४१. २६ and ३०; ४३. ३०.{{/F}} Observed the vow सौभाग्यशयनम्; lord of a गण, versed in महेश्वर dharma; advised नारद to take to प्रयाग; the standard of शिव. {{F}}7:  M. ६०. ४९; ९५. 3; ११२. २१; १३२. १८; १३३. ६०-5.{{/F}} Fought with विद्युन्मालि in Tripuram; {{F}}8:  Ib. १३५. ४८ and ५३; १३६. ६८; १३८. ४४. १४०. २०-1.{{/F}} related to सनत्कुमार about the स्थानुत्वम् of शिव at Benares. {{F}}9:  Ib. १८१. 2; १८३. ६४; २४५. ८०. २६६. ४२. २७८. 9.{{/F}}

नन्देन्दु|nandendu
--ruled for १०० years. वा. ९९. ३३०.

नभ|nabha
 (I)--a son of निषध, and father of पुण्डरीक. भा. IX. १२. 1.

नभ|nabha
 (II)--a month sacred to Indra. भा. XII. ११. ३७.

नभ|nabha
 (III)--see प्रथक्वान्य; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १२. २३.{{/F}} fourfold अग्नि in ग्र- तद्वोच स्थानम्। {{F}}2:  वा. २९. २१.{{/F}}

नभ|nabha
 (IV)--a son of Nala and father of पुण्ड- रीक of the dynasty of कुश, son of राम, (नभा-ब्र्। प्। and वि। प्।). Br. III. ६३. २०२; M. १२. ५२. वा. ८८. २०२. Vi. IV. 4. १०६.

नभ|nabha
 (V)--a son of स्वारोचिष Manu. M. 9. 7

नभ|nabha
 (VI)--a son of Auttama Manu. M. 9. १२. [page२-203+ २९]

नभ|nabha
 (VII)--a Pravara ऋषि. M. १९९. १५.

नभ|nabha
 (VIII)--a मन्त्रकृत्. वा. ५९. ९७.

नभ|nabha
 (IX)--a son of Vipracitti. Vi. I. २१. ११.

नभग|nabhaga
--a son of Vaivasvata Manu and father of नाभाग. भा. VIII. १३. 2; IX. 1. १२; 4. 1. Br. III. ६३. 5; वा. ८८. 5.

नभश्री|nabhashrii
--a queen of वऋषऋतु. Br. IV. ३२. २८.

नभस|nabhasa
--a son of ऊर्ज; from him were born two pieces which were combined by old age (जरा) and hence जरासन्ध. वा. ९९. २२५-26.

नभस्य|nabhasya
 (I)--the month sacred to विवस्वान्. भा. XII. ११. ३८; Br. II. १३. 9; वा. ३०. 8, ५०, २०१; ५२. ११.

नभस्य|nabhasya
 (II)--one of the four sons of स्वारोचिष Manu. M. 9. 7.

नभस्य|nabhasya
 (III)--a son of Auttama Manu. M. 9. १२.

नभस्य|nabhasya
 (IV)--(name of a month and tithi) (Trayo- दशि)--a युगादि for श्राद्ध. Trayambaka to be worshipped in कृष्णाष्तमि व्रत; {{F}}2:  Ib. ५६. 4.{{/F}} austerity to be observed in सौभा- gyasayana व्रत in this month. {{F}}3:  Ib. ६०. ३४.{{/F}} ^1 M. १७. 4. [page२-204+ ३६]

नभस्यश्री|nabhasyashrii
--a queen of वऋषऋतु. Br. IV. ३२. २८.

नभस्वन्|nabhasvan
--a son of Mura (s.v.), attacked कृष्ण under direction from Naraka. भा. X. ५९. १२-14.

नभस्वती|nabhasvatii
--a queen of अन्तर्धान and mother of हविर्धान. भा. IV. २४. 5.

नमस्यु|namasyu
--a son of प्रवीर and father of चारुपद. भा. IX. २०. 2.

नमुचि|namuchi
--a son of Vipracitti. Lord of the Asuras, hostile to Indra; {{F}}1:  Vi. I. २१. ११.{{/F}} a resident of the first talam or atala; {{F}}2:  वा. ५०. १५; ९८. ८१.{{/F}} a nephew of हिरण्यकशिपु; married सुप्रभा, the daughter of स्वर्भानु; {{F}}3:  भा. VI. 6. ३२; Br. III. 6. १९; M. 6. २७.{{/F}} followed वृत्र against Indra; {{F}}4:  भा. VI. १०. १९-31; Br. II. २०. १६.{{/F}} took part in the देवासुर war between Bali and Indra; fought with अपराजित; heard of Bali's and Jambha's fall and fought with Indra; resisted with success Vajra on account of the fact that he could not be killed either by a dry or wet thing; Indra who came to know of this by a voice in the air used फेन (foam) and killed him to the satisfaction of all gods; {{F}}5:  भा. VII. 2. 4; VIII. १०. २० to the end; ११. १९, २३, २९-40; M. २२. ६१.{{/F}} entertained desire for more territory; {{F}}6:  भा. XII. 3. ११.{{/F}} taken to पाताल by वामन. {{F}}7:  Br. III. ७३. ८१; M. २४९. ६७.{{/F}}

नय|naya
 (I)--is politics; according to प्रह्लाद, it must be a means to realise Hari; {{F}}1:  भा. VII. 6. २६.{{/F}} persons versed in Naya praise भेद उपाय। {{F}}2:  M. २२३. 4 and १६.{{/F}} [page२-205+ ३२]

नय|naya
 (II)--a son of Uttama Manu. Br. II. ३६. ३९.

नय|naya
 (III)--a son of Raucya Manu. Br. IV. 1. १०४.

नय|naya
 (IV)--a son of क्रिया. वा. १०. ३५.

नय|naya
 (V)--a साध्य god. वा. ६६. १६.

नय|naya
 (VI)--one of विश्वामित्र's sons. वा. ९१. ९६.

नय|naya
 (VII)--one of the २० Amita1bha गणस्. वा. १००. १७.

नर|nara
 (I) (नारायण)--an अवतार् of विष्णु, born of Dharma and मूर्ती, a daughter of दक्ष; आदिशेष form of Hari, distinguished for tapas; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 2. 4; 3. 9; II. 7. 6-7; XII. 8. ३२, ३५. Br. II. ३५-93; M. 1. 2.{{/F}} a friend and associate of नारायण said to have performed tapas at बदरी; {{F}}2:  भा. III. 4. २२; IV. 1. ५२; VII. 6. २७.{{/F}} seeing the sage's penance Indra got afraid and sent the God of Love and the Apsarasas to disturb his contemplation. Nara invited him and was hospitable by creating a number of beautiful women who served them; Nara asked them to choose one among them as an ornament of Heaven. So they took ऊर्वशि and narrated to Indra the superior powers of the sage; {{F}}3:  Ib. XI. 4. 6-१६; 7. १८.{{/F}} was seen with नारायण by मार्कण्डेय and was praised by him. {{F}}4:  Ib. XII. 8. ३२, ३५, ४०-49; 9. 1.{{/F}}

नर|nara
 (II)--a son of तामस Manu. भा. VIII. I. २७; Br. II. ३६. ४९. Vi. III. 1. १९. [page२-206+ २८]

नर|nara
 (III)--a son of सुधृति and father of Kevala (Candra वि। प्।). भा. IX. 2. २९. ३०; Br. III. 8. ३५; ६१. 9; Vi. IV. 1. ४०-1; वा. ८६. १३-14.

नर|nara
 (IV)--a son of Manyu and father of सम्कृति. भा. IX. २१. 1.

नर|nara
 (V)--a son of Gaya and father of विरात्. Br. II. १४. ६८; Vi. II. 1. ३८; वा. ३३. ५८.

नर|nara
 (VI)--one of the ten horses of the moon's chariot. Br. II. २३. ३५; M. १२६. ५२.

नर|nara
 (VII)--a साध्य; is satya in the स्वारोचिष epoch. Br. III. 3. १६-7; M. २०३. ११; २५१; २४-5; वा. ६६. १५; Br. II. ३६. ५०.

नर|nara
 (VIII)--a son of Bhuvamanyu. M. ४९. ३६; वा. ९९. १५९.

नर|nara
 (IX)--the riding vehicle of नैऋति and drawer of Kubera's chariot. M. २६१. १५ and २२.

नर|nara
 (X)--a son of तामस Manu. वा. ६२. ४३.

नर|nara
 (XI)--a देवऋषि. वा. ६१. ८३.

नरक|naraka
--a son of अनृत; another name of Raurava. Br. II. 9. ६४; वा. १०. ३९.

नरक|naraka
--a nephew of हिरण्यकशिपु and son of the Earth and Vipracitti; lived in प्राग्ज्योतिष; {{F}}1:  M. 6. २७; १६१. ७८; १६३. ८१-2; २४५. १२. Vi. I. २१. १२८; V. 1. २४; १२. २१.{{/F}} took away a [page२-207+ ४१] number of women belonging to sages and kings to his palace, robbed Mandara of its crest jewel, Aditi of her ear- rings and वरुण of his umbrella; demanded the ऐरावत from Indra; at Indra's request was cut in twain by कृष्ण in his own city प्राग्ज्योतिष; {{F}}2:  Ib. V. २९. 8-२१.{{/F}} spoils distributed among his fol- lowers while all women were appropriated to कृष्ण's harem. {{F}}3:  Ib. V. ३१. १४-15.{{/F}} Friend of वानर Dvivida who was killed by Baladeva. {{F}}4:  Ib. V. ३६. 2-२१.{{/F}}

नरक|naraka
--a दानव with मनुष्य धर्म; {{F}}1:  वा. ६८. १५.{{/F}} a Saimhi- keya; {{F}}2:  Ib. ६८. १९.{{/F}} killed by कृष्ण. {{F}}3:  Ib. ९८. १०२.{{/F}}

नरकम्|narakam
--is bhaumam (earth). M. ३९. 4, 7-8; ४१. 6.

नरकस्|narakas
--२७ hells under Yama; to them go the un- righteous according to their respective sins; after a certain period they are born as low beings according to their कर्म। {{F}}1:  Br. IV. 2. १४६-150.{{/F}} Seven under the earth below the शेषलोक-- Raurava, शीतस्तप, कालसूतु, अप्रतिष्ठ, अवीची, लोहपृष्ठ, and Avidhya. {{F}}2:  वा. १०१. १४४-92; Vi. II. 6. 1. (whole).{{/F}}

नरकान्तक|narakaantaka
--कृष्ण. Br. III. ३६. ३४.

नरकासुर|narakaasura
--(Naraka, s.v. Bhauma); Born of Hari in his Boar manifestation when he touched and raised the Earth, {{F}}1:  भा. X. ५९. ३०[1]; [६५ (v) 1].{{/F}} hence son of Earth, {{F}}2:  Ib. X. ५९. ५९. [1] and 2.{{/F}} an asura friend of Kamsa; {{F}}3:  Ib. X. 2. 2; ३६. ३६.{{/F}} a friend of the वानर Dvivida; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ६७. 2; ६९. [3] 1.{{/F}} ran away with the umbrella of वरुण, कुण्डल of Aditi and contested the position of Indra. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ५९. [1] and 2.{{/F}} Fought with सनैश्चर in the देवासुर war; {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ७३. २०; ८३. ४०; Br. III. 6. १५; ७३. १०२; IV. २९. १२५.{{/F}} find- [page२-208+ ३३] ing Mura and his sons dead, came out with elephants, which were all killed by गरुड; fought with कृष्ण till his head was cut off and the ladies of his harem married by Him (कृष्ण); {{F}}7:  भा. VIII. १०. ३३.{{/F}} lost his kingdom through pride of power. {{F}}8:  Ib. X. ५९. १४-22; ३७. १६; I. १०. २९.{{/F}}

नरदुर्ग|naradurga
--one of the 6 kinds of fortresses. M. २१७. 6.

नरदेव (राम)|naradeva (raama)
--the eighteenth, out of the अवतार्स् of विष्णु; did heroic deeds, subduing the sea and so on. भा. I. 3. २२.

नरदेव|naradeva
--a वानर chief. Br. III. 7. २४३.

नरनारायण|naranaaraayaNa
--The two sages comprising the fourth अवतार् of विष्णु and born of मूर्ती; universal joy and good omens at their birth; गन्धमादन their abode; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 2. 4, २६; 3. 9; IV. 1. ५२-57; Vi. V. २४. 5; ३७. ३४ and ३७.{{/F}} born later as कृष्ण and अर्जुण; {{F}}2:  Ib. IV. 1. ५९.{{/F}} worshipped by नाभी; {{F}}3:  Ib. V. 4. 4.{{/F}} wor- shipped in भारतवर्ष; {{F}}4:  Ib. V. १९. 9.{{/F}} praised by नारद. {{F}}5:  Ib. V. १९. १२-15.{{/F}} To their आश्रम the sages repaired for a visit; {{F}}6:  Ib. IX. 1. ३१.{{/F}} shrine of, at Badar- याश्रम. {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ५२. 4.{{/F}}

नरनारायणौ|naranaaraayaNau
--one of the births of the जयादेवस्; these are विपश्चित्, Indra, Satya and Hari. वा. ५४. ७५; ६६. १४.

नरमेधम्|naramedham
--the belly of the personified Veda. वा. १०४. ८४. [page२-209+ २९]

नरवाहन|naravaahana
--an attribute of Kubera. M. १७४. १८.

नरसिम्ह|narasimha
--The अवतार् of Hari to kill हिरण्यकशिपु by the nails neither wet nor dry; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 5. २६-27; ५७. ५७; ७३. ७४; वा. ६७. ६६; ९७. ७३; ९८. ७३; १११. ७२; Vi. I. २०. ३२.{{/F}} on ब्रह्मा granting the request of हिरण्यकशिपु, Narasimha was approached by the gods; Narasimha promised to slay him and left for the सभा of हिरण्यकशिपु; प्रह्लाद alone knew Him to be the Lord; all the Asuras attacked him from all sides; finally Narasimha killed him by tearing him with his teeth. {{F}}2:  M. ५३. ५०. chh. १६१, १६२ and १६३; २८५. 6.{{/F}}

नरा|naraa
--the daughter of सुयग्ञ (श्वफल्क, वा। प्।) and wife of भन्गकार; had two sons शत्रुघ्न and Ban- धुमान्, whom अक्रूर killed. Br. III. ७१. ८७. वा. ९६. ८६.

नराह्|naraah
--(एत्य्।) waters. वा. 7. ५६-8; १००. १८३.

नरान्तक|naraantaka
--a son of कालनेमि; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 5. ३९; वा 67. ८०.{{/F}} was killed in the लन्का war. {{F}}2:  भा. IX. १०. १८.{{/F}}

नरिष्यन्त|nariShyanta
 (I)--a son of Vaivasvata Manu and father of Citrasena and Suca; his line ends with जातूकर्ण्य. भा. VIII. १३. 2; IX. 1. १२; 2. १९, २२; Br. III. ६०. 3; M. ११. ४१; १२. २०; वा. ६४. २९; ८५. 4; Vi. III. 1. ३३; IV. 1. 7.

नरिष्यन्त|nariShyanta
 (II)--(नाभाग) a son of स्वायम्भुव Manu. Br. II. ३८. ३१. वा. ८५ 4. [page२-210+ ४३]

नरिष्यन्त|nariShyanta
 (III)--a son of Marutta and father of Dama. Br. III. 8. ३५; ६१. 7; वा. ८६. १२; Vi. IV. 1. ३४-5.

नरेन्द्र|narendra
--is Candragupta Maurya. Br. III. ७४. १४३.

नर्मदा|narmadaa
 (I)--a महानदि of the भारतवर्ष; a R. from the ऋक्ष or ऋष्यवत् hills: (Vindhyan ranges) on its northern bank was भृगुकच्छ: a sacred river that sur- vived the अन्तरक्षय, sacred to पितृस् and for श्राद्ध; in the neighbourhood of the Haihaya kingdom. {{F}}1:  भा. V. १९. १८; VIII. १८. २१; Br. II. १२. १४; १६. २९; III. १०. ९७; M. 2. १३-15; २२. २५; ११४. २३; वा. ४५. ९९; ७७. ३२; ९४. २८; १०८. ८२; V. II. 3. ११.{{/F}} The scene of battle between वृत्र and Indra; here Rukmi challenged कृष्ण when the latter was crossing the stream with रुक्मिणी; its current was stopped by कार्त- वीर्य. {{F}}2:  भा. VI. १०. १६; X. ५४. २३[1]; Br. III. १३. 8, ३२; २६. १० and ३८; ३८. 3 and 7; ४१. १५; ४५. 2; ६९. २८; M. ४३. ३१; ४४. ३१; ४४. ३१; १६३. ६३; Vi. IV. ११. १९.{{/F}} The महात्म्य of; just like मार्कण्डेय this river does not get lost in the time of the deluge; in Kalinga, near the अमरकण्टक hill; has a number of तीर्थस् like जलेश्वर, रुद्रकोटि, अम्रकण्टक, Kapila and विशल्य Karan2i. The devotee bathing in any तीर्थ on the नर्मदा gets the benefit of performing an अश्वमेध sacrifice. {{F}}3:  M. ch. १८६.{{/F}} The Lord enshrined here is महेश्वर who devised plans to vanquish बाणासुर of Tripura with the help of नारद. The Lord was much concerned about virtuous ladies in Tripura and नारद undertook to delude them by proclaiming ordinances to ladies to give gifts to poor and deserving Brahmanas. {{F}}4:  Ib. ch. १८७.{{/F}} शिव got ready for war here and attacked Tripura with incendiary materials. Out of the three cities comprising Tripura, (s.v.) two fell down reduced to ashes. The first city became converted into the श्रि S4aila hill, and the second अमरकण्टक hill, both adorned by the Siddhas, Gandharvas and so on. The Lord enshrined at the latter is ज्वालेश्वर. The third city was left unconsumed. {{F}}5:  Ib. ch. १८८.{{/F}} [page२-211+ ३८] It is said that at the confluence of the नर्मदा with कावेरी, Kubera practised tapas in honour of शिव and be- came the Lord of the यक्षस्. A bath here is equal to that at the confluence of the गन्गा and the यमुना. {{F}}6:  Ib. ch. १८९.{{/F}} To the north of the नर्मदा are a number of तीर्थम्स् like मन्त्रेश्वर, गर्जना, अम्रातक, करन्या, कुण्डेश्- vara and others. A bath in each of them rids one of all sins. Then follows other तीर्थस्, all equally sacred, includ- ing रावणेश्वर, the shrines of Kubera, अहल्यातीर्थ, and the shrine of जनार्दन. Here Agni, धर्मराज and वायु practised asceticism and attained emancipation. A visit to शुक्लतीर्थम् sacred to राजऋषि Ca1n2akya washes off all the sins of a life time. Any gift given here bears rich fruits. {{F}}7:  Ib. chh. १९०-192.{{/F}} Among the other sacred places can be mentioned the भृगुतीर्थम्, Kankhala, where गरुड once was in austereties, कन्यातीर्थ, पितामहतीर्थ, and स्वर्गद्वार- तीर्थम्; He who reads or listens to the glory of the नमदा has his wishes fulfilled whatever be his caste. {{F}}8:  Ib. chh. १९३-194.{{/F}} On its banks Purukutsa heard the विष्णु पुराण from the sages. {{F}}9:  Vi. I. 2. 9; IV. 3. 7-१६.{{/F}} Penance here by Asuras, who became converted into Arhats. {{F}}१०:  Ib. III. १८. 1 and १३.{{/F}} मरुभूमीविषय on the N. ruled by शूद्रस् and other castes. {{F}}११:  Ib. IV. २४. ६८.{{/F}}

नर्मदा|narmadaa
 (II)--the मानसकन्या of शुकाला Pitr2s; given in marriage to Purukutsa by her brother Uraga; and mother of Trasadasyu; she took him to रसातल where he killed some bad Gandharvas to the satisfaction of the नागस्: {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 7. 2-3; Br. III. १०. ९७; वा. ७३. ४८; ८८. ७४.{{/F}} Heard the विष्णु पुराण from him and narrated it to धृतराष्ट्र the नाग and आपूरण. {{F}}2:  Vi. VI. 8. ४५.{{/F}} [page२-212+ २७]

नर्मदा|narmadaa
