th; instructed him in मन्त्रोपनिषद् to realise the presence of सन्कर्षण; showed the king and his relations the जीव of the dead child but pointing how the आत्मन् alone is eternal; the text of the विद्या imparted to Citraketu; went back to Angiras in Brahmaloka; could not find fault with Hara for violating Brahmaloka धर्म; told शुक the story of Citraketu; could not comprehend the Great Being; {{F}}4:  भा. VI. १४. 9-६१; chh. १५, १६ and १७.{{/F}} could not comprehend Hari's माया; {{F}}5:  Ib. IX. 4. ५७.{{/F}} cursed नलकूबेर and मणिग्रीव, sons of Kubera, for their intoxicated pride; his view on the merits of poverty as contrasted with wealth; went to Nara-नारायण's abode after cursing Kubera's sons; {{F}}6:  Ib. X. 9. २३; १०. 8-१८, २३.{{/F}} welcomed ब्रह्मा while with Priyavrata and his father Manu; {{F}}7:  Ib. V. 1. 6-9, ३८.{{/F}} called on प्राचीनबर्हिस् and imparted अध्यात्मतत्व by narrat- ing the story of पुरञ्जन and explaining by it the relation of जीव to परमात्म; then he went back to Siddha- loka; met प्राचेतसस् performing austerities on the western sea and advised the quick path to reach Hari; departed to Brahmaloka; sang the praise of Ananta in Brhmasabha; {{F}}8:  Ib. IV. chh. २५-31; V. २५. 9.{{/F}} advised हरिश्चन्द्र to pray to वरुण for a child; {{F}}9:  Ib. IX. 7. 8.{{/F}} spoke to ऊर्वशी of पुरूरवस् as a handsome person; {{F}}१०:  Ib. IX. १४. १६.{{/F}} [page२-227+ ४९] informed हिरण्याक्ष of विष्णु's residence in रसातल; spoke of Kardama's greatness and personality to देवहूती who from that time fixed her mind on him; came with and went with ब्रह्मा to see Kapila born of Kardama; {{F}}११:  Ib. III. १८. 1; २२. १०-12; २४. २०.{{/F}} told शिव about Sati's self-immolation in दक्ष's यज्ञ; {{F}}१२:  Ib. IV. 5. 1.{{/F}} met Dhruva coming out of his father's city and advised him as to the way of worshipping विष्णु by initiating him into the secret मन्त्र; met उत्तानपाद and encouraged the distressed king that the boy would soon return and add glory to his line; praised Dhruva; {{F}}१३:  Ib. IV. 8. २५-69; १२. ४०-30.{{/F}} learnt from Hari the true knowledge which he imparted to प्रह्लाद; saw Indra taking हिरण्यकशिपु's queen and asked him to set her at liberty which he did; then he placed her under safe custody as she was pregnant until her hus- band's return; taught to प्रह्लाद a मन्त्र sacred to Hari. {{F}}१४:  Ib. IV. १९. 6.{{/F}} Spoke of Jamba's death to Namuci and others. Deputed by ब्रह्मा, नारद went to Gods requesting them to no more fight the asuras; {{F}}१५:  Ib. VII. 6. २७-28; 7. 7-१६.{{/F}} informed Kamsa of the divinity of Vasudeva, वृष्णिस्, Nandas, and went with Gods to encourage देवकी; {{F}}१६:  Ib. VIII. ११. १९-43.{{/F}} induced Yavana to lay siege to मथुरा; {{F}}१७:  Ib. X. 1. ६१[1]; 2. २५; Vi. V. 1. ६७.{{/F}} narrated the story of Pradyumna to his parents; inform- ed मायावती that the child discovered in the fish was Pra- dyumna, काम reborn, and hence her husband; revealed Pradyumna's identity to the doubters of द्वारका; {{F}}१८:  भा. X. [५०. ४४]; ५१. 5.{{/F}} sang the praise of कृष्ण when he lifted the Govar- dhana; informed Kamsa that राम and कृष्ण were the sons of Vasudeva who had kept them in secret and prevented Kamsa from starting out to kill Vasudeva; told Kamsa his story of his birth; visited कृष्ण and spoke to him in secret what he was destined to do beginning with the day after when he would kill Kamsa and others and left for his place; {{F}}१९:  Ib. X. ५५. 6-३६; Vi. V. २७. 9-१३, २५.{{/F}} informed कृष्ण of imprisonment of Aniruddha by बाण and शाम्ब by the Kurus; visited द्वारका desirous of seeing कृष्ण in the house of each of his numerous wives at the same time and saw that ब्रह्मण्यदेव who was [page२-228+ ४९] engaged in different things at the different houses, was wel- comed separately in every house; left the place pleased; called on कृष्ण to inform him of युधिष्ठिर's desire to perform राजसूय; the purpose of his visit was accom- plished; {{F}}२०:  भा. X. २७. २४; ३६. १६-19 [२७]; ३७. 9-२४; ३९. 9.{{/F}} narrated in the राजसूय sacrifice of युधिष्ठिर, how Caidya the hater of Hari entered into Him, the Supreme Being, as well as the previous history of दमघोष and Dantavaktra. {{F}}२१:  Ib. X. ६३. 2; ६८. १३; ६९ (whole); ७०. ३२-44; ७१. ११, १८; Vi. V. ३३. १०; ३७. 6.{{/F}} Came to see भीष्म on his death-bed; {{F}}२२:  भा. VII. 1. १२-43.{{/F}} addressed by युधिष्ठिर, नारद said that everything was the work of time and the will of God; informed युधिष्- ठिर that धृतराष्ट्र was in the हिमालयस् engaged in the penance and would die within five days; and went back to heaven; {{F}}२३:  Ib. I. 9. 6.{{/F}} came to see परीक्षित् practising प्रायोपवेश; {{F}}२४:  Ib. I. १३. ३७-59.{{/F}} welcomed by कृष्ण, युधिष्ठिर and others, नारद, drew the attention of कृष्ण to the necessity of vanquishing शाल्व who was out to cut the root of the यादवस्; knew of कृष्ण's glory and greatness and told लक्ष्मणा of it; praised Vasudeva for his question on Karma; left for Sya- मन्तपञ्चक; {{F}}२५:  Ib. I. १९. १०.{{/F}} went with कृष्ण to मिथिला, heard स्रुतिगीता from नारायण at नारायणाश्रम; visited श्वेतद्वीप during Brahmasatra; called upon व्यास and communicated to him what he heard from नारायण; advised by वृत्र to worship शिव as the most easily pleased among the Gods; {{F}}२६:  Ib. X. ७६. 2 [2-१०]; 3-7 [1-4]; ८३. १७; ८४. 3, ३०-33, ५७.{{/F}} left with other sages for पिण्डारक; visited द्वारका and met Vasudeva; questioned by him on भागवत धर्म, he related the conversation that took place between Nimi, the Videha King, and the nine sages, the sons of ऋषभ; {{F}}२७:  Ib. X. ८६. १८; ८७. 4-5, १०, ४७-8; ८८. १४-16.{{/F}} views of, on thirty characteristics of धर्म, on the वर्णस् and women; on a ब्रह्मचारि, वानप्रस्थ, a Yati, and a गृहस्थ; {{F}}२८:  Ib. XI. 1. १२; chh. 2-5 (whole).{{/F}} enquired of ब्रह्मा the knowledge lead- ing to the realisation of आत्मन्; a महाभागवत who attained Hari through devotion. {{F}}२९:  Ib. VII. chh. ११-14 (whole).{{/F}} Sang a गाथ in honour of कार्तवीर्य Arjuna: compiled the नारदीय धर्म; told the रामायण to वाल्मीकि; {{F}}३०:  Ib. II. 4. २५; 5. 1-8; VII. 1. ३०; XI. २७. 2.{{/F}} [page२-229+ २४] learnt the details of the vow नक्षत्रपुरुष from महा- deva and of माहेश्वरव्रतम् from नन्दिकेश; on the lat- ter's advice took a bath at प्रयागा. {{F}}३१:  M. ४३. २३; ४७. ३०; ५३. २३ and ७२.{{/F}} Informed Maya at Tripuram of the preparations of gods to attack his city; visited इलावृतम् sacred to Bali; arranged, at the request of Indra, the marriage of उमा with शिव; {{F}}३२:  Ib. ५४. 2-4; ९५. 4; १०२. १९; ११२. २१.{{/F}} His sister was अरुन्दती, wife of वसिष्ठ; informed सावित्री's father of the short lease of life of the bridegroom chosen; {{F}}३३:  Ib. १३४. 3-२३; १३५. 1; १५४. १११-207; १८७. १४-52; १९२. ११; २०१. ३०{{/F}} cursed दक्ष's sons. {{F}}३४:  Ib. २०८. १२-13.{{/F}}

