 (I)--a son of उत्तरा and Abhimanyu; birth of; जातकर्म by युधिष्ठिर by gifts of cows, gold and lands; named विष्णुरत as was born of विष्णु's grace; blessed by Brahmanas to be like इक्ष्वाकु, राम, शिबि, Arjuna, and so on; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 4. 9-१०; 7. १२; १२. 7-३०; Br. III. ६८. २१; वा. ९९. २४९.{{/F}} a great conqueror; {{F}}2:  M. ५०. ५७.{{/F}} with his capital at हस्तिनापुर was a सार्वभौम, a सम्राट्, and the foremost of the भागवतस्; {{F}}3:  भा. I. chh. १६ and १७ (whole).{{/F}} ruled the earth guided by Brahmanas; married इरावती, daughter of Uttara and had four sons Janamejaya and others; performed three अश्वमेधस् with कृप as preceptor; conquered भद्राश्व, केतुमाला, and other coun- [page२-298+ ४०] tries and took tributes from them; heard stories of कृष्ण's heroic deeds in those places; overheard conversation between Dharma moving on one leg and the weeping Goddess of Earth on the advent of Kali and at the departure of कृष्ण to Heaven; reached सरस्वती where it flows towards the east; saw a वृषल in royal robes beating a white bull totter- ing on one foot and a cow bereft of calf shedding tears; promised security of life to them; appreciation by Dharma and परीक्षित्'s answer; Kali in वृषल's garb fell at his feet and was asked to leave ब्रह्मावर्त. But on request the King permitted him to live in five unrighteous regions; dice, wine, women, slaughter-house, and gold; {{F}}4:  Ib. ch. १८ whole.{{/F}} once when he went ahunting he felt thirsty and hungry and entered the hermitage of a sage in meditation; As he was not welcomed he threw a dead serpent on his neck and returned home; the sage's boy got offended and cursed that the King be dead by the bite of तक्षक in a week; the sage who came to know of it regretted his son's conduct as it was a great punishment for a small offence; {{F}}5:  Ib. ch. १९. 1-१६, ३२. ३८; II. 8. 1-२६; VIII. 1. ३३.{{/F}} the King regretted his deed, knew that the Brahmana's curse would come true and was in a state of प्रायोपवेश, when he was visited by sages and kings to whom he bowed; thither came शुक whom the king enquired as to the beneficial course to seek मोक्ष; requested शुक to narrate the stories of कृष्ण; {{F}}6:  Ib. XII. 6. 1-7.{{/F}} heard the whole of भागवत पुराण from शुक and thanked him for enlightening him on निर्वाण; {{F}}7:  Ib. II. 4. 2; XII. 6. 9-१५; १२. 5-6.{{/F}} knew of his coming death at the hands of तक्षक and prepared calmly to cast off his body into गन्गा to attain Hari's feet; sat in contemplation in a detatched spirit; bitten by तक्षक, his body was reduc- ed to ashes by the poison; universal surprise and benediction at the occurrence; {{F}}8:  Br. III. ७४. २२७, २३०; M. २७३. ३६; Vi. IV. १९. ७८; २०-1.{{/F}} from P. to Nanda's accession was a period of १५०० years (१०५० years वि। प्।: १०१५ Wilson). Father of Janamejaya and three other sons. {{F}}9:  वा. ९९, २२९, ४२३; Vi. IV, १९. ७८; २०. I.{{/F}} [page२-299+ २९]

