पुलक|pulaka
--killed the king बृहद्रथ and installed his son, बालक on the throne. M. २७१. ३०; २७२. 1.

पुलस्त्य|pulastya
--a mind-born son of ब्रह्मा born of his ears in वारुणी यज्न; married Kardama's daughter Havir- भू; father of Agastya (ध्राग्नि in another birth) and विश्रवस्; {{F}}1:  भा. III. १२. २२ and २४; २४. २२; IV. 1. ३६; Br. II. ३२. ९६; III. 1. २१ and ४५; M. 3. 6; वा. २५. ८२; ६१. ८२; ६५. ४२; ९४. ३६; १०१. ३५, ४९.{{/F}} a महऋषि; sage presiding over the month of Madhu; {{F}}2:  भा. XII. ११. ३३; M. १४५. ९०; वा. ५२. 2; Vi. II. १०. 3.{{/F}} आश्रम of; near Pulaha's; {{F}}3:  भा. V. 8. ३०.{{/F}} requested पराशर to impart भागवत to Maitreya; {{F}}4:  Ib. III. 8. 9.{{/F}} not seen the Supreme Being; {{F}}5:  Ib. IV. २९. ४३.{{/F}} came to स्यमन्तपञ्चक to see कृष्ण; {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ८४. 4.{{/F}} a देवऋषि of दारुवन; {{F}}7:  Br. II. ३५. ९२; २७. १०४; III. 1. २१, ४५.{{/F}} married the twelve daughters of Krodha, whose sons were उरगस् and नगस्; {{F}}8:  Ib. III. 7. १७१; 8. ७०; II. ३५. ९२.{{/F}} father of Kubera and रावण and appealed to कार्तवीर्य Arjuna to release रावण; {{F}}9:  Ib. III. ६९. ३६; M. ४३. ३८.{{/F}} his sons are the groups of यक्षस्, राक्षसस्, etc., who worship the बर्हिषद् manes; {{F}}१०:  Ib. १५. 1-4.{{/F}} praised शिव, out to des- troy Tripuram; {{F}}११:  Ib. १०२. १९; १२६. 3; १३३. ६७.{{/F}} from the केश of fire to which ब्रह्मा's शुक्रम् was offered; {{F}}१२:  Ib. १७१. २७; १९५. १०.{{/F}} gave वामन white cloths. {{F}}१३:  Ib. २४५. ८७.{{/F}} [page२-359+ ४७]

पुलस्त्य|pulastya
 (II)--created from उदान; {{F}}1:  Br. I. 1. ११७; 5. ७०; वा. I. १३८; 3. 3.{{/F}} a son of ब्रह्मा and the elder brother of Pulaha; {{F}}2:  Ib. २५. ८२; ३६. ४८; Vi. I. 1. २२-3.{{/F}} of the स्वायम्भुव epoch; {{F}}3:  वा. 9. १०२; २८. २२.{{/F}} married प्रीती, daughter of दक्ष; {{F}}4:  Br. II. 9. १८, २४, ५५.{{/F}} father of three sons, of whom दत्तालि was one; {{F}}5:  Ib. II. ११. २६; १३. ५३; वा. ३१. १६.{{/F}} married to भूति; {{F}}6:  Vi. I. 7. 5 and 7.{{/F}} by his gift पराशर remembered the विष्णु पुराण। {{F}}7:  Ib. VI. 8. ५०.{{/F}}

पुलह|pulaha
 (I)--one of the ten mind-born sons of ब्रह्मा, born of his navel; married Kardama's daughter, गती and had three sons; born from the केश of fire to which ब्रह्मा's शुक्रम् was offered; presiding over the month of माधव; {{F}}1:  भा. III. १२. २२, २४; २४. २३; IV. 1. ३८; XII. ११. ३४; M. 3. 7; १७१. २७; १९५. १०; २०२. 7 and 9.{{/F}} a महऋषि; his hermitage, sacred to Hari; visited by बलराम; Bharata spent his last days in it; {{F}}2:  भा. VII. १४. ३०; X. ७९. १०; V. 7. 8; 8. ३०; M. १४५. ९०; वा. ५२. 2; Vi. II. १०. 5.{{/F}} had not realised the Supreme Being; {{F}}3:  भा. IV. २९. ४३.{{/F}} his descendants became आज्यप manes; {{F}}4:  M. १५. २१.{{/F}} praised शिव out to destroy Tripura; {{F}}5:  Ib. १०२. १९; १२६. 3; १३३. ६७.{{/F}} gave अक्षसूत्र to वामन; {{F}}6:  Ib. २४५. ८७.{{/F}} younger brother of Pulastya, mar- ried सम्भूति; {{F}}7:  Vi. I. 1. २३; 7. 5 and 7.{{/F}} King ऋषभ spent his last days in his hermitage. {{F}}8:  Ib. II. 1. २९.{{/F}}

पुलह|pulaha
 (II)--created from व्यान of ब्रह्मा; out of the वारुणि यज्ञ with hairs hanging from his body; {{F}}1:  Br. I. 5. ७०; II. 9. १८ and २४; वा. 3. 3; 9. १०२; ६१. ८२ and ८४.{{/F}} son of ब्रह्मा; {{F}}2:  Br. II. 9. ५५; १३. ५३; वा. २५. ८२.{{/F}} प्रजापति of the स्वायम्भुव period; {{F}}3:  Ib. २८. २५; १०१. ३५ and ४९.{{/F}} son-in-law of दक्ष; {{F}}4:  Ib. ३०. ४८.{{/F}} wife क्षमा; {{F}}5:  Ib. ३१. १६.{{/F}} father of four sons and a daughter, पीवरी. {{F}}6:  Br. II. ११. ३०.{{/F}} [page२-360+ ३१]

