पौष्यञ्जि|pauShyanji
 (II)--(पौष्पिन्जि-वि। प्।) a disciple of Sukarma among the disciples of the North given by Indra; taught the five hundred Samhitas; लन्गाक्षि and Mangali were some of his disciples; {{F}}1:  भा. XII. 6. ७७ and ७९; वा. ६१. ३३.{{/F}} a स्रुतऋषि and the chief among the सामगस्; {{F}}2:  Br. II. ३३. 7; III. ६३. २०७.{{/F}} his disciples; {{F}}3:  वा. ६१. ३६; Vi. IV. 6. 4.{{/F}} Udicya Samagas. [page२-400+ ३१]

प्रकटशक्तिस्|prakaTashaktis
