प्रचेतस|prachetasa
--a प्रजेश्वर. Br. III. 1. ५४.

प्रचेतसस्(अल्सो प्रचेतस्)|prachetasas(also prachetas)
--the collective name of the ten sons of प्राचीनबर्हिष and सामुद्री; commanded by their father they engaged themselves in penance in the [page२-403+ ३६] midst of the ocean and meditated on the teachings of शिव given to them; leaving their home they proceeded to the west and in a park near a great lake heard the divine music; when listening to it, there appeared शिव who on request initiated them in the meditation on विष्णु (रुद्रगीता); when शिव left they meditated under the waters for १००० years. विष्णु appeared before them and promised them a son by asking them to marry the daughter of कण्डु and प्रम्लोचा; pleased with seeing the God they praised Him; after his disappearance they came out of the waters and seeing the earth filled with wild growth they began to burn the trees by breathing spiritual fire and wind from their mouth. ब्रह्मा (Soma) interceded then and prevented them from further destroying the trees by offering वार्क्षि (मारिषा) the daughter of the trees in marriage to them; they married her and she gave birth to दक्ष on the eve of the चाक्षुष epoch. {{F}}1:  भा. IV. २४ (whole); २५. 1-2; ३० (whole) VI. 4. 4-१७; Br. II. १३. ४०; ३७. २७; M. 4. ४७-9; वा. ६३. २७-9.{{/F}} After a long period of enjoyment of life they placed their wife under their son दक्ष and went away to the western sea where Jajali attained siddhi; seeing them steadfast in devotion नारद came there, and was welcom- ed by them; requested by them to be instructed to get rid of सम्सार, नारद advised them to worship and contemplate on विष्णु directly, and than departed; they did so and attain- ed the world of विष्णु; {{F}}2:  भा. IV. ३१. 1-२५.{{/F}} sacrifice of, when नारद sang praises of Dhruva; {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. १२. ४०; १३. 2.{{/F}} worshipped for treasure. {{F}}4:  Ib. II. 3. 7.{{/F}}

