--a wife of विश्वकर्मन्. वा. ८४. १९.

प्रह्लाद|prahlaada
 (I)--(also प्रह्राद): son of हिरण्यकशिपु and कयाधु, a दानवी; {{F}}1:  भा. VI. १८. १२, १३. VII. 1. ४१; Br. III. 5. ३३; 8. 6; M. 6. 9; वा. ६७. ७०; Vi. I. १५. १४२.{{/F}} a devotee and attendant of Hari; of Narasimha and कृष्ण in हरिवर्ष, {{F}}2:  भा. I. 3. ११; १२. २५; IV. २१. २९; V. १८. 7; VI. १८. १०, १६; VII. 1. ४१-43; X. ३९. ५४; ६३. ४७-9; Vi. I. १५. १४३-52.{{/F}} Lord of the Daityas and दानवस्; {{F}}2: a) M. 8. 5; वा. ७०. 6.{{/F}} most righteous of हिरण्यकशिपु's sons, a महा- भागवत and a महात्म, {{F}}3:  भा. VII. 4. ३०-43.{{/F}} दत्तात्रेय was a tutor: सण्ड and Marka, sons of शुक्र, were his tutors to teach him kingly policy and Trivarga; {{F}}4:  Ib. VII. 5. 1-3.{{/F}} served as calf for the Asuras to milk liquor from the earth; {{F}}5:  Ib. IV. १८. १६.{{/F}} one of the twelve, who knew the धर्म ordained by Hari; {{F}}6:  Ib. VI. 3. २०.{{/F}} at the repeated tests of his father he spoke of the nine ways of devotion to Hari; was ordered to be killed, by being trodden by elephants, or to be done to death by poison, fire or water; all these were of no avail; he was then bound by noose; प्रह्लाद once lectured to his playmates and classmates on the importance of devo- [page२-435+ ३६] tion to Hari even from childhood as it is rare to be born a man, and even as a man one half of the life is wasted in sleep and one quarter in old age; once one got into the groove of सम्सार it was not possible to get out of it; so he asked them to aim at knowledge following the pure भाग- वत धर्म; asked by the Daitya boys how and when he got that knowledge, he narrated how when his father went out to Mandara for penance, his mother was taken captive by Indra who set her at liberty on the advice of नारद, who kept her in custody until his father's return. As she was pregnant she prayed to the sage for the welfare of the child in the womb; thus he earned the grace of नारद. He there- fore looked upon आत्मन् as the only thing eternal and all other things unreal; to attain Hari there were several ways, such as listening to his stories, or singing his praise; सम्सार and other objects of desire were to be discarded and any- body of any caste or creed could attain salvation by worship- ping Hari; when this was reported to his father by the tutor, प्रह्लाद was sent for and threatened with death if he persisted in his devotion to Hari. प्रह्लाद was defiant in the सभा of हिरण्यकशिपु; found in Narasimha the Lord वासुदेव and spoke to those in the सभा, but in vain; tak- ing up his sword हिरण्यकशिपु asked him to show Hari at the post near by which he knocked with his fist; out came Narasimha and destroyed हिरण्यकशिपु in the midst of portents; universal rejoicing and praise of Hari; the Gods found Narasimha still raging in anger and requested प्रह्लाद to praise Him; his praise; pleased, the Lord prompt- ed him to ask for boons; प्रह्लाद said that desires were the seeds of सम्सार and therefore he did not want them; he only wanted to be ever devoted to him; Narasimha asked him to be king and at the same time be devoted to him; and when the time came for him he could cast off his body and get himself merged into Hari; then प्रह्लाद requested for the pardon and purification of his father which were grant- ed; after the funeral ceremonies of his father, प्रह्लाद [page२-436+ ५५] became king; then he worshipped ब्रह्मा, शिव and other Gods who all blessed him; obliged to विष्णु; {{F}}7:  Ib. VII. 5. 5-५०; chh. 6 to 9 (whole) १० 1-२४, ३२-4; IV. २१. २९ and ४७; M. १६१. ७९; १६२. 2.{{/F}} father of आयुष्मान्, शिबि, बाष्कल and Virocana; {{F}}8:  भा. VI. १८. १५, १६; M. 6. 9.{{/F}} Indra afraid of; {{F}}9:  भा. IX. १७. १४.{{/F}} a boon to प्रह्लाद not to kill any of his race; {{F}}१०:  Ib. X. ६३. ४७.{{/F}} praise of by Bali who belonged to his family; arrived when Bali bound by ropes was addressing Hari; and was bowed to by him; addressed Hari; कृष्ण who had promised प्रह्लाद not to slay princes of his line allowed बाण to escape; blessings to Bali; {{F}}११:  Ib. VIII. २२. 8, १२-14, १६-17, X. ६३, ४७-9; VIII. १५. 6-7.{{/F}} his request to Hari before leaving for Sutala; left Sutala or the great cave; attained final release by सत्सन्ग। {{F}}१२:  Ib. VIII. २३. 6-8, ११-12; Br. II. २०. २५.{{/F}} परीक्षित् compared to for his pure devotion; {{F}}१३:  भा. I. १२. २५; Br. III. ३४. ३९.{{/F}} प्रह्लाद compared to the moon shining in the sky. {{F}}१४:  भा. VIII. १९. 4.{{/F}} One of the three Indras of the दानवस् and Asuras; {{F}}१५:  Br. III. ६७. ८८; ७२. ७९; ७३. ४१-2; M. 8. 5; ४७. ७७.{{/F}} fought for ३०० years with Indra, but was finally defeated by Raji son of आयु; defeated by Indra in the churning of the ocean for nector (an अवतार् of विष्णु); {{F}}१६:  Ib. २४. ३८-42; ४७. ४८.{{/F}} duration of rule, as long as that of Bali; {{F}}१७:  Ib. ४७. ५८.{{/F}} deceived by बृहस्पति begged excuse of शुक्र; {{F}}१८:  Ib. ४७. २०७, २१०.{{/F}} ब्रह्मा was purohita to God incarnate, {{F}}१९:  Ib. ४७. २३६.{{/F}} made the १६ gifts, {{F}}२०:  Ib. २७४. १२.{{/F}} asked by Bali why the Asuras lost their effulgence Prah- लाद found out by Yoga the Lord in the womb of Aditi and predicted evil to the Asuras; Bali poohpoohed and spoke of his prowess. प्रह्लाद predicetd that he would be ruined with his kingdom for having insulted the Lord. {{F}}२१:  Ib. २४५. 1-५०.{{/F}} Indra of the Asuras {{F}}२२:  Va. ९२. ८३;{{/F}} of the Vitalam; {{F}}२३:  Ib. ५०. २५.{{/F}} Maitreya's question on the career of; {{F}}२४:  Vi. I. ch. १६;{{/F}} tormented by his father for thinking of God विष्णु in different ways; {{F}}२५:  Ib. I. ch. १७;{{/F}} was administered poison and other means to kill him; शम्बर's hand in; {{F}}२६:  Ib. I. chh. १८-19.{{/F}} his father killed by Narasimha {{F}}२७:  Ib. I. ch. २०.{{/F}} becomes the lord (Indra) of the Daityas, and दानवस्. {{F}}२८:  Ib. I. २१. १४; २२. 4; IV. 9. 8.{{/F}} [page२-437+ २१]

प्रह्ल्(र्)आद|prahl(r)aada
 (II)--a काद्रवेय Na1ga. Br. III. 7. ३६; वा. ६९. ७३.

प्रह्रादि|prahraadi
--a wife of त्वष्ट and sister of Virocana; mother of त्रिशिरस्. Br. III. ५९. १९.

प्राकाम्यम्|praakaamyam
--an Uttama siddhi; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. १९. 5; ३६. ५१: ४४. १०८.{{/F}} a योगैश्वर्य. {{F}}2:  वा. १३. 3, १४.{{/F}}

प्राकृतसर्ग|praakRtasarga
--the creation of महत्, भूत and ऐन्द्रियक; {{F}}1:  वा. 6. ६२; Vi. VI. 2. ४०.{{/F}} eight प्रकृतिस् covering this अण्ड at the time of creation. {{F}}2:  वा. 4. ९०; Vi. VI. 3. 1; 4. ११, ३०.{{/F}}

प्राकृतिक|praakRtika
--the name of Pralaya. भा. XII. 4. 5-6. वा. १०४. ११०.

प्राक्सती|praaksatii
--is भवानी. Br. III. 9. 1.

प्रागायणस्|praagaayaNas
--कश्यप gotraka1ras. M. १९९. 6.

प्राग्ज्योतिषस्|praagjyotiShas
--an eastern tribe. M. ११४. ४५. Br. II. १६. ५४. [page२-438+ ३३]

प्रागियोतिषपुर (च्)|praagiyotiShapura (ch)
--an eastern kingdom; the city of of Naraka surrounded by nooses (पशास्); entered by कृष्ण and सत्यभामा; its fortress pulled down; invited by its citizens, कृष्ण entered the city and found मणिपर्वत and the umbrella of वरुण there; then entered the palace; was left by कृष्ण. M. १६३. ८१; भा. X. ५९. 2-5; २२ [1-3], ३२; [६५(v)1]; Vi. V. २९. 8, १४, १६-7.

प्राग्देश|praagdesha
--a country noted for horses. Br. IV. १६. १८.

प्रान्ग्मुखा|praangmukhaa
--a R. sacred to the पितृस्. M. २२. ६५.

प्राचीत्वत|praachiitvata
--son of Janamejaya made the प्राची (east) direction. M. ४९. 1.

प्राचीनगर्भ|praachiinagarbha
--a son of सृष्ति (पुष्टि-वा। प्।) and छाया; wife सुवर्चा and son उदारधि (धीय-वा। प्।). Br. II. ३६. ९८-100; वा. ६२. ८३, ८५.

प्राचीनबर्हिस्|praachiinabarhis
--(बर्हिषद्); a son of हविर्धान and धिषणा; a प्रजापति and एकराट्, etc.; married सामुद्री (सवर्णा), daughter of the ocean (Samudra) of the same caste; had ten sons named प्राचेतसस्, all versed in the Dha- nurveda; performed तपस् for १०,000 years when even the wind could not blow; out of their anger came fire and burnt down trees, etc.; taking soma; द्रुमक्षय represented their case to these Pracetasas and offered their daughter मारीषा in marriage to them; their son was दक्ष; {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 4. 4; Br. II. १३. ३९, ६९; ३०. ४०; ३७. २४-41; M. 4. ४६-7; वा. ६३. २३-25; Vi. I. १४. 4-7.{{/F}} knew the power of विष्णु's योग; {{F}}2:  भा. II. 7. ४३; IV. २४. १३.{{/F}} a राजऋसि; {{F}}3:  वा. ५७. १२२.{{/F}} it was he, who made the कुश [page२-439+ २७] grass rest eastward and earned the name, प्राचीनबर्हिस्; always devoted to यज्ञ। {{F}}4:  भा. II. 7. ४३; IV. २४. १३; Vi. I. १४. 2-4.{{/F}}

प्राचीनबर्हिषस्|praachiinabarhiShas
--the ten sons of सामुद्रि, also known as Pracetasas versed in Dhanurveda. वा. ३०. ३६.

प्राचीनयोग|praachiinayoga
--a disciple of श्रिन्गिपुत्र; author of a Samhita. His son was a pupil of Kauthuma. वा. ६१. ४०; Br. II. ३५. ४५-6.

प्राचीनयोगपुत्र|praachiinayogaputra
--a Kauthuma शाखा. वा. ६१. ४२.

प्राचीन्वन्|praachiinvan
--a son of Janamejaya and father of Pra- वीर. भा. IX. २०. 2.

प्राचीसरस्वती|praachiisarasvatii
--the east सरस्वती, the place where the Gandharva, Citraratha got his redemption after his bath. भा. VI. 8. ४०.

प्राचीसरस्वती तीर्थ|praachiisarasvatii tiirtha
--in गया; bath and offer of evening prayers lead one to विष्णुलोक. वा. ११२. २३.

प्राचेतस|praachetasa
--the sage who revealed the previous birth of king पुष्पवाहन to him. M. १००. 7; वा. ६२. ७२.

प्राचेतसस्|praachetasas
--(see Pracetasas); the surname of the ten sons of प्राचीनबर्हिस् and शतद्रुती; their history; per- formed tapas as directed by Rudra for १०,000 years. Hari revealed himself before them; entrusting their house to their [page२-440+ २९] son, दक्ष and following नारद's precepts attained मोक्ष; when they rose from the sea they saw the earth covered with trees; {{F}}1:  भा. IV. २४. १३-18; २५. 2; chh. ३० and ३१; IX. २३. १५-16. Vi. I. १४. 6.{{/F}} wife मारीषा, the daughter of plants given in mar- riage by Soma, king of plants, became the mother of दक्ष. {{F}}2:  भा. VI. 4. 4-5; Vi. I. १५. 1-१०, ७१-4.{{/F}} Father ordered them to worship Govinda and increase the world's population. The prayer was granted by Govinda. Burnt down trees and uprooted them as they were hin- drances to the growth of population. {{F}}3:  Vi. I. १४. १०-48.{{/F}}

प्राचेयस्|praacheyas
--कश्यप gotraka1ras. M. १९९. 8.

प्राच्य|praachya
--a सामग. वा. ९९. १९१.

प्राच्यसामस्|praachyasaamas
--of six Samhitas, attributed to कृत. भा. IX. २१. २८-9; Br. III. ६३. २०७. M. ४९. ७६.

प्राच्यसामगस्|praachyasaamagas
--disciples of हिरण्यनाभ. Vi. III. 6. 5-२४; IV. १९. ५२.

प्राच्यस्|praachyas
--a tribe. वा. ५८. ८१.

प्राजक|praajaka
--the driver of vehicles; if he is unskilled, for injury caused by him, his master will be punished; if skilled, he himself will be punished. M. २२७. ९५-6.

प्राजापत्य|praajaapatya
 (I)--a sacrifice which युधिष्ठिर per- formed as a preparation to cast off his mortal body. भा. I. १५. ३९; III. १२. ४२; वा. ८१. 3. [page२-441+ २८]

प्राजापत्य|praajaapatya
 (II)--a मुहूर्त of the day and the night; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 3. ४०, ४२; वा. ६१. ७५; ६६. ४१.{{/F}} in the month of पुष्य, the eighth day in the dark half of the month; {{F}}2:  Ib. ६६. ४३.{{/F}} the tenth गान्धर ग्रामिक। {{F}}3:  Ib. ८६. ४३.{{/F}}

प्राजापत्य|praajaapatya
 (III)--a form of marriage; others are ब्रह्मा, Daivata, आर्ष, आसुर, गान्धर्व, राक्षस and पैशाच. Vi. III. १०. २४.

प्राजापत्यम् (व्रतम्)|praajaapatyam (vratam)
--the performance of the vow leads to the world of शङ्कर. M. १०१. ६६.

प्रागियोतिषस्|praagiyotiShas
--a Janapada of the east. वा. ४५. १२३.

प्राड्विवाक|praaDvivaaka
--a judge, to be banished for miscarriage of justice. M. २२७. १६०-1.

प्राण|praaNa
 (I)--a son of विधात्रि and नियती (आयति-ब्र्। प्।)। His wife was पुण्डरीका and द्युतिमान् was his son. भा. IV. 1. ४४-45; Br. II. ११. 6-9, ४०.

प्राण|praaNa
 (II)--a Vasu and a son of Dharma; married ऊर्जस्वती. Father of Saha and two other sons. भा. VI. 6. ११-12; Vi. I. १५. ११३.

प्राण|praaNa
 (III)--a भार्गव and a sage of the स्वारोचिष epoch. Br. II. ३६. १७; M. 9. 8. [page२-442+ ३२]

प्राण|praaNa
 (IV)--a son of Dhara; {{F}}1:  M. 5. २४.{{/F}} a साध्य. {{F}}2:  Ib. २०३. ११; Br. III. 3. १६.{{/F}}

प्राण|praaNa
 (V)--a son of Angiras; {{F}}1:  M. १९६. 2; वा. ६५. १०५.{{/F}} a साध्य; {{F}}2:  Ib. ६६. १५.{{/F}} a तुषित; {{F}}3:  Br. III. 3. १९; वा. ६६. १८.{{/F}} an Ajitadeva. {{F}}4:  Ib. ६७. ३४.{{/F}}

प्राण|praaNa
 (VI)--the अन्तरात्म; it is अन्नम् or food; अन्नम् is ब्रह्मा, etc.; from this grows creatures. (cf. उपनिषद्; also Yajur Veda); {{F}}1:  वा. १५. १४.{{/F}} one of the वायुस् which determine the कर्म of people; {{F}}2:  Ib. २१. ४७; ३१. ४१.{{/F}} is जीव। {{F}}3:  Ib. १०२. १०१.{{/F}}

प्राण|praaNa
 (VII)--a son of धातृ and father of Dyutimat. V. I. १०. 4-5.

प्राण|praaNa
 (VIII)--one of the seven seers of the स्वारोचिष epoch. Vi. III. 1. ११.

प्राणरोध|praaNarodha
 (I)--One of the २८ hells where those who indulge in the hunting and killing of animals are punished. भा. V. २६. 7 and २४.

प्राणरोध|praaNarodha
 (II)--control of the breath, one of the aids to deep meditation. वा. १०४. २४.

प्राणाचार्य|praaNaachaarya
--the purohita to be consulted by the king. M. २१५. ३५.

प्राणायाम|praaNaayaama
 (I)--a साधन for yoga. Vi. I. २२. ४५; V. १०. १५; VI. 7. ४०. [page२-443+ ३४]

प्राणायाम|praaNaayaama
 (II)--three-fold: its utility; a mode of penance. {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 8. ४४; २३. 8; Br. III. २२. ७४; M. २२७. ३७.{{/F}} one of the constituents of महेश्वर yoga; एत्य्।, the control of प्राण or wind; three ways are distinguished; मन्ध, मध्य and उत्तम; the प्रमाण of प्राणायाम is १२ मात्रस्; मन्द is of १२ मात्रस् as also उद्घाता; मध्- यम इस् twice उद्घाता or २४ मात्रस्; उत्तम is three उद्घा- तास् or ३६ मात्रस्; उत्तम produces स्वेद, कम्प and विषाद; प्राण is like the cruel wild animal which if tamed becomes soft; if approached direct by yoga, प्राण becomes disciplined in course of time; having controlled the वायु one can live as he pleases; there is no sin in his body; प्राणायाम is equal to all penances and fruits of यज्ञ; all दोषस् become burnt as it were by this practice. {{F}}2:  वा. १०. ७८-92.{{/F}} fruits of; शान्ति, प्रशान्ति, दीप्ति, and प्रसाद; {{F}}3:  Ib. ११. 4; १८. १७-19.{{/F}} practice of:--द्रw in ॐ, pray to sun and moon, and sit in स्वस्तिक or पद्म posture; half- shut eyes; look at the tip of the nose a little raising the head, neck and the body; hence तमस् and रजस् look on सत्व; attaining this yoga, प्रत्याहार to be begun, मात्र--निमि- षोन्मेष--१२ मात्रस्। {{F}}4:  Ib. ११. १२-29; २२. १९; ११०. १३.{{/F}}

प्राणिनस्|praaNinas
