बाह्लीक|baahliika
 (I)--a son of Pratipa and father of Soma- datta; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. १२ and १८; ४९. 2; वा. ९९. २३४; Vi. IV. २०. 9; V. ३५. १२, २७, ३०.{{/F}} father of seven sons, kings of बाह्लि Kingdom; {{F}}2:  M. ५०. ३९.{{/F}} the [page२-482+ ३७] foremost among the Kurus; {{F}}3:  भा. X. ५२. ११ [9].{{/F}} was stationed by जरासन्ध at the southern gate of मथुरा; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ५०. ११ [4].{{/F}} placed on the south dur- ing the siege of Gomanta; {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ५२. ११ [9].{{/F}} informed by Uddhava of राम's visit to हस्तिनापुर; {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ६८. १७.{{/F}} his sons took active part in युधिष्ठिर's राजसूय and in Duryodana's army; {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ७५. 6; [९५ (v) १६].{{/F}} could not vanquish Arjuna, supported by कृष्ण; {{F}}8:  Ib. I १५. १६.{{/F}} went with his sons to स्यमन्तपञ्चक for the solar eclipse where he met the वृष्णिस्; left स्यमन्तपञ्चक; {{F}}9:  Ib. X. ८२. २६; ८४. ६९. [1].{{/F}} sisters, रोहिणी and पौरवी, married to Vasudeva. {{F}}१०:  Br. III. ७१. १६३.{{/F}}

