ब्रह्मा|brahmaa
 (I)--पितामह, (लोकपितामह)--appeared on the lotus from the navel of Hari at the end of the Kalpa; the Lord with four faces: origin of five faces connected with his daughter and wife शतरूपा; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 3. 2; III. 8. १३-16; IX. 1. 8-१०; XI. 4. 5; XII. 5. 1; M. 1. १४; 2. ३६; 3. 1, ३७, ४०.{{/F}} Born of Hari's grace: expression of रजस्: By Yoga saw the one पुरुष lying on शेष: Praised Him, who instructed him in the art of creation: nine-fold creation from प्रकृति; created the वेदस् and human society: created also a mind-born son to शम्भु who attained Brahmalokam: a second son of his, was Bhuva, who was sent to the mother--earth: the third son भूर्भुव and his son became Gopati. From his body was created गायत्री, who became his wife: then came प्रजा- patis, oceans. etc. {{F}}2:  भा. I. १८. १४. III. 8. २२-32; 9. 1-२४, २९-44; १०. 3-6, 8, १३-26; १२. ३७-56.{{/F}} [page२-515+ ६८] Known for impartiality, परीक्षित् compared to him; {{F}}3:  M. १७१. 8-१४, १७, २१; १८३. ८४.{{/F}} obliged to विष्णु; {{F}}4:  भा. III. १२. २३.{{/F}} knew the धर्म of Hari; a परमेष्ठिन्; {{F}}5:  Ib. IV. २१. २९; २९. ४२.{{/F}} resident at गया and guards Benares; {{F}}6:  Ib. VI. 3. २०.{{/F}} his golden city being in Meru; {{F}}7:  Ib. IV. 8. २०.{{/F}} his curses and blessings moderate. {{F}}8:  M. २२. 4; १८४. २८.{{/F}} A day of, is a thousand cycles of the 4 yugas; Pralaya, the night of ब्रह्मा; period of his life is द्वीपरार्ध. All the fourteen Manus flourish during his day. {{F}}9:  भा. V. १६. २८.{{/F}} Author of the Atharva mantras; learnt the Veda from Hari and taught it to Manu; {{F}}१०:  Ib. X. ८८. १२.{{/F}} his sons were मरीचि and Atri whose son was Soma. The last was made the lord of Brahmanas, stars, etc. Influenced Soma to restore तारा to बृहस्पति. Found out that Budha was Soma's son. Punished Soma as a sinful planet for enjoying तारा. {{F}}११:  Ib. XII. 4. 2-5; Vi. I. 3. १५-24; IV. 1. 5; VI. 3. ११-12.{{/F}} Made दक्ष the overlord of the प्रजापतिस्; {{F}}१२:  भा. XI. १४. 3-4; Vi. III. 4. १२.{{/F}} called on कैलास. {{F}}१३:  भा. IX. 1. 8-१०; १४. 2-3, 8, १२ [1] and १३. XII. 8. १२; M. २३. १०, ४४-6.{{/F}} Presented पृथु with armour and prevented him from slaying Indra. {{F}}१४:  M. २०१. १७; २२५. १२; २४९. १३, ५८.{{/F}} Visited Manu and Priyavrata and addressed her on home life. {{F}}१५:  भा. IV. 3. 2.{{/F}} gifts to माय. {{F}}१६:  Ib. IV. 6. 2.{{/F}} Did not help दुर्वास pursued by the चक्र of विष्णु; {{F}}१७:  Ib. XI. १३. १६-41.{{/F}} was unable to answer the question of his son, Sanaka and others on the subtlity of yoga; remembered Hari who explain- ed it in the form of a Hamsa. {{F}}१८:  M. १७८. ५६, ६४, ७९.{{/F}} Praised विष्णु for killing काल- nemi. {{F}}१९:  भा. VIII. 5. १८-50; 6. 1-१५.{{/F}} Met Hari-Ajita to restore the fortune of Indra; cursed by दुर्वास and his prayer. {{F}}२०:  Ib. X. ८७. 9.{{/F}} Performed यज्ञ in Janaloka; {{F}}२१:  Ib. X. ८९. 3-4.{{/F}} was displeased at भृगु's behaviour; {{F}}२२:  Ib. VII. 3. १४-38; 4. 2-3; 8. ४०; १०. २६-29, ३३; M. १६१. १७.{{/F}} went with भृगु and दक्ष to हिरण्यकशिपु engaged in austerities; granted boons to him and disappeared. Was present at प्रह्लाद's coronation; {{F}}२३:  Ib. १६१. १८-23.{{/F}} when petitioned by the gods to show a way to get rid of हिरण्यकशिपु, suggested Hari for it. Took the form of a calf, {{F}}२४:  भा. VII. १०. ६२, ७०.{{/F}} when Hari in the guise of a cow went to drink the immortalising fluid in श्रीपुर; praised शिव who burnt the Tripura; {{F}}२५:  M. १३३. ५२.{{/F}} charioteer of त्रिपुरारि. {{F}}२६:  भा. VIII. २१. 1, 3 and 5; २२. २१-3; २३. २४, २६-7.{{/F}} Came to see वामन measuring the world with his two steps; washed his feet with waters; and with other Gods worshipped Him with tributes; addressed वामन-Hari; with his approval वामन was taken to Indra's capital; praised वामन's deeds and also Aditi. {{F}}२७:  Ib. X. 1. १७-35; 2. २५-42; १३. ४०-64; १४. 1-४०.{{/F}} [page२-516+ ३१] On an appeal from Mother-Earth that she had to bear a heavy burden of the Asuras, ब्रह्मा went with शिव to the shore of the milk ocean and eulogised Hari by Puru- षसूक्त; they were told of the incarnation of कृष्ण at Vasu- deva's residence; encouraged देवकी on the eve of कृष्ण's birth; came to see Hari at बृन्दावन्; was staggered at the potency of his माया and praised the Lord. {{F}}२८:  Ib. IX. 3. ३३-4; X. ५२. १५ [3-११].{{/F}} Suggested to Raivata that बलराम was a suitable husband for रेवती and asked him to give his daughter in marriage to him; {{F}}२९:  Ib. X. ७४. १३.{{/F}} attended the sacrifices of वरुण and युधिष्ठिर. {{F}}३०:  Ib. XI. 6. 1, २१-27; 7. 1-2.{{/F}} Went with all the Devas to द्वारका first to remind कृष्ण to go back to his eternal abode; addressed the Lord on the purpose and fulfilment of the अवतार्। {{F}}३१:  Ib. XII. 8. १२.{{/F}} Wondered at मार्कण्डेय's व्रत; {{F}}३२:  Ib. XII. १३. १० and १९.{{/F}} heard the भा- गवत पुराण from Hari. {{F}}३३:  Ib. II. 5. 9 to the end.{{/F}} narrated to नारद the legend of the creation of the universe; {{F}}३४:  Ib. I. 7. १८.{{/F}} allusion to his fear of Rudra; {{F}}३५:  Br. III. 7. २७०; २४. 4.{{/F}} worshipped by वालि with fire rite.

