 (I)--son of Ketuman and father of Divo- दास (प्रजेश्वर-ब्र्। प्।); himself known as दिवोदास in वा। प्।; king of वाराणसि. भा. IX. १७. 5-6; Br. III. ६७. २६; वा. ९२. २३; Vi. IV. 8. ११.

भीमरथ|bhiimaratha
 (II)--a son of विकृति, and father of Nava- ratha (Rathavara-ब्र्। प्।) भा. IX. २४. 4; Br. III. ७०. ४२; वा. ९५. ४१; Vi. IV. १२. ४१.

भीमरथ|bhiimaratha
 (III)--a वानर chief. Br. III. 7. २३८.

भीमरथ|bhiimaratha
 (IV)--a son of Vimala and father of Nava- ratha. M. ४४. ४१. [page२-564+ ४२]

भीमरथी|bhiimarathii
--a R. in the Sahya hill in दक्षिणापथ; {{F}}1:  वा. ४५. १०४; Vi. II. 3. १२.{{/F}} in भारतवर्ष; visited by बलराम from the Sahya hill; {{F}}2:  भा. V. १९. १८; X. ७९. १२; Br. II. १६. ३४.{{/F}} sacred to the पितृस्. {{F}}3:  M. २२. ४५; ११४. २९.{{/F}}

भीमरोमकस्(च्)|bhiimaromakas(ch)
--a kingdom through which the गन्गा flows. M. १२१. ४७.

भीमवेग|bhiimavega
--a Tripravara. M. १९६. ३४.

भीमव्रतम्|bhiimavratam
--the observance of the vow leads to the world of विष्णु. M. १०१. ५१.

भीमसेन|bhiimasena
 (I)--(also भीम); a पाण्डव son of कुन्ती; father of श्रुतसेन; had another son घटोत्कच by हिदिम्बा, and a third Sarvagata by काली; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. २९-31; Vi. IV. १४. ३५; २०. ४०.{{/F}} failed to hit the fish in लक्ष्मणा's स्वयम्वर; {{F}}2:  Ib. X. ७१. २७; ५८. 4; ६४. 9.{{/F}} joy at कृष्ण's visit to Indraprastha and कृष्ण's respects to him; was consoled by कृष्ण when banished to forest; {{F}}3:  भा. X. ८३. २३.{{/F}} sent to the western terri- tories with the Matsyas, Kekayas and Madrakas. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ७२. १३.{{/F}} Advised by Uddhava to go in Brahmana's disguise to जरासन्ध and vanquish him; went with कृष्ण and Arjuna to Girivraja. After killing जरासन्ध, भीमसेन returned to हस्तिना- pura. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ७१. 7; ७२. ३२-46; ७३. ३१.{{/F}} Declined to follow बलराम's advice not to fight; fought with Duryodhana at कुरुक्षेत्र and felled him with his गदा; {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ७८ [९५(v)३९]; ७९. २३ and २८; I. 7. १३.{{/F}} was in charge of cooking in the राजसूय of युधिष्ठिर; {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ७५. 4.{{/F}} fed धृतराष्ट्र; advocated killing of अश्वत्- थाम and felt sorry at कृष्ण's separation; {{F}}8:  Ib. I. १३. २२; II. 7. ३५; I. 7. ५१ and ५४; 9. १५; १०. १०.{{/F}} put an end to the राक्षसस् born of क्रोधवशा: propagator of भीमद्वा- दशीव्रत; {{F}}9:  M. 6. ४३; ६९. १२-3.{{/F}} gave पिण्ड sitting on his left leg to जनार्धन, [page२-565+ २४] and attained Brahmaloka with his brothers; {{F}}१०:  वा. ८६. ४८; १०८. ९१.{{/F}} strength of; depended on the good will of कृष्ण. {{F}}११:  Vi. V. ३८. ३३.{{/F}}

भीमसेन|bhiimasena
 (II)--a son of परीक्षित्. भा. IX. २२. ३५; Vi. IV. २०. 1; २१. 2.

भीमसेन|bhiimasena
 (III)--a Mauneya Gandharva. Br. III. 7. 1.

भीमसेन|bhiimasena
 (IV)--an author of a treatise on Music. Br. III. ६१. ४२.

भीमसेन|bhiimasena
 (V)--a son of दक्ष. M. ५०. ३८.

भीमसेन|bhiimasena
 (VI)--a son of Suratha. वा. ९९. २२९.

भीमसेन|bhiimasena
 (VII)--a son of ऋक्ष, and father of दिलीप. वा. ९९. २३३; Vi. IV. २०. 7.

भीमा|bhiimaa
 (I)--a mother-goddess; {{F}}1:  M. १७९. २२.{{/F}} enshrined in हिमाद्रि. {{F}}2:  Ib. १३. ४७.{{/F}}

भीमा|bhiimaa
 (II)--a R of the केतुमाला country. वा. ४४. १८.

भीमेश्वरम्|bhiimeshvaram
--a तीर्थ on the नर्मदा; sacred to the पिट्र्स्. M. २२. ४६, ७५; १९१. 5. [page२-566+ ३७]

भीरवस्|bhiiravas
--one of the १४ gan2as of Apsarasas, born of मृत्यु. Br. III. 7. २०.

भीरु|bhiiru
--a यक्ष, son of पुण्यजनी and मणिभद्र. Br. III. 7. १२३.

भीषण|bhiiShaNa
 (I)--a वानर born of Pulaha. Br. III. 7. १७९.

भीषण|bhiiShaNa
 (II)--a son of हृदीक. M. ४४. ८२.

भीषणिका|bhiiShaNikaa
--a Goddess following रेवती. M. १७९. ७३.

भीष्म|bhiiShma
--son of शन्तनु; Grandsire of the पाण्डवस् and गन्गा. The best of Bharatas, the foremost of the Vasus, and versed in dharma: Learned, self-controlled, and devoted to Hari. His prowess was praised even by परशु- राम. Leader of a thousand legions, called सहस्राणी; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. १९-20; I. 9. 4-6, ३०; M. १०३. 5. वा. ९९. २४०. Vi. IV. २०. ३३; V. ३५. 5 and २७.{{/F}} Informed by Uddhava of बलराम's visit to हस्तिनापुर: was invited for the राजसूय of युधिष्ठिर; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ६८. १७ and २८; ७४. १०.{{/F}} went to स्यमन्तपञ्चक for the solar eclipse and there met कृष्ण and the वृष्णिस्. Left it for his home. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ८२. २४; ८४. ५७, ६९ [1].{{/F}} Joined Duryodhana's army and was commander for ten days when he was mortally wounded; while on his death- bed he welcomed the sages and the royal guests, who visit- ed him; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ७८. [९५(v)१६], [२८]; I. 9. 8-१०; १५. १०.{{/F}} told the पाण्डवस् that they were safe under the guidance of कृष्ण; {{F}}5:  Ib. I. 9. ११-14.{{/F}} युधिष्ठिर addressed B. lying on a bed of arrows on the various aspects of dharma and especially मोक्ष धर्म। The discourse was over when it was उत्तरायन, B. cast off his mortal coil with his mind fixed on कृष्ण Va1sudeva. His praise of कृष्ण; {{F}}6:  Ib. I. 9. २५-42; XI. १९. ११-12.{{/F}} was [page२-567+ ४०] seen among others by अक्रूर, कृतवर्मन्, कृष्ण and बलराम; {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ४९. 1; ५२. [५६(v)4, and ११]; ५७. 2.{{/F}} one of the twelve, who knew the धर्म ordained by Hari; {{F}}8:  Ib. VI. 3. २०. {{/F}} gave पिण्ड in विष्णुपद; {{F}}9:  वा. १११. ६९.{{/F}} Baladeva's respect for; {{F}}१०:  Vi. V. ३५. ३६; ३८. १६, ४७, ४९ and ६४.{{/F}} narrated to Nakula what he heard from his Brahmana friend कालिन्गक, on the mystery of birth and death; {{F}}११:  Ib. III. 7. 8.{{/F}} the best of the Kurus; {{F}}१२:  Ib. III. 7. ३५.{{/F}} heard a legend from वसिष्ठ as to who was a नग्न। {{F}}१३:  Ib. III. १७. 7.{{/F}}

भीष्मक|bhiiShmaka
--the invincible king of Vidarbha, capital of कुण्डिन (Berar); {{F}}1:  भा. III. 3. 3; Vi. V. २६. 1.{{/F}} had five sons (Rukmi one of them) and a daughter, known as वैदर्भी and रुक्मिणी. Agreed to his son, Rukmi's wish to give रुक्मिणी in marriage to शिशुपाल: on the eve of the day of marriage, the city was decorated; prayers were offered to पिट्र्स् and Devas; प्रेसेङ्त्स् were given to Brahmanas to exalt मन्गलम्। दमघोष and other friends of the Cedi King were welcomed. Housed राम and कृष्ण in comfortable lodgings. But कृष्ण won her in the स्वयम्वर; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ५२. १६, २१-22; ५३. 7-३५; Vi. V. २६. 3-6.{{/F}} was stationed by जरासन्ध on the northern side during the siege of Gomanta; {{F}}3:  भा. X. ५२. ११[15].{{/F}} went to the स्यमन्तपञ्चक for the solar eclipse. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ८२. १५.{{/F}}

भीष्ंअचण्डिक|bhiiShMachaNDika
--a place near Benares. M. १८३. ६२.

भुजन्ग|bhujanga
--served as a rope for Manu to tie the divine boat to the horn of the fish; {{F}}1:  M. 2. १८; 4. 6.{{/F}} Indra took the guise of, to disturb the तपस् of वज्रान्गी; {{F}}2:  Ib. १४६. ६५.{{/F}} born to ward off poison. {{F}}3:  Ib. २१९. 6.{{/F}} [page२-568+ २८]

भुजन्गमस्|bhujangamas
--see नागस्; vanquished by रावण. Br. III. 7. २५५.

भुजातपूर|bhujaatapuura
--a Pravara ऋषि. M. १९९. १६.

भुतावाप्ति|bhutaavaapti
--of five elements: पृथ्वि, वायु, आकाश, आप, and ज्योति; each has its own function; the body is of the earth, प्राण of मारुत or wind, the आकाश of water, and तेजस् of ज्योत्स्न; by their virility, सन्ग्रामस् and visayas do their respective work. वा. ९७. ५५.

भुद्रकस्|bhudrakas
--the राक्षसस्, being the destroyers of यज्ञस् as also निकरस्। वा. ६९. १८९.

भुरण्य|bhuraNya
--a सुधामान god. Br. IV. 1. ६०.

भुर्भर|bhurbhara
--a weapon. वा. ३०. २३६.

भुव|bhuva
 (I)--also अन्तरिक्ष--the second of the seven created worlds: वायु is its presiding deity: burnt down by प्रलय fire; {{F}}1:  Br. II. १९. १५५; २१. २१; IV. 1. १५६; 2. १४-17, २७-30.{{/F}} residents: Marut, मातरिश्व, Rudras, अश्विन्स्, आदित्यस्, साध्यस्, Pitrs, Angirasa sages etc., intervening between the earth and the sun; the residents here drink सोम and ghee. {{F}}2:  वा. १०१. १९, २९, ४०, ४३.{{/F}}

भुव|bhuva
 (II)--the second kalpa. वा. २१. २९. [page२-569+ २१]

भुव|bhuva
 (III)--the eleventh kalpa. वा. २१. ३१.

भुव|bhuva
 (IV)--a son of उन्नेता. वा. ३३. ५६.

भुव|bhuva
 (V)--the seventh son of देवकी. वा. ९६. १८१.

भुवत|bhuvata
--a son of क्षेम, a बृहद्रथ: ruled in Magadha for ६४ years. वा. ९९. ३०३.

भुवन|bhuvana
 (I)--a son of भृगु and a Deva. Br. III. 1. ८९; M. १९५. १२; वा. ६५. ८७.

भुवन|bhuvana
 (II)--(भुवनेश्वर) a Rudra. Br. III. 3. ७१; वा. ६६. ७०.

भुवना|bhuvanaa
--the sister of बृहस्पति and wife of प्रभात, the 8th Vasava. Br. III. 3. २८.

भुवनाण्डगर्भ|bhuvanaaNDagarbha
--Lord of the Universe; ब्रह्मा. M. 8. १०.

भुवमन्यु|bhuvamanyu
--a son of Vitatha, and father of four powerful sons, बृहद्क्षत्र and three others. M. ४९. ३५; वा. ९९. १५८-59. [page२-570+ ३०]

भुवर्लोक|bhuvarloka
--from Bhuvana according to निरुक्तञ्ज; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३८. १६; वा. २३. ८४; ४९. १४८; ६४. १४; १००. १६०.{{/F}} that world between the earth and the sun; burnt by the flame of Rudra in the dissolution. {{F}}2:  Vi. II. 7. १७; VI. 3. २६ and ३९.{{/F}}

भुवस्थानम्|bhuvasthaanam
--the place of अच्छावक agni. वा. २९. २८.

भुवस्पति|bhuvaspati
--is वायु, lord of Bhuva. Br. IV. 2. २०; वा. १०१. २२.

भुशुण्डि|bhushuNDi
 (I)--a weapon of war used in the Kubera Jambha war; {{F}}1:  M. १५०. ७३.{{/F}} used by Kujambha; {{F}}2:  Ib. १५०. १०६.{{/F}} तारक defeated Yama with. {{F}}3:  Ib. १५२. २८; १५३. १९५; १७७. 9.{{/F}}

भुशुण्डि|bhushuNDi
 (II)--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. १६.

भू|bhuu
 (I)--Earth: (भूमि, s.v.) one of the seven worlds; released from रसातल by Hari in वराह form, this, देवी worships Hari in that form in Uttara-Kuru; {{F}}1:  भा. IV. १७. ३४; M. ६०. 2.{{/F}} when पृथु wanted to punish her for scarce supply of food, she trembled and appealed to him to make the ground level plain and milk her with a calf and a pail; was milked by the King, sages, Gods, asuras and others; hilly tracts got levelled, and cities and villages were founded. {{F}}2:  भा. IV. १७. १३-36; १८. 2-३२.{{/F}} भू is said to have given योगिच् पादुकस् to पृथु. {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. १५. १८.{{/F}} presiding deity is Agni; [page२-571+ २९] burnt by प्रलय fire; {{F}}4:  Br. II. १९. १५५; २१. २१; IV. 1. १५६; 2. 9-१९, ४१, २२३.{{/F}} the measurement of the earth (Pra- माणम्) attempted by हर्यश्वस् (s.v.). {{F}}5:  M. 5. 6.{{/F}}

भू|bhuu
 (II)--(Samiti) a कृतलोक, the first world; first was said भू and then came this world; {{F}}1:  वा. २३. १०७; २४. १८. १०१. ११, ३५-36.{{/F}} is पार्थिव loka; {{F}}2:  Ib. १०१. १८.{{/F}} these lokas are burnt by the flames of the seven suns; {{F}}3:  Ib. १०१. २०.{{/F}}  मरीचि, कश्यप, दक्ष and other प्रजापतिस् live here; {{F}}4:  Ib. १०१. ३४.{{/F}} people here live on rice and juice. {{F}}5:  Ib. १०१. ४०, ४२.{{/F}}

भूत|bhuuta
 (I)--a sage who married two daughters of दक्ष --भूता and सरूपा. Had sons; eleven Rudras, besides crores of their attendants. भा. VI. 6. 2, १७-18.

भूत|bhuuta
 (II)--a son of पौरवी and Vasudeva. भा. IX. २४. ४७.

भूत|bhuuta
 (III)--a name for प्रजापति. वा. १००. २३९.

भूत|bhuuta
 (IV)--a member of the रोहिणी family. Vi. IV. १५. २२.

भूतकेतु|bhuutaketu
--a son of दक्ष sa1varn2i. भा. VIII. १३. १८.

भूतगणस्|bhuutagaNas
--a deva गण. वा. ७२. ५०. [page२-572+ ३०]

भूतग्राम|bhuutagraama
--the group of five भूतस्; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३७. 6; III. 1. ३२; M. 1. १५; १६५. २३-24.{{/F}} beings are of four kinds; viviparous, अण्डज (egg-born), udbhijja (sprout- ing as plant) and svedaja (sweat produced); {{F}}2:  वा. २३. ८२; ३०. १०१ and २२७; ६३. 5; ६५. १२२.{{/F}} worshipped in ceremonies prior to the construction of tanks, etc. {{F}}3:  M. ५३. ३१; ५८. २६; १६६. 5-8.{{/F}} Born of the sacrifice of वरुण clothed with तमस्, रजस् and सत्व। {{F}}4:  वा. ६५. ३३.{{/F}}

भूतज्योतिस्|bhuutajyotis
--son of Sumati, and father of Vasu. भा. IX. 2. १७.

भूतडामरी|bhuutaDaamarii
--a mother-goddess. M. १७९. ३१.

भूततन्मार्ग(मात्र-वि। प्।) सर्ग|bhuutatanmaarga(maatra-vi. p.) sarga
--भूत and others. {{F}}1:  वा. 4. ४९.{{/F}} elementary creation proceeding from तामसिच् अहम्कार; see पुरुष. {{F}}2:  Vi. I. 2. ४६.{{/F}}

भूतनन्द|bhuutananda
--a prince who ruled from किलिकिला after the Maunas ceased to reign. भा. XII. 1. ३२.

भूतपति|bhuutapati
--is Agni; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. 2. १९; वा. १०१. २१.{{/F}} also शिव. {{F}}2:  Br. II. २५. ३९.{{/F}}

भूतपतिस्|bhuutapatis
--see भूतस्. भा. I. 2. २६.

भूत(बलि)|bhuuta(bali)
--see Andhaka. M. २५२. 5-१९. [page२-573+ २६]

भूतमता|bhuutamataa
--a वर्ण s4akti. Br. IV. ४४. ५८.

भूतरयस्|bhuutarayas
--a group of १३ gods of the Raivata epoch. भा. VIII. 5. 3; Br. II. ३६. ५१ and ५६; Vi. III. 1. २१.

भूतलम्|bhuutalam
--is पृथ्वी. Br. III. 2. २१.

भूतवटम्|bhuutavaTam
--the residence of different भूतस् and गणस् of Trayambaka; description of. वा. ४०. २०-6; १०१. २०८.

भूतवादी|bhuutavaadii
--as different from भूतानुवादि; is also प्रवाती. Br. III. 3. १२५-6.

भूतविनायकस्|bhuutavinaayakas
--leaders of भूतस् and attendants on Rudra. भा. VI. 6. १८.

भूतसम्ताप|bhuutasamtaapa
--an Asura who took part in the देवा- sura war between Bali and Indra. भा. VIII. १०. २०.

भूतसम्तापन|bhuutasamtaapana
--a son of हिरण्याक्ष. A follower of वृत्र in his battle with Indra. भा. VII. 2. १८; VI. १०. [२०]; Br. III. 5. ३१; M. 6. १४; वा. ६७. ६८; Vi. I. २१. 3.

भूतसम्प्लव|bhuutasamplava
--the period when the planets, seers, Manus and other gods cease their work and seek their abode in Maharloka. Br. II. २१. १५६-64; २४. ८५; २५. १०६; ३२. ६३; ३५. १६८, १९८ and २०३. [page२-574+ ३३]

भूतस्|bhuutas
 (I)--(also भूतपतिस्)--fierce, and abandoned by those who seek मोक्ष; spirits harassing children; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 2. २६; II. 6. १३; IV. 2. १५; VI. 8. २४; IX. १४. 6; X. 6. २७; ६६. ३४; XI. १०. २८.{{/F}} follow- ers of Rudra (शिव) some born of sexual union; and some mind-born; belong to the line of क्रोधवशा; vanquished by रावण; {{F}}2:  Br. II. २५. ३९; III. 7. २५६, ३५९-74; ४४०; 8. ७१; M. 8. 5.{{/F}} sons of भूति and followers of Rudra and निशा- caras; described. {{F}}3:  वा. ५४. ३७-43; ६९. २४२-56.{{/F}}

भूतस्|bhuutas
 (II)--five elements--पृथ्वी, वायु, आप, आकाश and ज्योति। Br. III. ७२. ५४; IV. 2. ११६.

भूता|bhuutaa
 (I)--a wife of भूत and a daughter of दक्ष. Her sons were the एकादश Rudras. भा. VI. 6. १७.

भूता|bhuutaa
 (II)--a daughter of क्रोधवशा (क्रोधा- वा। प्।), and a wife of Pulaha. Br. III. 7. १७२; वा. ६९. २०५.

भूतादिक सर्ग|bhuutaadika sarga
--creation; first is महत् सर्ग, second भूत सर्ग, third ऐङ्द्रियक सर्ग; this is प्राकृत सर्ग। वा. 4. ५०; 6. ५८-62.

भूतादित्(क्)अ|bhuutaadit(k)a
--(अहम्कार); of the 6th sarga; the five भूतस्: earth, waters, fire, wind and ether; each is ten times greater than the preceding one. Br. I. 5. ५३-8; II. ३२. ७६. M. १२३. ५२; वा. १०१. ११६.

भूतानि|bhuutaani
--three-fold movements; नैमित्तिक, प्राकृतिक, and आत्यन्तिक; नैमित्तिक is ब्रह्मा; in the dissolution of creatures lies the natural destruction of all beings; आत्यन्तिक is due to knowledge, not as a result of action; from these ब्रह्मा again begins the work of creation after he wakes [page२-575+ २८] up from his sleep; during his sleep there is no continuous rain; rivers are with little or no waters; the sun's seven rays scorch the earth and draw away even the little water; every- thing is burnt down; no trees or plants; the heat penetrates the पाताल and the वायु लोकस्; all the worlds are burnt down; everywhere is to be seen one flame of fire; then set in clouds in different hues and in different shapes, pour down rains and appease the fire which enters into waters, result- ing in the condition of एकार्णव out of which emerges ब्रह्मा, the first progenitor and पुरुष; the seven sages see him; then, are gradually born all the kings one by one; simi- larly sages, men, gods and other things. Br. IV. 1. १२८ to २०७.

भूति|bhuuti
 (I)--a son of युयुधान and father of Yugan- dhara. Br. III. ७१. १०१; वा. ९६. १००.

भूति|bhuuti
 (II)--the mother of Bhautya. Br. IV. 1. ५१.

भूति|bhuuti
 (III)--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ४४. ७४.

भूति|bhuuti
 (IV)--a son of Bhautya; the future Manu. M. 9. ३५; वा. १००. ५५.

भूति|bhuuti
 (V)--a साध्य; destroyer of all Asuras. M. १७१. ४४.

भूति|bhuuti
 (VI)--gave birth to भूतस्, followers of Rudra. वा. ६९. २४२.

भूति|bhuuti
 (VII)--the wife of Pulastya. Vi. I. 7. 7. [page२-576+ ३४]

भूतिनन्द|bhuutinanda
--the king after Dhanadharma. His brother was नन्दियश; the fifth ruler of विदिश. Br. III. ७४. १८२; वा. ९९. ३६८.

भूतिमित्र|bhuutimitra
--the son of नवकण्ठायन, a शुन्ग ruled in Maghada for २४ years. वा. ९९. ३४५.

भूतेश|bhuutesha
--as calf for the यक्षस् and the राक्षसस्, भूतस् and others, to milk आसव in a skull from the earth as cow. भा. IV. १८. २१.

भूमन्|bhuuman
 (I)--a son of Pratihartu and स्तुती; wife ऋषि- कुल्या, and son उद्गीथ. भा. V. १५. 5-6.

भूमन्|bhuuman
 (II)--a son of उन्नेता. Br. II. १४. ६६.

भूमि|bhuumi
