 (V)--approached by वरूत्रि's sons to ruin the offerings to Gods but interrupted by Indra. वा. ६५. ७९.

मनु|manu
 (VI)--a son of बाष्कल. वा. ६७. ७९.

मनु|manu
 (VII)--a son of शिघ्रक; established himself in कलापग्राम by yoga. वा. ८८. २१०.

मनु|manu
 (VIII)--one of the sons of Madhu. वा. ९५. ४५.

मनु|manu
 (IX) (रैवत)--the fifth Manu; son of Priya- vrata and brother of तामस; Bali and others were his sons. Vibhu was Indra; भूतरयस् were the gods of the epoch; वैकुण्ठ was the manifestation of Hari in this मन्वन्तर। {{F}}1:  भा. V. 1. २८; VIII. 5. 2-5.{{/F}} देवबाहु and others were the seven sages; served as calf to milk the earth. {{F}}2:  Br. II. ३६. 3, ५१. ६४; ३७. १७. 8.{{/F}} [page२-619+ ४३]

मनु|manu
 (X)--(चाक्षुष)--a son of विश्वकर्मन् (विश्- वेश-म्। प्।) and कृती। Father of विश्वस् and साध्यस्. भा. VI. 6. १५; M. १७१. ४८.

मनु|manu
 (XI) (सावर्णि)--the eighth Manu. A son of छाया and विवस्वान्. Father of Nirmoka and other sons. In this epoch Sutapas, Virajas अमिताभस्, Mukhyas were the gods. Bali was Indra. गालव, कृप, राम and others were the sages. Hari manifested himself as सार्वभौम। {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. ४१; VIII. १३. ११-7; २२. ३१; Vi. III. 2. 4; १३-19.{{/F}} Ini- tiated in the mystery of Lord's glories by नारद, worship- ping नरनारायण; {{F}}2:  भा. V. १९. १०.{{/F}} originally श्रुतश्रवस्; performs aus- terities on the slopes of Meru even to-day. {{F}}3:  Br. IV. 1. २८; III. ५९. ४९ and ८०.{{/F}}

मनु|manu
 (XII) (स्वायम्भुव)--the first son of ब्रह्मा and the first king (सम्राट्) also विराट्. Ruled the earth, girt by seven seas, occupying ब्रह्मावर्त with बर्हिष्मती as capital. A विप्रराजऋषि. Learnt the Veda from his father, who asked him to rule according to Dharma. Wife शत- रूपा; sons Priyavrata and उत्तानपाद besides eight more through अनन्ता and a daughter, देवहूती. Other daughters were आकूति and प्रसूति {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. 1. 1, 5 and 7, XI. १४. 4; III. २०. 1 and १०; २१. 1-3, २५-26; २२. २६-9; VI. 1. 1; 8. 6; Br. II. १३. १०५; M. 3. ४४-5; 4. ३४; १४५, ९०; वा. 3. 2, ३६; २३. ४७; ५९. ५६-7; Vi. I. 7. १४-19; III. 1. 6.{{/F}} who married दक्ष and Ruci res- pectively. Met Kardama on the सरस्वती, spoke of inter- dependence of the क्षत्रिय and the Brahmana, and offered his daughter देवहूती in marriage to that sage. {{F}}2:  भा. III. २१. ४५; २२. 3-१४.{{/F}} Another daughter धन्या became the wife of Dhruva. Seeing Dhruva fighting with the यक्षस् in utter wrath, Manu asked him to cease slaughtering the innocents and to ask pardon of Kubera, their chief. {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. ११. 6-३४; M. 4. ३८.{{/F}} Appointed Priyavrata in charge of the kingdom and retired to तपस्। Spent ७१ yugas meditating on विष्णु, and gave Him the name, Hari. Did not take objection to Hara's violation of धर्म, though he was one of the twelve who knew the धर्म ordained by Hari. {{F}}4:  भा. V. 1. २१-2; XI. 2. १५; III. २२. ३१-6; II. 7. 2; VI. १७. १२; 3. २०; IV. २१. २८.{{/F}} Served as calf for पृथु to milk the earth. {{F}}5:  Ib. IV. १८. १२; २९. ४२.{{/F}} Formed one half of the Creator [page२-620+ ३८] and the other was शतरूपा. Asked ब्रह्मा for the earth being lifted out of the waters to form an abode for him and his subjects, when a वराह issued from ब्रह्मा's nostrils to do the work. {{F}}6:  Ib. III. १२. ५३-4; १३. 3-१८.{{/F}} Renouncing the world, Manu stood on one leg medi- tating on the glory of Hari on the bank of the सुनन्दा for a hundred years; when the Asuras tried to attack and devour him, Hari in the form of यज्ञ slew them. {{F}}7:  भा. VIII. 1. 7-१०.{{/F}} The first to give out स्मार्त धर्म, वर्णाश्रम धर्म and the first to practice शिष्टाचार; requested by Brahma to protect the वेदस् and consequently the यज्ञस्। Divided the Vedas into four sections. {{F}}8:  Br. II. २९. ४६, ६१-4; ३०. ३४; ३२. ३५-8, ९६; ३४. 2-8; ३५. १७५; ३६. 3; ३७. १४; IV. 1. ३२ and १०९; M. १४२. ४२.{{/F}} An आदिपुरुष. From him were born वैराजस्. {{F}}9:  Ib. 3. ४५-6; १७१. २७; १९२. १०; २२७. ३२.{{/F}}

मनु|manu
 (XIII)--(स्वारोचिष)--the second Manu, and son of Agni. Father of Dyumat and others. In this epoch Rocana was Indra, तुषित and others were gods, ऊर्ज्जस्तम्ब and six others were the seven sages. भा. VIII. 1. १९-20; Br. II. ३६. 3, २३; ३७. १५.

मनु|manu
 (XIV)--(वैवस्वत)--the seventh Manu, also known as ‘श्राद्धदेव’. {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. १३. 1-9; Br. II. ३६. 4, ८१; III. ५९. २२ and ३८; ६३. २१५; IV. 1. 6-२८; वा. ८४. २२; Vi. IV. 1. 6-7.{{/F}} Son of सम्ज्ञा and Vivasvat (सुरेणु and विवस्वान् वा। प्।): wife श्रद्धा: father of ten sons of whom इक्ष्वाकु was the eldest; {{F}}2:  Br. II. ३८. 1.{{/F}} in this epoch Puran- dara was Indra: कश्यप, Atri and others were sages: आदित्- yas and Vasus were gods: वामन was the manifestation of Hari; {{F}}3:  भा. VIII. १३. 1-9.{{/F}} a क्षत्रिय मन्त्रवादिन्: His sacrifice was disturbed by sons of वरूत्रि who were burnt by Indra in the वेदि: [page२-621+ ४१] a प्रजापति: king and दण्डधर. {{F}}4:  Br. II. ३२. १२०; ३८. २६ and ३२; III. 1. 3 and 6; 8. २१; १०. ९८; ६०. 7; M. १४५. ११५; २४८. १५.{{/F}} Saved by the Matsya Hari during the deluge. After anointing his son on the throne, M. performed penance on the Malaya Mt. for a lac of years when ब्रह्मा blessed him as protector of the universe after the प्रलय। Once in making a water oblation to his manes, a fish fell into his hand which he put into his water vessel. Finding its rapid growth he placed it in a well, tank, Ganges and the sea respectively. From its abnormal growth he suspected it to be an asura or वासुदेव; on questioning it he found it to be the Lord and was asked to use it (the fish) as the life boat when the whole world went down in the deluge, saving at the same time some lives; {{F}}5:  Ib. 1. ११ to the end; 2. १६; 9. 1; १६. 1; ५२. 3.{{/F}} performed तपस् on the यमुना for one hundred years with a view to get progeny; {{F}}6:  भा. I. 3. १५; VIII. २४. ५०; IX. 1. 3-१२; 2. 1; 6. 4.{{/F}} see Satyavrata; celebrated an अश्वमेध in honour of Mitra and वरुण; out came इला who went to them; {{F}}7:  Br. III. ६०. 1-१०.{{/F}} the Lord of men, and seven worlds with towns; {{F}}8:  वा. ७०. १८.{{/F}} divided the Vedas into four for the pro- gress of the world; {{F}}9:  Ib. ६०. 8.{{/F}} in order to get sons he performed the मित्रावरुण ritual; owing to the होत'स् carelessness a daughter इला came out; she became again a male Sudyumna by name; by an imprecation of शिव he again became a woman near Budha's hermitage. Budha got by her a son by name पुरूरवस्; {{F}}१०:  Vi. IV. 1. 8-१२.{{/F}} interpretation of शब्दब्रह्म by. {{F}}११:  Ib. VI. 5. ६४.{{/F}}

मनु|manu
 (XV) (दक्ष सावर्णी)--the ninth Manu. Born of वरुण; father of भूतकेतु and other sons. पारस् and others were gods of his epoch, and Adbhuta was Indra; Dyu- timat and others were sages. During this period Hari mani- fested himself as ऋषभ. भा. VIII. १३. १८-20. [page२-622+ ३५]

मनु|manu
 (XVI) (रुद्रसावर्णि)--the twelfth Manu; father of देववान् and other sons. ऋतधामन् was Indra. हारित and others were gods. तपोमूर्ति and others were sages. स्वधाम was Hari manifesting in this epoch; {{F}}1:  भा. VIII. १३. २७-29.{{/F}} the fourth सावर्ण Manu in the १२थ् पर्याय। {{F}}2:  Br. IV. 1. ८२-93.{{/F}}

मनु|manu
 (XVII) सावर्ण(इ)--the second Manu in the epoch of the Vaivasvata Manvantara; son of सावर्ण; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. 1. ५१-5, ७३-81.{{/F}} in his age Bali was to reign over the whole world. {{F}}2:  Ib. II. ३६. 4; III. ७३. ५२.{{/F}}

मनु|manu
 (XVIII) (रौच्य)--a सावर्ण Manu of the XIII पर्याय; three groups of gods, all addicted to Soma and ghee through यज्ञस्। Br. IV. 1. ९५-116.

मनु|manu
 (XIX)--(चाक्षुषान्तरम्)--भृगु and other sages lived in this epoch. {{F}}1:  M. 2. १४; 6. 3; 8. १२.{{/F}} There were five classes of devas, Lekha, ऋभव, ऋभाद्य, वारिमूल, and Divaukasa; चाक्- षुष had ten sons commencing with Ruru; {{F}}2:  Ib. 9. २२, २५.{{/F}} King पुरूरवस् flourished in the same line in this epoch. {{F}}3:  Ib. ११५. 7-8.{{/F}}

मनु|manu
 (XX) (औत्तम)--the third Manu; {{F}}1:  M. 3. ४७.{{/F}} father of ten sons; the devas of the epoch are भावनस् and there were also seven sages, कौकुरुण्डि, etc., all engaged in yoga. {{F}}2:  Ib. 9. ११.{{/F}}

मनु|manu
 (XXI) (चाक्षुष) (VI)--the son of चक्षु and वीरिणी; married a royal princess नड्वला and had ten sons. M. 4. ४०; Vi. I. १३. 4.

मनु|manu
 (XXII)--the son of हर्यश्व and father of Pra- tika. Vi. IV. 5. २७. [page२-623+ २९]

मनुस्|manus
--worshipped with Devas for kingdom; their duties in different epochs described. {{F}}1:  भा. II. 3. 9; VIII. १४. 2-१०{{/F}} Fourteen in number; went to Maharloka when their duties were over; {{F}}2:  Br. IV. 2. 2 nad 5.{{/F}} in order: स्वायम्भुव, स्वारोचिष, Auttama, तामस, Raivata, चाक्- षुष; these six are past ones; the future are eight; सावर्ण, पञ्चरौच्यस्, Bhautya and Vaivasvata. {{F}}3:  वा. ६२. 3-4.{{/F}}

मनुकाल|manukaala
--the whole period of the fourteen Manus covering a कल्प of one thousand yugas--the fourteen man- vantaras. भा. VIII. १३. ३६; १४. ११.

मनुग|manuga
--a son of द्युतिमान् after whose name is a Janapada. वा. ३३. २१.

मनुज|manuja
--a विश्वेदेव. M. २०३. १३.

मनुतीर्थ|manutiirtha
--a तीर्थ visited by बलराम. भा. X. ७९. २१.

मनुत्तम|manuttama
 (मनुत्त or मरुत्त)--a king equal to a cakravartin, went to heaven with Samvarta, a sage; father of नरिष्यन्त. वा. ८६. 9.

मनुवन्ती|manuvantii
--a daughter of Tumburu. Br. III. 7. १३.

मनुवम्शधर|manuvamshadhara
--an अवतार् of Hari. भा. II. 7. २०. [page२-624+ २३]

मनुवश|manuvasha
--a son of Madhu. वा. ९५. ४५.

मनुष्यस्|manuShyas
--created out of the रजस् element; {{F}}1:  Vi. I. 5. २३, ३७-8; 6. 1.{{/F}} four वर्णस् of. {{F}}2:  Ib. I. 6. 5.{{/F}}

मनुष्यपितृस्|manuShyapitRs
--are Laukikas (s.v.). Br. II. २८. ७१, ७८, ९५.

मनोजव|manojava
 (I)--a son of मेधातिथि of शाकद्वीप. भा. V. २०. २५.

मनोजव|manojava
 (II)--a son of ईशान and शिवा. Br. II. १०. ७९; वा. २७. ५२.

मनोजव|manojava
 (III)--a Lekha god. Br. II. ३६. ७५.

मनोजव|manojava
 (IV)--the Indra of the चाक्षुष epoch. Br. II. ३६. ७६; Vi. III. 1. २६.

मनोजव|manojava
 (V)--a son of Anila (Anala-म्। प्।) a Vasava. Br. III. 3. २६; M. 5. २५; वा. ६६. २५; Vi. I. १५. ११४.

मनोजव|manojava
 (VI)--a god of one of the ten branches of the हरीत gan2a. Br. IV. 1. ८४; वा. १००. ८९.

मनोजवा|manojavaa
--a R. in क्रौञ्चद्वीप. Br. II. १९. ७५; M. १२२. ८८; वा. ४९. ६९; Vi. II. 4. ५५. [page२-625+ २४]

मनोदण्ड|manodaNDa
--restraint of mind. वा. १७. 6.

मनोनुग|manonuga
 (I)--a son of द्युतिमान् after whom the kingdom, मानोनुग took its name. Br. II. १४. २२, २४.

मनोनुग|manonuga
 (II) (च्)--a region of the क्रौञ्चद्वीप adjoining the वामन hill. Br. II. १४. २४; १९. ७१; M. १२२. ८४.

मनोनुग|manonuga
 (III)--a वर्ष of the hill, वामनक. वा. ४९. ६६.

मनोभवा|manobhavaa
--an Apsarasa. Br. III. 7. 7.

मनोरमा|manoramaa
 (I)--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. २६.

मनोरमा|manoramaa
 (II)--an Apsarasa. वा. ६९. 6.

मनोवती|manovatii
 (I)--the सभा of ब्रह्मा on the first inner- slope of Meru in which reside ईशान and Indra besides sages and seers. वा. ३४. ७२-7.

मनोवती|manovatii
 (II)--a daughter of Tumburu. वा. ६९. ४९.

मनोहरम्|manoharam
--a तीर्थ on the नर्मदा sacred to पितृस्. M. १९४. 7. [page२-626+ २८]

मनोहरा|manoharaa
 (I)--a wife of Dhara. M. 5. २४.

मनोहरा|manoharaa
 (II)--the wife of Dharma, the Vasu. Vi. I. १५. ११३.

मन्कन|mankana
--the form of a Brahmana assumed by गणेश Nikumbha when he appeared in a dream to दिवोदास. Br. III. ६७. ४२.

मन्कुति|mankuti
--a R. from the ऋक्ष hill. Br. II. १६. ३१.

मन्त्रद्रुम|mantradruma
--Indra of the चाक्षुष epoch. भा. VIII. 5. 8.

मन्त्र(इ)नाथा|mantra(i)naathaa
--also मन्त्रिणी, {{F}}1:  Br. IV. १७. २२, २७; २७, ५८; १९. ६१.{{/F}} and मन्त्रिणीश्यामा; war master of ललिता; residence at कदम्बवनवाटिका; {{F}}2:  Ib. IV. ३१. ८२, ८९.{{/F}} helped कुमारी in vanquishing भण्ड's sons; rode on Kiri- cakra; consulted दण्डनाथा; {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. २६. 2, ८३, ११३; २७. ५८.{{/F}} invoked मदीरासिन्धु (s.v.). {{F}}4:  Ib. IV. २८. १४, ४८, ९२, १०३.{{/F}}

मन्त्र(इ)नायिका|mantra(i)naayikaa
--see मन्त्रनाथा. Br. IV. १७. ३१, ३३, ४०.

मन्त्रप्रवचनस्|mantrapravachanas
--a branch of the Vedic literature. वा. ५८. १४.

मन्त्रब्राह्मणम्|mantrabraahmaNam
--a branch of Vedic literature; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३१. १२; ३३. ५४; वा. ५९. १३८.{{/F}} ety. of. {{F}}2:  Ib. ५०. १४१; ६१. १०२.{{/F}} [page२-627+ ३८]

मन्त्रम्|mantram
 (I)--(also मन्त्रस्थानम्, Council Cham- ber) consultation to be held with many and individually and with people in whom the king has confidence; at least one expert must be consulted; generally with people learned in the three Vedas, elders who have the ability to correct the erring king; {{F}}1:  M. २१५. ४८-52.{{/F}} kingdom rests on mantra; {{F}}2:  Ib. २२०. ३३.{{/F}} king not to decide alone nor to consult too many; {{F}}3:  Ib. २२०. ३७.{{/F}} भण्ड's War Council. {{F}}4:  Br. IV. २१. २१; २५. 3{{/F}}

मन्त्रम्|mantram
 (II)--a portion of the पूर्व samhita1. वा. ६१. ६५.

मन्त्रस्|mantras
--take the food offered in sacrifices to the पितृस् as the calf finds out its mother among the lost cows; {{F}}1:  Br. II. २८. ९१; वा. ५९. ६१.{{/F}} came out of discontent, fear, difficulties, happiness and misery of ऋषिस्; later put into form and order by sages; differences in मन्त्रस् as many as twenty-four; {{F}}2:  Br. II. ३२. ६८; ३३. ४२; वा. ५९. ३५-61; M. १४५. ६२-3.{{/F}} the two major divisions --ग्राम्यम् and आरण्यकम्; {{F}}3:  Br. II. ३५. ७३, ८५; IV. 8. ५१-3, ५७.{{/F}} Veda mantras, विष्णु mantra, दुर्गा mantra, गाणपत mantra, etc.; {{F}}4:  Ib. IV. ३८. 4.{{/F}} ety of. {{F}}5:  वा. ५९. १४१.{{/F}}

मन्त्रमाला|mantramaalaa
--a R. in कुशद्वीप. भा. V. २०. १५.

मन्त्रय|mantraya
--a son of सत्यभामा. वा. ९६. २३८.

