मन्दर|mandara
 (I)--(Mt.) on one side of Meru; one of विष्- kambhagiris round the Meru; sacred to शिव; in its valleys हिरण्यकशिपु performed austerities; used in churning the milk ocean; lest it should sink in the sea Hari in the form of कूर्म supported the mountain; was lifted up with great difficulty by the Gods and Asuras, who could not carry it to the ocean, when Hari asked गरुड to bear it on his back to the sea and which he did. {{F}}1:  Br. IV. 9. ५१, ५६, ६०; भा. I. 3. १६; III. २८. २७; V. १६. ११; VII. 3. 2; 7. 2; VIII. 5. १०; 6. ३३-9; X. ४०. १८; XII. १३. 2; M. ६९. 1; २४९. १५; २५०. २६; २५१. ३५; Vi. I. 9. ७७, ८४.{{/F}} Recipient of mango fruits as large as hill-tops falling from a divine mango tree, ११०० yoja- nas high (see अरुणोदा). {{F}}2:  भा. V. १६. १६.{{/F}} Here पृथु died and was cre- mated. {{F}}3:  Ib. IV. २३. २४.{{/F}} (Also known, Mandaragiri and मन्दराचलम्). भद्राश्व vars2a and Caitraratha park in; {{F}}4:  M. ८३. २०, ३१.{{/F}} शिव spent his honeymoon here with उमा after marrying her; उमा's delights in the woods. {{F}}5:  Ib. ११३. ४५; १५४. ४९६, ५७३; १६३. ८७; १८३. 1.{{/F}} [page२-630+ २६]

