ममता|mamataa
--the wife of the sage उशिज (Asija-वा। प्।), (Utathya वि। प्।) whose younger brother बृहस्पति wanted sexual union with her when she was pregnant eight months; he raped her, and cursed the baby in the womb which obstructed the completion of the act, to be ever in darkness, and hence the child was born blind, दीर्घतमस्; the result of the union was भरद्वाज; ममता, abandoned Bharad- वाज fearing divorce by her husband on account of the in- discret act of बृहस्पति (s.v.) see also दीर्घतमस्. भा. IX. २०. ३७-39; Br. III. ७४. ३६-7; M. ४८. ३२-41; ४९. १७, २६; वा. ९९. ३६-8; Vi. IV. १९ 16.

मय|maya
 (I)--The architect of the Asuras of the other world, and a past master in the practice of माया। Served as calf for the मायिन्स् to derive माया from Earth. Built aerial cities, three in number, of gold, silver and iron for the pro- tection of the Asuras, and constructed the divine सभा। The cities were well equipped and furnished, with paintings and drawings of couples of नागस् and Asuras, pigeons, parrots and शारिकस्, interspersed by charming gardens of flowers and fruits with lakes of crystal waters. Being the Lord of Tripura which he built, he took part with Bali in the देवासुर war, and also fought with विश्वकर्- man; {{F}}1:  भा. I. १५. 8; II. 7. ३७; IV. १८. २०; V. २४. 9-१०; VII. १०. २२ and २९, ५१-60.{{/F}} son of विश्वकर्मन्; सुरेणु was his sister; {{F}}2:  Br. III. ५९. २१; IV. १२. 3; २०. ४६; ३१. 7; वा. ८४. २०-1.{{/F}} had an evil dream that a naked lady and a man of three eye burning the city: reported it to the सभा: was explained by नारद: precautions for defence: army stationed at respec- tive places of vantage; विद्युन्मालि was over-powered; Maya constructed a tank of medicinal waters to make the dead live and restored विद्युन्मालि. Knowing this immortalising fluid, ब्रह्मा and Hari drank the whole of it; fierce war; शिव directed his arrows against the three cities and killed the Asuras by destroying their cities. Maya's address to the Asuras for a bold stand. विद्युन्मालि and तारक were killed. Maya was let off and asked to live in a special house [page२-635+ ३२] after burning the city. In the तारकामय it is said he rode on a golden chariot with arms and weapons. {{F}}3:  M. ch. १२९; १३१. २५-30; १३४. 9-३०; chh. १३५-140. १७३. 2-१३; १७७. 3-6.{{/F}}

मय|maya
 (II)--the Asura architect and a contemporary of कृष्ण. His son enslaved the gopas and hid them in a cave. कृष्ण recovered them; {{F}}1:  भा. II. 7. ३१.{{/F}} freed from the forest fire of काण्- डव by Arjuna, he erected a सभा for the use of the पाण्- डवस्. Once Duryodhana (s.v.) mistook a floor of this for a sheet of water and had a nasty fall; {{F}}2:  Ib. X. ५५. २१; ७१. ४५; ५८. २७; ७५. ३४ and ३७.{{/F}} Supplied a magic car to शाल्व under orders of शिव. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ७६. 7; ७७. २८.{{/F}}

मय|maya
 (III)--an Asura; Lord of तलातल region, won the grace of शिव and attained मोक्ष by सत्सन्ग। A follower of वृत्र in his battle with Indra; {{F}}1:  भा. V. २४. २८; XI. १२. 5; VI. १०. ३१.{{/F}} wife रम्भा and father of six sons; {{F}}2:  Br. III. 6. 5 and २८; वा. ६८. २८-9.{{/F}} had daughters like उपदानवी. {{F}}3:  M. 6. २१.{{/F}}

मय|maya
 (IV)--father of माया. Br. II. 9. ६४.

मय|maya
 (V)--an author on architecture. M. २५२. 2.

