--the thirteenth अवतार् of विष्णु (नारायण) to delude the Asuras from having any share of the अमृत and distribute it to the Devas; reappeared in that form before शिव at his request and शिव who got enamoured of her, ran after her letting his seed fall down; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 3. १७; VIII. 8. ४१-46; Chh. 9 and १२ (whole) M. २५१. 7; वा. २५. ४८.{{/F}} a शक्ति. {{F}}2:  Br. IV. १०. २७. ३४; १९. ६५ and ७४; २०. 6, ३८ and ५७; ४४. ७२ and १४१.{{/F}} [page२-743+ २६]

मौञ्ज|maunja
--आर्षेय Pravara (भार्गवस्). M. १९५. ३७.

मौञ्जकेश|maunjakesha
--an आत्रेय-gotraka1ra. M. १९७. 7.

मौञ्जयनि|maunjayani
--a sage. M. १९८. २०.

मौञ्ज वृष्टि|maunja vRShTi
--a Pravara (Angiras). M. १९६. १८.

मौद्गलायन|maudgalaayana
--a भार्गव gotraka1ra. M. १९५. २२.

मौद्गल्यस् (काण्व मुद्गलस्)|maudgalyas (kaaNva mudgalas)
--कन्ठ Mudgalas- वा। प्।) from Mudgala, son of भद्राश्व; Brahmanas with क्षत्रिय profession; belonging to the Angirasa line; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २१. ३३; M. ५०. 5; वा. ९९. १९८; Vi. IV. १९. ६०.{{/F}} no marriage alliance with ताण्डि or Angiras. {{F}}2:  M. १९६. ४३.{{/F}}

मौनस्|maunas
--eleven of them ruled as kings, (१८ kings- वा। प्।); for three centuries, while the total reign of आभीरस्, Gardabhins, Kankas, Yavanas, तुरुष्कस् and गुरुण्डस् amounted to १०९९ (१००९ वि। प्।) years. Thereafter came the Maunas. भा. XII. 1. ३०-32; Br. III. ७४. १७३-7; वा. ९९. ३६०; Vi. IV. २४. ५३-54.

मौनिकस्(च्)|maunikas(ch)
--a दाक्षिणाथ्य des4a. वा. ४५. १२७. [page२-744+ २६]

मौनिदेश (च्)|maunidesha (ch)
--a kingdom after Muni. Br. II. १४. २६.

मौनेयस्|mauneyas
--Devagandharvas; १६ in number; (२४ वा। प्।) Apsarasas were their younger sisters; had six daughters. Br. III. 7. 1-2; वा. ६९. 1, 4, १०.

मौर्यस्|mauryas
--(Maurvyas-वि। प्।) succeeded the Nandas. The पुराण speaks of ten kings ruling for १३७ (१७३ वि। प्।) years. Only nine kings are mentioned from Candragupta to बृहद्रथ; were succeeded by the शुन्गस्. {{F}}1:  भा. XII. 1. १२ and १५; Br. III. ७४. १४९; वा. ९९. ३३६; Vi. IV. २४. २७, ३२-3.{{/F}} म्।प्। men- tions शतधन्व, बृहद्रथ, शक and his grandson दश- ratha and his son; the first four are missing. {{F}}2:  M. २७२. २२, २६.{{/F}}

मौलि|mauli
 (I)--a Tripravara. M. १९६. ३३.

मौलि|mauli
 (II)--a son of मणिभद्र. वा. ६९. १५६.

मौलिकस्|maulikas
--a southern country. Br. II. १६. ५८.

मौसल|mausala
--the battle with clubs after the महाभारत war. M. ७०. ११.

मौहूर्तिकी|mauhuurtikii
--the गति of the sun; when the sun is in माघ it moves past southward; returning from the south [page२-745+ ३७] it goes to विषु rising in the north of the milky ocean; when the sun is in श्रवण नक्षत्र it goes to the north and rises in the north end of शाकद्वीपम्. वा. ५०. १२१-7.

मौहूर्तिकस्|mauhuurtikas
--a गण born of मुहूर्ता and Dharma. These regulate the timely results of the actions of Beings. भा. VI. 6. 9.

म्लेच्छस्|mlechChas
 (I)--born out of the left side of Vena's body when the latter's body was churned; {{F}}1:  M. १०. 7;{{/F}} begin with Anu, son of ययाति; ruled by दक्ष; ruled by Turvasu; ruled by the hundred sons of Pracetas of Druhyu family in the east; the rule of the kings; {{F}}2:  Ib. ३४. ३०; 4. ५४; ३३. १४; ४८. 9; ५०. ७६; भा. IX. २३. १६.{{/F}} not to be seen in कुशद्वीप; शकस् (परादस्-वि। प्।), Pallavas (Paplava-वि। प्।) and काम्बोजस्, all Mlecchas; (आभिरस्-वि। प्।) गुरुण्दस् and वृषलस्, also belonged to this group; {{F}}3:  Br. II. १६. १२; १९. ६०; ३१. ७९, ८४ and ९०; III. २०. 5; ४८. ४८-9; ६८. ४४; ७३. १०९; ७४. ११-12, २०३-6, २१५; M. २७३. २२; Vi. IV. 3. ४८; १७. 5; २४. ६९; V. ३८. २८.{{/F}} kingdoms of, found in the lotus coming out of the naval of the Lord; {{F}}4:  M. १६९. ११;{{/F}} their kingdoms side by side with those of the आर्यस्; {{F}}5:  Ib. २७३. २५.{{/F}} people who live in their countries are ineligible for पार्वन s4ra1ddha; {{F}}6:  Ib. १६. १६.{{/F}} attain salva- tion at Benares; {{F}}7:  Ib. १८१. १९.{{/F}} do not molest the women of their enemies; {{F}}8:  Ib. १८८. ५१.{{/F}} to be conquered by Kalki; {{F}}9:  Br. II. १८. ४३.{{/F}} put down by Pramati god. {{F}}१०:  M. ११४. ११-12; १२१. ४३; १४४. ५३.{{/F}}

म्लेच्छस्|mlechChas
 (II)--these were the elder Madhucchandasas, who were cursed by विश्वामित्र to become Mlecchas; defeated by Bharata; these were the Mlecchas of the north; {{F}}2:  भा. IX. १६. ३३; २०. ३०; २३. १६; XII. 1. ४०-43.{{/F}} [page२-746+ ११] worship progenitors; {{F}}3:  वा. ९३. ४४.{{/F}} eleven kings ruled for ३०० years. {{F}}4:  Ib. ९९. ३६४.{{/F}} Then Kolikilas followed; {{F}}5:  वा. ९९. ३६४.{{/F}} their धर्म described. {{F}}6:  Ib. ९९. ३९२-400.{{/F}} ^1 वा. ४५. ८२; ४७. ४१; ४८. १५, २१, ३६; ५८. ७८; ८३. ११२; ९९. १२, २६८; ९८. १०९.

म्लेच्छगणस्|mlechChagaNas
--foreign tribes on the हिमालयन् slopes. वा. ४१. ४६. [page२-747+ 8]

यक्ष|yaxa
 (I)--a राक्षस and a son of खशा. As he wanted to eat his own mother, he got the name of यक्ष; of four hands and four feet, a fearful figure wandering in the night in search of prey; took the form of Vasuruci and lived with the apsaras क्रथुस्थला in Nandana; she bore him a son रजतनाभ; went home in the हिमालयस् with the son, when क्रथुस्थला came to know of his birth as a राक्षस. Br. III. 7. ६०, १००-17; २२. १४; ४१. ३०; ७१. १११; वा. ६९. १६०, १६७.

यक्ष|yaxa
 (II)--a son of गान्दिनी. वा. ९६. ११०.

यक्षस्|yaxas
--a semi-celestial group, usually of the class of demons; born of विश्वा and कश्यप; {{F}}1:  भा. II. 6. १३; VI. 8. २४; X. 6. २७; ६२. १९; ८५. ४१; Br. II. ३२. 1-2; ३५. १९१; ३६. ११८; M. 6. ४६.{{/F}} followers of Rudra (शिव), their overlord; their lord, Kubera; {{F}}2:  भा. IV. १०. 5; XI. १६. १६; २३. २४; M. 8. 5.{{/F}} milked the cow- earth, with वैश्रवण as the calf and आम as the vessel; {{F}}3:  Ib. १०. २२.{{/F}} worship the बर्हिषद् manes; {{F}}4:  Ib. १५. 4.{{/F}} helped वृत्र against Indra and went with सती to दक्ष's sacrifice; {{F}}5:  भा. VI. १०. २०; IV. 4. 4, ३४.{{/F}} sport of; {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ९०. 9.{{/F}} got मोक्ष meditating on Hari; {{F}}7:  Ib. VII. 7. ५०.{{/F}} usurped the आनर्त kingdom of Kakudmi when he was absent at ब्रह्मा's court; {{F}}8:  Ib. IX. 3. ३६.{{/F}} came with the gods to see कृष्ण and saw कृष्ण retiring to his own region; {{F}}9:  Ib. VII. 8. ३८; XI. ३१. 2.{{/F}} (see पुण्यजनस्); vanquished by रावण; {{F}}१०:  Br. III. 7. २५५.{{/F}} worship the पितृस् and ruin the श्राद्ध; {{F}}११:  Ib. III. १०. ३८, १११; ११. ८१; IV. 2. २६; १४. 4; २०. ५०; ३०. 9; ३३. ७५.{{/F}} their kingdom; {{F}}१२:  M. २३. ३९; १२१. ४८.{{/F}} their loka; {{F}}१३:  Br. IV. ३९. ५६.{{/F}} the nails of वामन when he grew. {{F}}१४:  M. २४६. ५४.{{/F}} [page३-002+ २७]

यक्षगणस्|yaxagaNas
--chiefly four, Loheyas, Bharateyas, कृशाङ्- geyas, and विशालेयस् after the four daughters of सुयशा (स्।व्।). वा. ६९. १५-6.

यक्षराक्षसस्|yaxaraaxasas
--the tribe born to Kapila, the यक्ष and केशिनी--inferior to Gandharvas by three steps. Br. III. 7. १४६-167; IV. 4. 2; वा. ६९. १७८.

यक्षास्य|yaxaasya
--a वानर chief. Br. III. 7. २३५.

यक्षिस्|yaxis
--women of the यक्षस्. भा. X. ९०. 9.

यक्षिनी|yaxinii
--a शक्ति; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. २०. १५.{{/F}} an image of; surrounded by the Devas, दानवस् and the नागस्; hoods and two tongues to be carved above the head; also the spirits of the air and the evil spirits encircle her. {{F}}2:   M. २६१. ४७-50.{{/F}}

यक्षी|yaxii
--one of the ten पीठस् for images with three मेखलस्; this gives one plenty of cows. M. २६२. 6, 8, १७.

यक्षेश्वर|yaxeshvara
--is Kubera (स्।व्।); {{F}}1:  Br. IV. २०. ५०.{{/F}} a follower of शिव in battle; helped वामदेव S4iva in his war with Soma. {{F}}2:  M. २३. ३८.{{/F}}

यक्ष्म|yaxma
--Phthisis which afflicted Soma as a result of दक्ष's curse. भा. VI. 6. २३. [page३-003+ ३७]

यजनी|yajanii
--the wife of शुक्र; mother of देवयानी. वा. ६५. ८४.

यजमान|yajamaana
--the man who installs a new image, becomes part of the deity; the presiding deity is Ugra. M. २६५. ३८, ४१.

यजुस्|yajus
 (I)--imparted to वैशम्पायन {{F}}1:  भा. I. 4. २१; IV. 4. ३२; X. 7. १४; ५३. १२.{{/F}} its history; {{F}}2:  Ib. XII. 6. ६४-65.{{/F}} सूर्य celebrated in; {{F}}3:  Ib. XII. ११. ४७.{{/F}} fruits of its repetition; {{F}}4:  Ib. XII. १२. ६२.{{/F}} arranged by व्यास; learnt by the Asuras; {{F}}5:  Br. II. ३३. ३७; ३५. ७३; IV. १२. १७.{{/F}} rearranged by वैशम्पायन into four. It is Yajus by the action of यजनम्। It is चतुर्- होत्रम्, divided into four parts, hence यज्ञ; three versions --northern with स्यामायनि, middle country with आसुरि, and eastern with ८६ Samhitas अलम्बी; {{F}}6:  Ib. II. ३४. १४-22; ३५. ११; वा. ६०. १४, १७, २२; ६१. 5-8.{{/F}} personified as present in वरुण's sacrifice; {{F}}7:  Br. III. 1. २४; वा. ६५. २५.{{/F}} with वृत्ताध्य, face in the shape of ॐ and with सूक्त, ब्राह्मण and mantra; served as horse of त्रिपुरारि's chariot; {{F}}8:  M. ९३. १२९; १३३. ३१.{{/F}} length of, including शुक्रियस् and याज्ञवल्क्य portions; {{F}}9:  वा. ३१. ३३; ३२. 2; १०१. ३४६.{{/F}} two मात्रस्, ईकाराक्षर। {{F}}१०:  Ib. २६. २०.{{/F}}

यजुस्|yajus
 (II)--one of the ten horses of the moon's chariot. Br. II. २३. ५६.

यजुस्|yajus
 (III)--the fifth son of Caidyoparicara, the Vasu and गिरिका. M. ५०. २८.

यजुस्|yajus
 (IV)--one of the मरुत्गणस्. वा. ६७. १२९.

यजुदाय|yajudaaya
--a son of देवकी. वा. ९६. १७३. [page३-004+ ४३]

यजुर्धामन्|yajurdhaaman
--a son of पर्वश. Br. II. ११. १६.

यजुर्वाक्यार्थपण्डितस्|yajurvaakyaarthapaNDitas
--interpreters of the Yajur Veda. They are लोमहर्षणिकस्, काश्यपिकस् and सावर्- णिकस्. वा. ६१. ६०.

यजुर् वेद|yajur veda
--see Yajus; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३४. १४-18: M. ९३. १२९; १३३. ३१. वा. २६. २०. ६०. १४, १७, २२; ६१. 5-8; ६५. २५.{{/F}} divided into four parts from which originated यज्ञ, performed by four orders of priests --अध्वर्यु to recite यजुस्, होत, the र्क्स्, and उद्गात, the सामन्, and ब्रह्मा, the अथर्वमन्त्रस्, {{F}}2:  Vi. III. 4. 8-१२.{{/F}} its शाखस् are २७; arranged by वैशम्पायन, pupil of व्यास, and taught to his disciples including याज्ञवल्क्य; the latter was made to vomit for his behaviour, all the texts, which the other disciples digested, in the form of partridges and hence this portion came to be known as तैत्तिरीय; but याज्ञवल्क्य prayed to the Sun-god who initiated him into the other por- tions of the Yajus in the form of a horse and hence called वाजसेनेय; {{F}}3:  Ib. III. ch. 5 (whole).{{/F}} part of विष्णु. {{F}}4:  Ib. V. 1. ३७.{{/F}}

यजूम्षि|yajuumShi
--from the right (south वि। प्।) face of Brah- मा; {{F}}1:  Br. II. 8. ५१ and ५५; Vi. I. 5. ५४.{{/F}} one learned in, becomes an expert in यज्ञस्। {{F}}2:  वा. ७९. ९५.{{/F}}

यज्ञ|yaJNa
 (I)--the seventh अवतार् of विष्णु; born with दक्षिणा as twins to अकूती and Ruci. Adopted as his son by his grandfather स्वायम्भुव Manu. {{F}}1:  भा. I. 3. १२; III. १९. १३; IV. 1. 4-5; VI. 8. १५; VIII. 1. 6.{{/F}} Followed by the याम gods, slew the Asuras and यातुधानस् who attacked and sought to devour स्वायम्भुव Manu engaged in con- templation of Hari, and ruled the celestial kingdom; {{F}}2:  Ib. VIII. 1. १७-18; X. 6. २२.{{/F}} wor- shipped for attaining celebrity; {{F}}3:  Ib. II. 3. 7; Br. II. ३४. 7.{{/F}} to यज्ञ and दक्षिणा were born twelve sons who were known as यामस् in the period of स्वायम्भुव; यज्ञ also याम; {{F}}4:  वा. १०. १९-20; Br. II. 9. ४४ff.{{/F}} constitutes धर्म and [page३-005+ ४४] मन्त्र; the Yajva goes to heaven; {{F}}5:  वा. ३२. १६.{{/F}} a soma yajus of पशु, द्रव्य, हविस्, ऋत्विक्स्, दक्षिण। {{F}}6:  Ib. ५७. १०७; ५९. ४२.{{/F}}

यज्ञ|yaJNa
 (II)--a जयादेव. Br. III. 3. 7; 4. 3; वा. ६६. 7.

यज्ञ|yaJNa
 (III)--origin of, in Treta and dispute on its nature, whether हिम्सा or not; {{F}}1:  वा. ५७. ८६-125.{{/F}} trees fit for; समान, प्लक्ष, nyagrodha, अश्वत्थ, udumbara, vikarika, bilva, चन्दण, sarala, देवदारु, शाल, khadira; unfit are: श्लेष्मातक, nak- तमाल, kapittha, शाल्मलि, नीप, विभीतक and those which are enveloped by creepers and are the residence of birds; {{F}}2:  Ib. ७५. ७१-76.{{/F}} of शूद्रस् by Brahmanas for livelihood (वृत्ति); {{F}}3:  Ib. ९९. ४२६; १०१. २९६; ११२. 1 and १४.{{/F}} performance of, pleases the gods who give rain; {{F}}4:  Vi. I. 6. 8.{{/F}} personified as God with wife दक्षिणा and twelve sons, generally known as यामस्; {{F}}5:  Ib. I. 7. २१.{{/F}} born of विष्णु and आकूती in the स्वायम्भुव epoch; of तुषिता in स्वारोचिष, of सत्या in Uttama, of Havya in तामस and सम्भूति in Raivata; {{F}}6:  Ib. III. 1. ३६-40.{{/F}} duty of all. {{F}}7:  Ib. III. 8. २२{{/F}}

