यदुस्|yadus
--(also Yadu kula and Yadu वम्श); members and descendants innumerable; one hundred and one families recognised. {{F}}1:  भा. X. ९०. ४०-4.{{/F}} Their king was Ugrasena. Ill-treated by Kamsa, they migrated to different countries like Kuru and पाञ्चाल, and became delighted at Kamsa's death. Their Purohita was Garga. {{F}}2:  Ib. X. 1. ६९; 2. 2-3; ४५. १५; 8. 1.{{/F}} Krsna born among them; {{F}}3:  M. २४६, ९०.{{/F}} cursed by [page३-011+ ३१] ययाति, his successors could not be kings; unacceptable to good men according to शिशुपाल; {{F}}4:  भा. X. ४५. १३; ७४. ३६.{{/F}} took part in the marriage festivities of कृष्ण and रुक्मिनी, and attended the राजसूय of युधिष्ठिर; turned into a caste by Puramjaya; {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ५४. ५८; ७५. १२; XII. 1. ३६.{{/F}} destroyed by कृष्ण before he left the earth, under the pretext of the Brahmanas' curse; the rest lost their reason after कृष्ण's departure to Heaven, drank wine and killed one another. Four or five alone left alive. Attained योग through the grace of Datta; became defunct after the महाभारत war. {{F}}6:  Ib. XI. 1. 4-5; ३१. १६; I. १५. २२-6; II. 7. 4; M. ७०. १२.{{/F}}

