यम|yama
 (I)--(Vaivasvata) the Lord of पितृस्; punishes men after death according to their actions, sinful or other- wise. {{F}}1:  भा. V. २६. 6; M. 8. 5; वा. ६२. १८६; ६५. ५२; ७०. 8; Vi. I. २२. 5.{{/F}} A son of Vivasvat (सूर्य)  and सम्ज्ञा; explains the nature of धर्म and the glory of Hari to his messen- gers (यमदूतस्, s.v.). Appeared in the form of a child before the queen and the subjects of सुयज्ञ weeping over his dead body and showed the truth that no amount of wail- ing would bring the dead back to life; {{F}}2:  भा. VI. 6. ४०; VIII. १३. 9; VI. 3. १२-34; VII. 2. ३६-58;{{/F}} welcomed राम and कृष्ण and fulfilled their desire by restoring सान्दिपानि's son; presented पृठु with a rod of justice. Punished नृग to be a lizard for having given a cow of a ब्रह्मण as a gift to another, and as the owner refused to accept the apologies and compensation offered by नृग; {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ४५. ४२-6; IV. १५. १५; III. ३०. २३; X. ६४. १६-24.{{/F}} fought with कालनाभ in the देवासुर war; rode on buffalo to help Indra against कृष्ण taking away पारिजात, but discomfited, ran away in fear; {{F}}4:  Ib. VIII. १०. २९; X. [६५ (v) ४१]; [६६ (v) ३३-5]; Vi. V. ३०. ६०; VI. 5. ४४.{{/F}} his authority set aside in the case of अजामिल. Dhruva is said to have set his foot on his head; was a शुद्र for a hundred years owing to a curse; {{F}}5:  भा. VI. 3. 2; IV. १२. ३०; I. १३. १५.{{/F}} His penance at गोकर्ण and शिव made him लोकपाल; his city being Samyamana; represents the planet शनैश्चर; served as calf for पितृस् milk- ing the earth; धर्मराज; Lord of three deva गणस्-- Amarttas, अप्रकाशस्, and ज्योतिष्मन्तस्; {{F}}6:  Br. II. २१. ३१; २४. ४९; २९. ६५; ३६. २०८; III. 1. ५२; 7. २५३ and ३३०; १३. ७२; M. ९३. १४; २६६. २१ and ६३; वा. ५०. ८८; ६९. २१५; Vi. II. 8. 9; III. 7. १९, ३५.{{/F}} narrated to शश- bindu varieties of श्राद्ध; protested against the ill-treat- ment by his stepmother छाया and was cursed by her to lose his legs. [Cursed his legs to be sores and worms. His father gave him a cock to eat them. म्।प्।]. The father assured their restoration after a temporary loss; overlord of पितृस्. {{F}}7:  Br. III. १८. 1; २४. 4; ५९. २३, ५२-80; M. ११. 4-२०.{{/F}} in charge of hells; {{F}}8:  Br. IV. 2. १५१; 7. ५४.{{/F}} buffalo, his riding animal; {{F}}9:  M. ६७. ११.{{/F}} his ac- tive part in Tripuram, defeated by कालनेमि; {{F}}१०:  Ib. १३३. ६३; १३७. ३२; १३८. २५; १७७. ५०.{{/F}} burnt with काम and attained godhood again by pleasing शन्कर by तपस्; {{F}}११:  Ib. १९१. ११२-4.{{/F}} dialogue of, with his servant about those who could not be taken to his region. {{F}}१२:  Vi. II. 6. 6; III. 7. 5, १३-20.{{/F}} acted as calf when Antaka milked the cow-earth; other names of; world of; {{F}}१३:  M. १०. १९; ३१. १२; ९३. १४; १०२. २२-3; १२४. २२; १४६. ७७.{{/F}} in the war against तारक: war with Grasana and the latter's suc- cess. {{F}}१४:  Ib. १४८. ७९-81; १५०. 1-४९; Vi. III. 2. 2.{{/F}} सम्वाद with सावित्री; the latter's praise of; {{F}}१५:  M. २११. १४-28 and ch. २१३ (whole).{{/F}} काल and मृत्यु are assistants; god to be worshipped in house building. {{F}}१६:  Ib. २५०. ४६; २५३. २५.{{/F}}  Image of, with Citragupta by the side; gift of [page३-013+ २८] buffalo pleasing to; {{F}}१७:  Ib. २६१. १२; २६८. १३.{{/F}} (धर्मराज): a golden image of him standing on a copper plate to be given to guru in सप्तमी- svapana; {{F}}१८:  Ib. ६८. २०.{{/F}} weapon of दण्ड, used by, in the battle of Tri- puram; {{F}}१९:  Ib. १३५. ७७.{{/F}} seen by सावित्री while taking the life of her hus- band; blessed her with three requests of hers and finally the life of her husband; {{F}}२०:  Ib. २१०. 5, chh. २११-14.{{/F}} meting out justice impartially; {{F}}२१:  Ib. २१३. 3.{{/F}} father of two daughters उपदानवी and हिमा. {{F}}२२:  वा. ६८. २३; ६९. ६१; ७५. ५६; ८२. 1; १०१. १५०, २८६; १०६, ४६; १०८. 4 and ३१; ११० 10 and ३८.{{/F}}

