यशोदा|yashodaa
 (I)--the wife of Nanda (gopa); {{F}}1:  भा. I. 8. ३१; X. 2. 9; M. ४७. 7; Vi. IV. १५. ३१.{{/F}} gave birth to a female child who was योगमाया incarnate. Without her knowledge, Vasudeva placed कृष्ण born on the same day in her bed and removed the girl to his residence. This was known to नारद. {{F}}2:  Bha. X. 3. ४७-53; ३६. १७; वा. ९६. २०६-9.{{/F}} Regarded कृष्ण as her own child; per- formed रक्षा to कृष्ण after his killing पूतना; her concern at कृष्ण's kicking the cart (शकटासुर) upside down, and शान्ति arranged; distressed at कृष्ण being carried away by the whirlwind (तृणावर्त); glad to see him alive; her con- cern at कृष्ण's eating mud, and wonder when he revealed his true form and the whole universe in his mouth; binding of कृष्ण with a rope for breaking the pot and stealing butter; took home कृष्ण playing on the river-bank; intense love to कृष्ण; joy at his escape from कालीय; surprise at कृष्ण holding Govardhana; recalled his exploits at Uddhava's visit, and gave him a hearty welcome. {{F}}3:  भा. X. 6. १९-29; Chh. 7-9 (whole); ११. १४-20; १५. ४४; १७. १५; २५. ३०; ४६. २८-9.{{/F}} Went to Syamanta- पञ्चक and was embraced with affection by रोहिणी and देवकी; {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ८२. ३६-9.{{/F}} represents the Mother Earth; {{F}}5:  Br. III. ७१. २१२-3, २३६ and २३९.{{/F}} remedy of, against बालदोष; {{F}}6:  Vi. V. 1. ७७; 2, 3; 3. २०.{{/F}} prayer of, to शकट; {{F}}7:  Ib. V. 5. १२.{{/F}} rope round the belly of कृष्ण for mischief. {{F}}8:  Ib. V. 6. 7, १४; 7. २०.{{/F}} [page३-023+ २४]

यशोदा|yashodaa
 (II)--the mind-born daughter of उपहूत Pitr2s; wife of विश्वमहत्; mother of खट्वान्ग. Br. III. १०. ९०; वा. ७३. ४०-41.

