--a partisan of जरासन्ध stationed by him at the western gate of मथुरा during its siege, and on the southern gate of Gomanta during its siege; went to Sya- मन्तपञ्चक for the solar eclipse. भा. X. ५०. ११[5]; ५२. ११[9]; ८२. २६. [page३-032+ ४७]

युधिष्ठिर|yudhiShThira
--a son of कुन्ती and पाण्डु born of Dharma, and father of Prativindhya and Sudhanu. Devaka was another son by पौरवी; descendants of अजमीढ; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २२. २७-30; I. १५. १३; Br. III. ७१. १५४ and २५९; M. ४६. 9; ५०. ४९; १०३. 2; १८९. 1; वा. ९६. १५३; ९९. २४४; ११२. ४४; Vi. IV. १४. ३५.{{/F}} was defeated in a game of dice and was banished to the forest with his brothers and their wife. Was met and consoled by कृष्ण and सत्यभामा. कृष्ण's respects to: heard from नारद that कृष्ण was the Supreme Hari and was much pleased. Enquired of Him when he met him at the city of the पाञ्चालस्. He and his four brothers were met by कृत- varman. {{F}}2:  भा. X. ६४. 4-१०; ५८. 4 and ११; VII. १५. ७९; X. ५२. [५६ (v) 5-8]; ५७. १०[4].{{/F}} His desire to perform the राजसूय; joy at कृष्ण's visit: provided suitable lodgings for कृष्ण and his family. Addressing of the assembly on his desire to perform the राजसूय, कृष्ण asked him to get ready by defeating all the kings and bringing thus all the earth under his control: sent out his brothers in the four directions who defeated kings and brought much wealth. Was glad of जरासन्ध's death at the hands of his brothers: Sent for Purohitas for the sacrifice and invited all his kith and kin. The यज्ञ comparable to that of वरुण; attended by all gods. For doing honour to the सदस्यस् there was some doubt about the first place, and Sahadeva's suggestion of कृष्ण's name was accepted by all except शिशुपाल who insulted him in the public assembly. कृष्ण's silence. The पाण्डवस् with the Matsyas and others unsheathed their swords, and कृष्ण sent his चक्र which cut off his head. After अवभृत, युधिष्ठिर shone like Indra. All took leave of him in joy except Duryodhana, who became jealous of the success of the राजसूय and of द्रौपदी, and of कृष्ण. Heard of Duryodhana's fall in the सभा and sent कृष्ण with dress and ornaments to him, which he rejected. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ७०. ४१; ७१. २३-6 and ४४; ७२. 1-१४; ७३. ३५; Chh. ७४ and ७५ (whole); ७६. 2[3]; ७७. 7.{{/F}} On the occasion of the राजसूय, asked नारद how Caidya, शिशुपाल and Dantavaktra, haters of Hari became merged with him after their death, as also about सनातन धर्म; {{F}}4:  Ib. VII. 1. १२-20 and ३०; ११. 1.{{/F}} was met by उपप्लाव्य, by कृष्ण and the other Yadus; {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ७८[95 (v) 2-5]; Ch. ७८ whole; ७९. २४; ८० [5-6], [१६].{{/F}} went to कुरुक्षेत्र for war. On his side were विराट, Drupada, शीखण्डि, धृष्टद्युम्न, सात्यकि, Kekayas, Saibya and others. Killed शाल्व in the field. Welcomed बलराम after [page३-033+ ३५] the war, and left for हास्तिनपुर and was anointed king: rule of righteousness. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ७८[95 (v) 2-5]; Ch. ७८ whole; ७९. २४; ८० [5-6], [१६].{{/F}} Felt aggrieved over the slaughter of his kith and kin: agreed with द्रौपदी regarding the release of अश्वत्थाम, went with his brothers to see भीष्म in his death-bed, like Kubera with the यक्षस्. Requested भीष्म to give him the truth of मोक्ष धर्म। Did the funeral rites to him, and after returning to the capital, ruled righteously with the approval of धृतराष्ट्र and कृष्ण: three अश्व- मेधस् were performed by him at the suggestion of कृष्ण: Missed seeing धृतराष्ट्र and गान्धारी, and learnt of their life in the हिमालयस्. The rule was characterised by plenty of rains and crops and by absence of diseases and difficul- ties; {{F}}6:  Ib. I. 7. ४९; 8. ४७; Ch. 9. whole; १२. 4-6, ३४; १३. ३०-57; XI. १९. ११-12; III. 3. १८; M. ११२. 3.{{/F}} learnt the अन्गारव्रत from the sage, पिप्पलाद; {{F}}7:  Ib. ७२. 1.{{/F}} went to स्यमन्तपञ्चक for the solar eclipse and there met कृष्ण and other friends; was taken leave of by the sages: left it for his capital. {{F}}8:  भा. X. ८२. २७; ८३. 1-4; ८४. २७, ६९[3].{{/F}} Felt the advent of Kali everywhere: Installed his grandson परीक्षित् on the throne and Vajra at मथुरा: Prepared to go to स्वर्ग: Clad in bark, fasting, and silent, he went towards north with a view to attaining heaven: was followed by his brothers: Attained Hari through friendship. {{F}}9:  Ib. I. १५. ३२-48; VII. 1. ३०; Vi. IV. २०. ४०; २४. ११०-1; V. १२. २४; ३५. २८.{{/F}}

युयुत्सु|yuyutsu
--survived the कुरुक्षेत्र war: grieved at कृष्ण's departure from हास्तिनपुर: received Vidura in joy. भा. I. १०. 9; १३. 3; X. ८०.[4].

युयुध|yuyudha
--a son of Vasvananta, and father of सुभा- षण. भा. IX. १३. २५. [page३-034+ ३४]

युयुधान|yuyudhaana
--(see सात्यकि) the grandson of शिनि, and son of Satyaka, and father of Jaya. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २४. १४; Br. II. ७१. १०१; M. ४५. २३; वा. ९६. १००; Vi. IV. १४. 2.{{/F}} Learnt the धनुर्वेद from Arjuna. Approved of द्रौपदी's suggestion to release अश्वत्थमन्: accompanied कृष्ण to हास्तिनपुर; {{F}}2:  भा. I. 7. ५०; III. 1. ३१; X. ५८. 1; ६३. 3.{{/F}} took active part in the राजसूय of युधिष्ठिर: was sent to द्वारका for defence; {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ७५. 6; ७६. 7[5].{{/F}} went with the sacrificial horse of कृष्ण. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ८९. २२[2].{{/F}}

युवत्यस्|yuvatyas
--one of the १४ gan2as of apsaras born of the sun's rays. Br. III. 7. १९.

युवन|yuvana
--a god of the Lekha group. Br. II. ३६. ७६.

युवनाश्व|yuvanaashva
 (I)--a son of Candra, (Indu) and father of श्राव. भा. IX. 6. २०-21; M. १२. २९.

युवनाश्व|yuvanaashva
 (II)--a righteous king and a son of (Pra) सेनाजित्: Issueless though he had a hundred wives of whom गौरी was one; went to the forest, where he got up the Aindra इष्टि, a sacrifice in honour of Indra. One night he felt thirsty and drank the consecrated water from the sacri- ficial pot. In due time a son was born splitting open the right side of his stomach. He lived for some time and went to Heaven. This son was the great मान्धात (s.v.). भा. IX. 6. २५-32; 7. 1; Br. III. ६३. ६६; वा. ८८. ६५; Vi. IV. 2. ४८-63.

युवनाश्व|yuvanaashva
 (III)--An Angirasa and मन्त्रकृत्. By his curse half the Ganges came out. Br. II. ३२. १०८; III. ६६. २९; वा. ५९. ९९. [page३-035+ २८]

युवनाश्व|yuvanaashva
 (IV)--a son of Andhra. Br. III. ६३. २७; वा. ८८. २६.

युवनाश्व|yuvanaashva
 (V)--the son of अम्बरीष, wife नर्मदा, and son सम्भूत (Harita-वा। प्। and वि। प्।). Br. III. ६३. ७३; वा. ८८. ७३; Vi. IV. 3. 2-3.

युवनाश्व|yuvanaashva
 (VI)--during his यज्ञ, there were differen- ces as to the division of पशु। ब्रह्मा interfered and appeased while शक्ति got angry. Br. IV. 6. ५९.

युवनाश्व|yuvanaashva
 (VII)--a son of रणाश्व and father of मन्धात; a मन्त्रकृत्. M. १२. ३४; १४५. १०२.

युवनाश्व|yuvanaashva
 (VIII)--a son of शूलि of the २४थ् dva1para. वा. २३. २०७.

युवराज|yuvaraaja
--the Crown Prince; {{F}}1:  वा. ९६. २१९.{{/F}} his initiation against a King, an instance of अन्तह्कोप; {{F}}2:  M. २२३. 8.{{/F}} the residence of, to consist of five wings as that of the Kings. {{F}}3:  Ib. २५४. १७.{{/F}}

युषिताश्व|yuShitaashva
--the son of शन्खण and father of विश्व- saha. Vi. IV. 4. १०६.

यूका|yuukaa
--a measurement; eight times the लिख्या (स्।व्।), (लिक्षा). Br. IV. 2. १२१; M. २५८. १८; वा. १०१. १२१.

यूथपास्|yuuthapaas
--धूम्र Para1s4aras. M. २०१. ३८. [page३-036+ ५१]

यूप|yuupa
--a sacrificial post; {{F}}1:  वा. ३०. १४८; ९४. १७; ९७. २८; १०६. ४३.{{/F}} circumambulation of the, leads to the fruit of वाजपेय; {{F}}2:  Ib. १११. ३१-2.{{/F}} in the Gaura hill on the banks of the Ganges where Indra made many sacrifices; {{F}}3:  Br. II. १८. २८.{{/F}} near ब्रह्मतीर्थ where ब्रह्मा performed sacrifice and planted a यूप. {{F}}4:  वा. १११. ३१.{{/F}}

योग|yoga
 (I)--practices of: {{F}}1:  भा. I. 2. २८; II. 1. 6; 2. २३; M. 1. १२.{{/F}} eight-fold: its characteristics. {{F}}2:  भा. III. Ch. २८.{{/F}} Bhaktiyoga: {{F}}3:  Ib. III. Ch. २९.{{/F}} born of Kriya, क्रियायोग: {{F}}4:  Ib. IV. 1. ५१; वा. ७१. ६४.{{/F}} the course of: fol- lowed by नारद and others in their worship of नारायण: {{F}}5:  भा. V. १४. ४५; १९. १०; VII. 3. 9; ११. 3.{{/F}} System of. {{F}}6:  Ib. IX. १२. 4; X. 8. ४५; Ch. २९ (whole) ; XI. १४. २०.{{/F}} Also three-fold ज्ञान, भक्ति and कर्म: of this भक्ति is important. {{F}}7:  Ib. XI. २०. 6-8.{{/F}} Spoiled by bad association, especially association of women; {{F}}8:  Ib. XI. २६. 3 and २४.{{/F}} is an ऐश्वर्य, and possible through kriya and gurupriya: of २४ truths: त्रयी is its limb; {{F}}9:  Br. II. ३४. ६५; III. 3. ८९; 9. ६२ and ६६; १०. 4 and ११५; १९. २९ and ६२; IV. 3. ५५.{{/F}} other limbs, यम, नियम, {{F}}१०:  M. १३. 5; १८३. ४४ and ५०; १९३. ३८; २४७. 9; २४८. १७.{{/F}} यज्ञ, दान, वेदाभ्यास, and धारण; philosophy of; {{F}}११:  Ib. 2. १६; वा. ६६. ११०.{{/F}} the strength of the पितृस्, out of which soma grows; from ज्ञान; {{F}}१२:  Ib. ७१. ६६; १०१. ७५, २११, ३५०.{{/F}} methods of: control of the senses and the mind by fasting; a means to fructify austeri- ties, then knowledge sprouts; {{F}}१३:  Ib. ७७, १२४-35.{{/F}} praise of; {{F}}१४:  Br. I. 6. ४०; वा. १८. 5-6.{{/F}} of नक्षत्र and ऋषि; {{F}}१५:  Ib. ९९. ४२२.{{/F}} as a result of स्वाध्याय or study and vice-versa; {{F}}१६:  Vi. VI. 6. 2.{{/F}} explanation of the nature of yoga by केशिध्वज to खाण्डिक्य. {{F}}१७:  Ib. VI. 7. २६-92.{{/F}}

योग|yoga
 (II)--a name of शिव. वा. ९७. १७५.

योगतन्त्र|yogatantra
--authorship attributed to विष्वक्सेन. भा. IX. २१. २६. [page३-037+ ३४]

योगधर्म|yogadharma
--the first of all धर्मस्; {{F}}1:  वा. ८३. ६०.{{/F}} hidden by कश्यप in a cave and discovered and published by Sanat- कुमार for the benefit of humanity; {{F}}2:  Ib. ८३. ८३-4.{{/F}} not to be discussed with Yogins; but implicit obedience to it leads to heaven, and non- conformity would lead to hell. {{F}}3:  Ib. ८३. ९१-94; १०४. १४.{{/F}}

योगनिद्रा|yoganidraa
--of विष्णु on the waters: His primordial form; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 3. 2-5.{{/F}} his sleep at प्रयागा; {{F}}2:  M. २२. 9.{{/F}} left it for churning the ocean. {{F}}3:  Ib. १५०. २१२; २४९. ४५.{{/F}}

योगप्रवृत्ति|yogapravRtti
--the signs in the body of; when the Yogi feels himself and the earth full of tejas, then siddhi is attain- ed; {{F}}1:  वा. ११. ६२-63.{{/F}} क्रियायोग. {{F}}2:  Ib. ७१. ६४.{{/F}}

योगमाया|yogamaayaa
--Ordered by Hari to transfer the धाम of His in the womb of देवकी to that of रोहिणी; she was to take birth as the daughter of यशोदा and Nanda, at the same time he became कृष्ण. She would be worshipped by all as दुर्गा, भद्रकाली, अम्बिका. She did as was commanded. Born of यशोदा: taken to prison by Vasudeva leaving देवकी's babe at यशोदा's bed. Dashed against a rock by Kamsa, she predicted that soon a baby born already would kill him (See विष्णुमाया). भा. X. 2. 6-१५; 3. ४५[1]-५३; 4. 7-१३, २९.

योगशास्त्रस्|yogashaastras
--works on Yoga. Br. IV. ३७. २७.

योगसिद्धा|yogasiddhaa
--the sister of बृहस्पति and wife of Pra- भास, the eighth of the Vasus; son, विश्वकर्म, author of the सील्पशास्त्र. वा. ८४. १५-16. [page३-038+ ३६]

योगसूनु|yogasuunu
--a son of Brahmadatta. वा. ९९. १८०.

योगा|yogaa
--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ३२. १७.

योगाग्नि|yogaagni
--by his quality of lordship, God assumes this shape in the world. वा. १०१. २१७.

योगाचार्य|yogaachaarya
--Lord नारायण. M. १७१. 3.

योगात्म|yogaatma
--the अवतार् of the Lord in the २८थ् dva1para with a bachelor's body; entered the Meru cave with ब्रह्मा and विष्णु and took the name of Nakuli. वा. २३. २१९-21.

योगि|yogi
--(Siddha) he who has practised brahmacarya, ahimsa, satya, non-stealing, and a parigraha and cultivated a sense of detachment; {{F}}1:  वा. ७६. २८; Vi. VI. 7. ३६.{{/F}} is superior to all for he performs तपस् for a hundred years standing on one foot and living on air; {{F}}2:  वा. ७१. ७३.{{/F}} धर्मशासनम् of: ahimsaka; walking on good roads, drinking clean and filtered water and speaking truthful words; after serving his guru for a year goes about begging alms; {{F}}3:  Ib. १६. 8-१७.{{/F}} gets the धारण and tries to avoid the उपसर्गस्; must understand the seven सूक्ष्मस्; महिसूक्ष्म, आप, तेजस्, वायु, व्योम, मनस् and बुद्धि सूक्ष्म, and the condition of these before these elements attain the स्थूलभाव; all of them inter-dependent; {{F}}4:  Ib. १२. 9, १७.{{/F}} always intent on प्राणायाम be- comes one with the great being; {{F}}5:  Ib. १०. ९४.{{/F}} the best to be fed on the occasion of the श्राद्ध; superior to the feeding of a thousand householders, a hundred वानप्रस्थस् and a thousand ब्रह्मचारिन्स्. {{F}}6:  M. १३. 5; १६. १०; वा. ७१. ६७; Vi. III. १५. 2 and २४.{{/F}} [page३-039+ २५]

योगिनी|yoginii
 (I)--a वर्ण s4akti: an attendant on शिव. Br. IV. ४४. ५९ and १०५; III. ४१. ३०.

योगिनी|yoginii
 (II)--the goddess who stands in Kanakhala- तीर्थ and dances with शिव. M. १९३. ७०.

योगेश्वर|yogeshvara
--a manifestation of Hari in the epoch of XIII Manu: a friend of Indra Divaspati. भा. VIII. १३. ३२.

योगेश्वरी|yogeshvarii
--image of, with hanging tongue, knotted hair on the top of the head and a garland of skulls and bones, etc. M. २६१. ३३-6.

योगोत्पत्ति|yogotpatti
--the mind-born daughter of काव्य Pitr2s. Br. III. १०. ८६.

योजन|yojana
--८००० धनुस् make one योजन। Br. II. 7. १०१; IV. 2. १२६; वा. 8. १०७; ५१. ३७; १०१. ११३ and १२६.

योधनिपुरम्|yodhanipuram
--a place sacred to वासुदेव; bath in the तीर्थ here rids one of his Brahmahatti दोष. M. १९१. १००.

योधयानस्|yodhayaanas
--कश्यप gotraka1ras. M. १९९. 5.

योनि|yoni
 (I)--same as धूतपापा: a river in कुशद्वीप. M. १२२. ७१.

योनि|yoni
