योनि|yoni
 (III)--from प्रकृति. वा. १०१. २२८.

योनितोया|yonitoyaa
--a sacred river of शल्मलिद्वीप. Vi. II. 4. २८.

योनिमुद्रा|yonimudraa
--the symbol pertaining to देवी; description of. Br. IV. ४२. १८; ४४. ११.

योषित्सन्ग|yoShitsanga
--contact with women, condemned. भा. III. ३१. ३४-42.

यौधेय|yaudheya
--a son of युधिष्ठिर by देवकी. M. ५०. ५६.

यौधेया|yaudheyaa
--the capital of नृग (मृग-वा। प्।). Br. III. ७४. २१; वा. ९९. २१.

यौधेयी|yaudheyii
--a queen of युधिष्ठिर and mother of Devaka. Vi. IV. २०. ४४.

यौवनाश्व|yauvanaashva
 (I)--a son of अम्बरीष, and father of हारित; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 7. 1.{{/F}} killed in a battle lasting for १४ months and more Aruddha and Ripu. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ७४. 8; वा. ९९. 8.{{/F}}

यौवनाश्व|yauvanaashva
 (II)--a grandson of कावेरी. वा. ९१. ५८. [page३-041+ २२]

रक्त|rakta
--the thirtieth Kalpa; ब्रह्मा got a son red in colour, dress and eyes; finding him to be महादेव, ब्रह्मा bowed to him and contemplated upon वामदेव; शर्व appeared to him and made अट्टहास when were born four sons beginning with Viraja. वा. २२. २१-30.

रक्तकम्पना|raktakampanaa
--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. २६.

रक्तकर्णा(ई)|raktakarNaa(ii)
--a ब्रह्मराक्षसी. वा. ६९. १३४. Br. III. 7. ९९.

रक्तबीज|raktabiija
--an Asura killed by दुर्गा. Br. IV. २९. ७६.

रक्तयोगिनीवल्लभ|raktayoginiivallabha
--one of the six charioteers of ललिता. Br. IV. २०. ९२.

रक्ता|raktaa
--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. १२.

रक्ताक्ष|raktaaxa
--an attendant on शिव. Br. III. ४१. २६.

रक्ष|raxa
 (I)--a son of वसिष्ठ and ऊर्जा. Br. II. ११. ४१. [page३-042+ २७]

रक्ष|raxa
 (II)--the son of खश: A fearful figure of three heads, three hands and three feet: roamed in the night in search of prey of men and animals. Br. III. 7. ६१-77.

रक्ष|raxa
 (III)--meaning पालन or protection from राक्षसस्. वा. ६९. १०१.

रक्ष|raxa
 (IV)--resides in the sun's chariot during the month of शुची; {{F}}1:  Vi. II. १०. 7.{{/F}} फाल्गुन. {{F}}2:  Ib. II. १०. १८.{{/F}}

रक्षस्|raxas
--(also राक्षसस्) evil spirits. भा. X. 6. २७.

रक्षसस्|raxasas
--born of विश्वा and कश्यप; {{F}}1:  M. 5. 1; 6. २९, ४६.{{/F}} worship बर्हिषद् manes. {{F}}2:  Ib. १५. 4.{{/F}}

रक्षा|raxaa
 (I)--the sister of ऋक्ष; wife of प्रजापति and mother of जाम्बवन्. Br. III. 7. २९९-300.

रक्षा|raxaa
 (II)--the use of amulets to protect children and others from evils. Vi. V. 5. १३.

रक्षात्मिका|raxaatmikaa
--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ४४. ८६.

रक्षावधारिनी|raxaavadhaarinii
--a वर्णशक्ति. Br. IV. ४४. ६१. [page३-043+ २८]

रक्षोगणभोजन|raxogaNabhojana
--one of २८ hells for the sin of पुरुषमेध. भा. V. २६. 7 and ३१.

रक्षोघ्नमन्त्रपठनम्|raxoghnamantrapaThanam
--cited on the श्राद्ध day to keep off the राक्षसस्. Vi. III. १५. ३१.

रक्षोघ्नम् सूक्तम्|raxoghnam suuktam
--to be uttered in founding a new temple; {{F}}1:  M. २६५. २५.{{/F}} to be uttered in palace building; {{F}}2:  Ib. २६८. ३४.{{/F}} of the सामवेदिन्स्, recited in tank ritual. {{F}}3:  Ib. ५८. ३७.{{/F}}

रक्षोहा|raxohaa
--a son of अर्काग्नि. Br. II. १२. ४३; वा. २९. ४०.

रघु|raghu
 (I)--a son of दीर्घबाहु, and a man of ever- lasting glory. His son was Aja. Lust after more territory: knew the power of विष्णु's योगमाया. भा. IX. १०. 1; XII. 3. 9; II. 7. ४४; Br. III. ६३. १८३; वा. ८८. १८३; Vi. IV. 4. ८४-5.

रघु|raghu
 (II)--a son of Nighna. M. १२. ४७.

रघुनन्दन|raghunandana
--an epithet of विष्णु. M. ५४. १८.

रन्गम्|rangam
--the wrestling place where separate seats were arranged for judges, nobles, women, cowherds, etc. Women of the palace and the city attended such matches; these women recalled कृष्ण's former exploits. Vi. V. २०. २३-29, ४३, ४५-7. [page३-044+ २३]

रन्गोपजीवक|rangopajiivaka
--professional actors. वा. १०१. १६४.

रचना|rachanaa
--a Daitya lady and queen of त्वष्ट. भा. VI. 6. ४४.

रज|raja
 (I)--son of Viraja and father of Ketuman (शत- jit, वि। प्।). Br. II. १४. ७०; III. 8. १९; Vi. II. 1. ४०.

रज|raja
 (II)--son of Dhara. Br. III. 3. २२.

रज|raja
 (III)--is राजसीवृत्ति: Leads to duhkha and तृष. Br. IV. 3. ३२-41.

रज|raja
 (IV)--one of the seven sons of वसिष्ठ and ऊर्जा; wife मार्कण्डेयी and son Ketuman. वा. २८. ३६-37; Vi. I. १०. १३.

रज|raja
 (V)--the quality present both in तमस् and सत्व as oil in the oil-seed and ghee in milk; it is the result of agitation in the प्रधान। वा. 3. 2; 5. १०, १२.

रज|raja
 (VI)--son of Arija; a राजऋषि and tapassiddha. वा. ३३. ६०; ५७. १२२.

रज|raja
 (VII)--one of the ten branches of the Rohita clan of devas. वा. १००. ९०. [page३-045+ ३०]

रजक|rajaka
--a washerman; {{F}}1:  M. १९२. २०.{{/F}} शुक्लतीर्थम्, compared to, in washing sins; to be fined a माष of gold by the king for not properly washing. {{F}}2:  Ib. २२७. १५५.{{/F}} the washerman of Kamsa was killed on his refusing cloths to कृष्ण and राम. {{F}}3:  Vi. V. १९. १४-17.{{/F}}

रजत|rajata
--son of Varatri. Br. III. 1. ७९.

रजतनाभ|rajatanaabha
 (I)--the milkman of the यक्षस् on the earth and father of मणिधर. Born of यक्ष and apsaras क्रतुस्थला. Br. II. ३६. २१६; III. 7. १११.

रजतनाभ|rajatanaabha
 (II)--the grandfather of the यक्षस्, mar- ried भद्रा, the daughter of अनुह्राद, the Daitya; father of मणिभद्र and मणिवर; wives of these two become the aunts of सम्सिद्धकरण. वा. ६९. १५१-2.

रजतम्|rajatam
--silver, came out of शिव's eyes; hence dear to पितृस्; but inauspicious and to be avoided in देवकार्यस्. M. १७. २२-3.

रजनी|rajanii
--a R. in शाल्मलिद्वीप. भा. V. २०. १०.

रजि|raji
--son of आयु and father of five hundred (hundred म्।प्।) sons known as Rajeyas; a devotee of नारायण; was invested with conquering powers; fearing प्रह्लाद and other enemies, Indra gave his kingdom to Raji; once when the देवासुर (कोलाहल) war broke out between प्रह्लाद and Indra extending for ३०० years both parties invoked his assistance; he joined the Devas who unlike the Asuras [page३-046+ २९] accepted him as their Lord and he vanquished the Asuras; Indra became thus his adopted son to whom he gave back his kingdom and returned to forest for penance. Indra, however, returned the kingdom to Raji; after Raji's death his sons appropriated the kingdom and refused to give it to Indra; the latter therefore killed all of them with the help of बृहस्पति. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. १७. 1-१६; Br. III. ६७. 2, ७९-105; ७२. ८६; M. २४. ३५-42; वा. ९७. ८६; Vi. IV. 8. 3, २१; 9. 1-२३.{{/F}} It is said where Raji is, there लक्ष्मी finds her abode; where लक्ष्मी is there धृति lives; where धृति resides, धाम lives; where धाम lives, there is Jaya. {{F}}2:  वा. ९२. ७४-99.{{/F}}

रजेयु|rajeyu
--one of the ten sons of रौद्राश्व. वा. ९९. १२४.

रञ्जन|ranjana
--son of वरूत्रि. वा. ६५. ७८.

रणक|raNaka
--son of क्षुद्रक, and father of Suratha. भा. IX. १२. १५.

रणचन्द्र|raNachandra
--born of Pulaha. Br. III. 7. १७८.

रणञ्(म्)जय|raNaNJ(m)jaya
 (I)--a son of कृतञ्(m)jaya, and father of सम्जाय; of the बृहद्बल (बार्हद्बलायन-भा। प्।) dynasty. भा. IX. १२. १३; Vi. IV. २२. 7-8.

रणञ्जय|raNanjaya
 (II)--a son of व्रात. वा. ९९. २८७.

रणधृष्ट|raNadhRShTa
--a son of धृष्ट. M. १२. २१. [page३-047+ ३०]

रणाश्व|raNaashva
--a son of सम्हताश्व. M. १२. ३४.

रणेजय|raNejaya
--a son of कृतम्जय, the इक्ष्वाकु king. M. २७१. ११.

रति|rati
 (I)--a name of शतरूपा; wife of स्वायम्भुव Manu. Br. II. 9. ३८; वा. १०. १३.

रति|rati
 (II)--the consort of काम. Hearing that he was burnt by शिव, she clad herself in sorrowful clothes. श्या- मला restored him back to life, and in her presence both were married again; {{F}}1:  Br. IV. ३०. ३७-51; M. 7. १३; १००. ३२; १५४. २१९, २७२-3;{{/F}} a शक्ति; {{F}}2:  Br. IV. १९. ६४-71; ४४; ७२.{{/F}} mother of हर्ष; {{F}}3:  वा. १०. ३८.{{/F}} प्रीति became her co-wife; after the burning of काम, was माया- वती in शम्बर's house and brought up Pradyumna (an incarnation of काम); {{F}}4:  Vi. I. 7. ३१; V. २७. ३०.{{/F}} Image of, with swan. {{F}}5:  M. २६१. ५५.{{/F}}

रति|rati
 (III)--a कला of the moon. Br. IV. ३५. ९२.

रति|rati
 (IV)--a son of शतरूपा. M. 4. २५.

रतिप्रिया|ratipriyaa
--the goddess enshrined at गन्गाद्वार. M. १३. ३७.

रती|ratii
 (I)--the wife of Vibhu and mother of पृथुसेन. भा. V. १५. 6.

रती|ratii
 (II)--see मायावती. भा. X. ५५. 7. [page३-048+ २९]

रत्नकूटा|ratnakuuTaa
 (I)--one of Atri's wives. Br. III. 8. ७६.

रत्नकूटा|ratnakuuTaa
 (II)--a daughter of भद्राश्व and घृताची. वा. ७०. ६९.

रत्नकूटि|ratnakuuTi
--the tenth daughter of रौद्राश्व. वा. ९९. १२६.

रत्नधर|ratnadhara
--a Mt. south of मानस; {{F}}1:  वा. ३६. २३.{{/F}} residence of the seven sages. {{F}}2:  Ib. ३८. २७; ३९. ४५.{{/F}}

रत्नधेनु|ratnadhenu
--the gift of a cow with precious gems set in every part of its body takes one to the world of विष्णु and makes him attain the place of शम्भु; {{F}}1:  M. २७४. १०; २८८. 1-१७.{{/F}} Gudadhenu, fit for gift on the विशोकद्वादशि day. {{F}}2:  Ib. ८२. 2.{{/F}}

रत्नमय शाला|ratnamaya shaalaa
--of ललिता described. Br. IV. ch. ३३ (whole).

रत्नशैल|ratnashaila
 (I)--(रत्नाचलम्): of thousand pearls is the best; then of ५०० and ३००; with २५० pearls विष्कम्भपर्- vatas to be made around the principal one; the giver is relieved from Brahmahatti and other sins. M. ८३. 6; ९०. 1.

रत्नशैल|ratnashaila
 (II)--a chief hill of क्रौञ्चद्वीप like वडवामुख. Vi. II. 4. ५०.

रत्ना|ratnaa
--a daughter of शैब्य, queen of अक्रूर and mother of eleven heroic sons. M. ४५. २८. [page३-049+ २७]

रत्नाकर|ratnaakara
--ocean personified. Br. IV. १५. २१.

रत्नानि|ratnaani
 (I)--of kings; are seven in number; cakra, ratha, मणि, queen, nidhi, horses and elephants. Br. II. २९. ७४-5; M. २१७. ३७; वा. ५७. ६८.

रत्नानि|ratnaani
 (II)--the essence got by mountains by milk- ing the cow-earth; {{F}}1:  M. १०. २५.{{/F}} seven gems in the epoch of स्वायम्- bhuva; generally gems. {{F}}2:  Vi. III. १२. 2.{{/F}}

रत्नि|ratni
--a measurement of २१ angula parvas. Br. II. 7. ९८; IV. 2. १२२. M. १६. २५; ५८. 7. वा. १०१. १२२.

रथ|ratha
--of the moon, description of; sprang out of waters with ten horses, charioteer, etc., has three wheels. वा. ५२. ५०-4.

रथकृच्छ्र|rathakRchChra
--a ग्रामणि with the sun in spring. वा. ५२. 4.

रथकृत्|rathakRt
 (I)--the यक्ष presiding over the month of Madhu. भा. XII. ११. ३३; Br. II. २३. 3.

रथकृत्|rathakRt
 (II)--one of the seven प्रानिन्स् of the king. वा. ५७. ७०, Br. II. २९. ७६.

रथचित्र|rathachitra
 (I)--with the sun in the months of शुचि and शुक्र (in the month of आषाढ वि। प्।). Br. II. २३. 7; Vi. II. १०. 8.

रथचित्र|rathachitra
 (II)--a ग्रामणि with the sun in summer. वा. ५२. 7. [page३-050+ २९]

रथञ्ज|rathanja
--a यक्ष, who resides in the sun's chariot during the month of माधव. Vi. II. १०. 5.

रथन्तर|rathantara
--a जयादेव and son of ब्रह्मा; a man- त्रशरीर. Br. III. 3. 6; वा. ६६. 6; ६७. 5.

रथन्तरकल्प|rathantarakalpa
--an account of, in the ब्रह्मवै- वर्त पुराण; {{F}}1:  M. ५३. ३४; ६९. 1, 5.{{/F}} king पुष्पवाहन belonged to this aeon. {{F}}2:  Ib. १००. 1.{{/F}}

रथन्तरम्|rathantaram
 (I)--the साम sung by Bhauvana; ele- phants, Kapila and पुण्डरीक born of; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 7. ३२४ and ३३५; वा. 9. ४८; २२. 8; ३०. ११९; ६९. २०९.{{/F}} to be heard on the श्राद्ध day; {{F}}2:  M १७. ३८.{{/F}} to be uttered while installing a new image; {{F}}3:  Ib. ५८. ३७; २६५. २७.{{/F}} from the first face of ब्रह्मा. {{F}}4:  Br. II. 8. ५०; III. 4. 2. Vi. I. 5. ५३.{{/F}}

रथन्तरम्|rathantaram
 (II)--(सूर्यमण्डलम्) ८८,000 yojanas in measurement. वा. २१. ७५ and ७९.

रथभृत्|rathabhRt
--a यक्ष who resides in the sun's chariot in the months of Caitra and Madhu. Vi. II. १०. 3.

रथराजी|ratharaajii
--a wife of Vasudeva. M. ४६. २१.

रथरेणु|rathareNu
--a measurement; 8 त्रसरेणु. Br. IV. 2. १२०; वा. १०१. १२०. [page३-051+ २६]

रथवर|rathavara
--a son of भीमरथ, and father of Nava- ratha; {{F}}1:  Br. III. ७०. ४२.{{/F}} adhered to dharma and satya. {{F}}2:  वा. ९५. ४१-2.{{/F}}

रथसप्तमि|rathasaptami
--the Saptami of the month of माघ when the sun turns his chariot; fit for making gifts and per- forming श्राद्ध to please पितृस्. M. १७. 9-१०.

रथस्वन|rathasvana
 (I)--the यक्ष presiding over the month of शुक्र (in the sun's chariot during the month of शुचि- वि। प्।). भा. XII. ११. ३५; Br. II. २३. 7; Vi. II. १०. 7.

रथस्वन|rathasvana
 (II)--a ग्रामणि with the sun in the summer. वा. ५२. 7.

रथाकार|rathaakaara
--a kingdom of कुशद्वीप. Br. II. १४. २९; १९. ५८.

रथान्तर|rathaantara
 (I)--a क्षत्रोपेत dvija. Br. III. ६६. ८८.

रथान्तर|rathaantara
 (II)--a disciple of सत्यश्रिय; a शाख प्र- वर्तक, शाखपूर्णरथीतर (?). वा. ६०. २९, ६५.

रथान्तर|rathaantara
 (III)--an elephant. वा. ६९. २१९.

रथिमुख्य|rathimukhya
--a son of भजमान. Va. ९६. १३५. [page३-052+ २९]

रथी|rathii
--a military title below महारथ {{F}}1:  वा. ९९. २४९.{{/F}} earned by ययाति and कार्तवीर्यार्जुन. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ६८. २०; ६९. २१.{{/F}}

रथीतर|rathiitara
 (I)--a son of पृषदश्व; had no issue and at his desire, Angiras blessed him with sons. Their descend- ants became Angirasas and क्षत्रोपेत dvijas. भा. IX. 6. 1-3; Br. III. ६३. 6-7; वा. ८८ 6-7. Vi. IV. 2. 9-१०.

रथीतर|rathiitara
 (II)--a pupil of सत्यशृण्ग--also शाखवैण; author of three सम्हितस् given to four pupils Paila and others; also author of Nirukta--a त्रयार्षेय, with Angiras and विरूप; {{F}}1:   Br. II. ३४. ३२. ३५. 3; M. १९६. ३८; वा. ६१. 2.{{/F}} had four disciples, Ketava, Dalaki, Dhama- शर्म and देवशर्म; all of them became murderers of Brahmanas on the death of their master; they approached the creator for light who advised them to make a visit to वालुकेस्वरम् to get redeemed of their sins by bath and prayer; on the completion of the pilgrimage they reached सूर्यमण्डलम्. {{F}}2:  Ib. ६०. ६५-72.{{/F}}

रथीतर|rathiitara
 (III)--a वानर chief. Br. III. 7. २३४.

रथीतर|rathiitara
 (IV)--a राजऋषि who became a Brahmana and attained siddhi. वा. ९१. ११७.

रथीतरस्|rathiitaras
--a branch of the Angirasas. वा. ६५. १०६.

रथोर्मि|rathormi
--a Pratardana god. Br. II. ३६. ३१. [page३-053+ २५]

रथौजस्|rathaujas
--a यक्ष with the sun in the months of Madhu and माधव. Br. II. २३. 3.

रन्ति|ranti
 (I)--a son of Nandana. Br. III. ७१. १९२.

रन्ति|ranti
 (II)--a son of Riveyu, his wife was सरस्वती. वा. ९९. १२८, १२९.

रन्तिदेव|rantideva
 (I)--a son of सम्कृति: attained permanent fame. He performed a sacrifice when he gave up all he had and suffered with his family having nothing to eat for fortyeight days. When he had something to eat, there came a Brahmana guest and a वृषल, and another guest with dogs around him; they all shared it. When he had some- thing to drink, there came a Pulkasa and asked for the drink and got it. To such a high soul, the gods showed दर्शन्. All his followers became Yogins, himself having realised the योगमाया of विष्णु. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २१. 2-१८; X. ७२. २१; II. 7. ४४; Vi. IV. १९. २२.{{/F}} परीक्षित् compared to him for his generosity. {{F}}2:  भा. I. १२. २४; Br. III. ३४. ३८.{{/F}}

रन्तिदेव|rantideva
 (II)--a son of महायशस्. M. ४९. ३७.

रन्तिपाल|rantipaala
--a son of Nandana. Br. III. ७१. १९२. [page३-054+ २८]

रन्तिभास|rantibhaasa
--a son of ऋतेयु, and father of Sumati and two other sons. भा. IX. २०. 6.

रन्ध्रकरकस्|randhrakarakas
--a kingdom of the West watered by the Sindhu. Br. II. १८. ४८.

रभस|rabhasa
--a son of Rambha, and father of गम्भीर. भा. IX. १७. १०.

रभसा|rabhasaa
--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. २६.

रमण|ramaNa
--a son of Dhara. M. 5. २४.

रमणक|ramaNaka
 (I)--An उपद्वीप to जम्बूद्वीप: a terri- torial division of शाल्मलिद्वीप: {{F}}1:  भा. V. १९. ३०; २०. 9.{{/F}} The island where कालीय originally lived. Here the serpents agreed to give बलि every fortnight to गरुड, except कालीय. {{F}}2:  Ib. X. १६. ६३; १७. 1-4.{{/F}} South of श्वेत and north of नील. People live here for thousands of years (१०१५० years वा। प्।) by drinking the juice of the fruit of the banyan tree, रोहण in the island; people living there, pleasant to look at, devoid of disease and difficulties. {{F}}3:  Br. II. १५ 62-5; M. ११३. ६१; वा. ४५. 2-5.{{/F}}

रमणक|ramaNaka
 (II)--son of वीतिहोत्र of पुष्करद्वीप. भा. V. २०. ३१.

रमणा|ramaNaa
--the Goddess enshrined at रामतीर्थ. M. १३. ४०. [page३-055+ २८]

रमा|ramaa
--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ४४. ९०.

रमोद|ramoda
--आर्षेयप्रवरस् (भार्गवस्). M. १९५. ३९.

रम्बला|rambalaa
--a daughter of the वालेयस्; originator of the कम्बलेयगण. वा. ६९. २१.

रम्भ|rambha
 (I)--a son of विविम्शति, and father of Khani- netra. भा. IX. 2. २५.

रम्भ|rambha
 (II)--a son of आयु, and father of Rabhasa: known for his valour; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. १७. 1 and १०; Br. III. ६७. 2.{{/F}} had no son. {{F}}2:  Vi. IV. 8. 3; 9. २४.{{/F}}

रम्भ|rambha
 (III)--the fifth Kalpa. वा. २१. ३०.

रम्भक|rambhaka
--with the sun in the months of शुचि and शुक्र. Br. II. २३. 8.

रम्भा|rambhaa
 (I)--the Apsaras presiding over the month of शुचि; {{F}}1:  भा. XII. ११. ३६.{{/F}} wife of Maya; {{F}}2:  Br. III. 6. २८; 7. 7.{{/F}} presiding over the month of ऊर्ज. {{F}}3:  Ib. II. २३. २२; IV. ३३. १८; भा. XII. ११. ४४.{{/F}}

रम्भा|rambhaa
 (II)--the goddess enshrined at Malaya hills: a mother goddess. M. १३. २९; १७९. २०. [page३-056+ ३३]

रम्भा|rambhaa
 (III)--An Apsaras versed in dancing; {{F}}1:  M. २४. २८; वा. ६९. 6.{{/F}} created by ब्रह्मा; {{F}}2:  M. १३६. ११.{{/F}} going with the sun sometime; {{F}}3:  Ib. १२६. २३.{{/F}} seized by the Asuras; {{F}}4:  Ib. १२६. 7; १३३. 9.{{/F}} in the सभा of हिरण्यकशिपु. {{F}}5:  Ib. १६१. ७५.{{/F}}

रम्भा|rambhaa
 (IV)--a snake with the sun in summer. वा. ५२. 6.

रम्भा|rambhaa
 (V)--with the sun during फाल्गुन month; शुक्र or आषाढ; {{F}}1:  Vi. II. १०. १८.{{/F}} along with other Apsaras cursed by अष्तावक्र. {{F}}2:  Ib. V. ३८. ७३. ७७.{{/F}}

रम्य|ramya
 (I)--son of आग्नीध्र, and Lord of नीलम् (नीलवर्ष-वा। प्।); {{F}}1:  Br. II. १४. ४६-50; वा. ३३. ३९, ४२.{{/F}} placed in charge of the kingdom bordering on नीलाचल. {{F}}2:  Vi. II. 1. १७ and २०.{{/F}}

रम्य|ramya
 (II)--(केशरि s.v.) Mt. in शाकद्वीपम्. वा. ४९. ८४.

रम्यक|ramyaka
 (I)--son of आग्नीध्र. भा. V. 2. १९.

रम्यक|ramyaka
 (II)--(नीलवर्ष) a continent bounded by नील on one side: Here विष्णु in the form of Matsya is worshipped by Manu. भा. V. १६. 8; १८. २४-28. M. ११३. ३०; वा. ३४. ३०. Vi. II. 2. १४.

रम्या|ramyaa
--a daughter of Meru, and wife of Ramyaka. भा. V. 2. २३.

रय|raya
--son of पुरूरवस् and ऊर्वशी. Father of Eka. भा. IX. १५. 1-2. [page३-057+ ३४]

रव|rava
--disciple of लोकाक्षि, an अवतार् of the lord. वा. २३. १३४.

रवन|ravana
--son of Dharma (Vasu). Vi. I. १५. ११३.

रवयस्|ravayas
--their lord is विष्णु. M. 8. 4.

रवि|ravi
 (I)--from अव् to protect--see सूर्य; {{F}}1:  Br. II. २१. 4; २३. २६; २४. ३५; III. ५९. ३७; IV. 1. १३८; वा. ५०. ६०; Vi. II. 8. ११-12.{{/F}} got a place among श्राद्धदेवस्; {{F}}2:  M. १३. 1.{{/F}} the श्राद्धदेव; {{F}}3:  Ib. १५. ४३.{{/F}} an आदित्य; {{F}}4:  Ib. १७१. ५६.{{/F}} in three forms, गयादित्य, उत्तरार्क, and दक्षिणार्क; {{F}}5:  वा. १०६. ५७.{{/F}} movements of the sun, detailed; मण्डल measurement of; rise at Samy- amana, mid-day at अमरावती, mid-night at सुषा, setting at विभावरी; other similar calculations; the movement in a मुहूर्त; movement for a day and a night; movement in दक्षिणायनम्; chariot of, limbs of the year; the seven horses are च्छन्दस्, गायत्री, त्रिष्टुब्, जगती, अनुष्टुब्, पङ्क्ती, बृहती and उष्णिक्; gives a list of sages, Gandharvas, Apsaras, नागस्, ग्रामणि and राक्षसस् with the sun in the six seasons; these go with the sun in his own wheel; {{F}}6:  M. chh. १२४-6; वा. १००. २२२.{{/F}} a marut- गण; {{F}}7:  M. १७१. ५२.{{/F}} standard of नाग in the तारकामय. {{F}}8:  Ib. १७३. 9.{{/F}}

रवि|ravi
 (II)--son of स्वारोचिष Manu. Br. II. ३६. १९; वा. ६२. १९.

रविद्वारम्|ravidvaaram
--the path of devas. वा. 8. १९८.

रविनन्दन|ravinandana
--a name of Manu. M. 1. ११ and २२. [page३-058+ २५]

रविपदम्|ravipadam
--in गया. वा. १०९. १९.

रविमूर्तिस्|ravimuurtis
--four, representing the four Yugas. वा. १०८. ३६.

रशदु|rashadu
--a son of स्वाहा and father of Citraratha; the best among givers; performed many sacrifices. वा. ९५. १६-17.

रश्मि|rashmi
--one of the २० Sutapa गणस्. वा. १००. १५.

रस|rasa
 (I)--a तुषित god. Br. III. 3. १९.

रस|rasa
 (II)--the गुण of waters becomes absorbed in ज्योतिस् or तेजस् and consequently waters reach the verge of destruction. वा. १०१. ४२. १०२. 9.

रसकर्षनिका|rasakarShanikaa
--a देवी. Br. IV. १९. १८; ३६. ६९; ४४. ११८.

रसकल्याणिनी|rasakalyaaNinii
--a व्रत to be performed on the third day of the माघ month; sacred to ललिता; this is continued every month preceded by fasting and followed by gifts to Brahmanas; the person who does this enjoys in the world of गौरी. It is equal to performing १००० यज्ञस्। M. ch. ६३ (whole)

रसकुल्या|rasakulyaa
--a R. in कुशद्वीप. भा. V. २०. १५. [page३-059+ ३४]

रसज्ञ|rasaJNa
--a companion of Puramjana, allegorically the organ of taste. See मुख्या. भा. IV. २५. ४९; २९. ११.

रसधेनु|rasadhenu
--fit for gift during the विशोकद्वादशि व्रत। M. ८२. १९.

रसन|rasana
--a son of the राक्षस Vidyuta. Br. III. 7. ९५.

रसपासर|rasapaasara
--son of Kuthumi. वा. ६१. ३८.

रसराज|rasaraaja
--one of the eight सौभाग्यम्स्. M. ६०. 8, २८.

रससिद्धि|rasasiddhi
--is a yoga siddhi. Br. IV. ३६. ५२; ४४. १०८.

रसातल|rasaatala
--(also पातालम्) the underworld of rocky soil. Here live पणिस्, नागस्, निवातकवचस् and कालेयस्; all दानवस् of great strength and enterprising spirit and afraid of Hari and Sarama, the messenger of Indra. {{F}}1:  भा. V. २४. 7 and ३०; Br. II. १९. १७१; २०. १० and १२, ३९-40; ३०. ३१; M. ४७. ६३; वा. ४९. १६३; ९७. ९५; १००. १५७; Vi. IV. 3. 4 and 8; V. 1. २८.{{/F}} Visited by Arjuna in search of the dead child of the द्वारका Brahmana; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ८९. ४४.{{/F}} burnt by Pralaya; {{F}}3:  Br. III. ५३. 1; ७२. ९६. ७३. ४६ and ४८; IV. 1. १५३.{{/F}} the Asuras entered it help- less; {{F}}4:  M. ४७. २१२-13, २३३.{{/F}} Vasu, cursed by the sages to live there, for his decision against the killing of पशु in sacrifices; {{F}}5:  Ib. १४३. २४-25; १६६. 3; २४८, 4, ११, ५३, ६७ff; वा. ५७. ११०.{{/F}} of १०,000 Yojanas in extent; other talams are Atala, Sutala, Vitala, Gabhastala, महातल, Sritala, and पताल with the characteristics of black, white, पीतम्, chunam, rocky and gold they are in groups of earth, water and space. {{F}}6:  Ib. 6. २५; ५०. 9-१४.{{/F}} [page३-060+ २८]

रसौ|rasau
--the months of Madhu and माधव. Br. II. १३. 9; वा. ३०. 8.

रहम्वर्चस्|rahamvarchas
--a son of सम्पाति. M. ४९. 4.

रहस्ययोगिनी|rahasyayoginii
--a group of deities. Br. IV. १९. ४६.

रहूगण|rahuugaNa
--the king of Sindhu--सौवीर kingdom: employed जड-Bharata as his palanquin bearer, and found fault with him for not bearing it properly: He understood that he was a Brahmana, felt remorse and enquired who he was. Heard precepts on आत्मविद्या from Bharata and became devoted to Hari in a spirit of detachment. भा. V. १०. 1-२५; १३. २५.

राका|raakaa
 (I)--a daughter of Angiras and स्म्र्ती; wife of धात्रि, and mother of प्रातस्; {{F}}1:  भा. IV. 1. ३४; VI. १८. 3; वा. २८. १५; Vi. I. १०. 7.{{/F}} a शक्ति. {{F}}2:  Br. IV. ३२. १२.{{/F}}

राका|raakaa
 (II)--a R. in शाल्मलिद्वीप. भा. V. २०. १०.

राका (एका?)|raakaa (ekaa?)
 (III)--the full moon shining resplendent and much pleasing to the eye; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ११. १८; २८. ३८, ४६ and ६०; वा. ५०. २०१; ५६. ३५, ४१ and ५५.{{/F}} a day fit for giving gifts; {{F}}2:  Vi. II. 8. ८०.{{/F}} ety. of. {{F}}3:  वा. ५६. ४१.{{/F}}

राका|raakaa
 (IV)--Two lavas of the afternoon of Pratipada. M. १३३. ३६; १४१. ३३, ४१, ५१. [page३-061+ ३७]

राक्षस|raaxasa
--a form of marriage by which कृष्ण married रुक्मिणी. But Rukmi objected to this form of marriage. भा. X. ५२. १८ and ४१; ५४. १८; Vi. III. १०. २४.

राक्षसस्|raaxasas
 (I)--see रक्षस्: semi-divine beings; {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 8. २४; Br. II. ३२. 1 and 2; ३५. १९१.{{/F}} different clans--देवराक्षसस् like नैरृतस्, भूमिराक्षसस्, Guhya- राक्षसस् Daityara1ks2asas like कापिलेयस्; Another classifica- tion is दीवाचरस् (यज्ञमुखस्) (यातुधान, Brahma- धान, and वार्त्त) and निशाचरस् (Paulastya, नैरृत, आगस्त्य, and विश्वामीत्र) who ruin the श्राद्ध, but wor- ship पितृस्; {{F}}2:  Ib. III. 7. १३२- १६७; 8. ६०-65; १०. १११; ११. ८१; IV. 1. १५५; 2. २६; २०. ४७; वा. ७०. ५४-7.{{/F}} of sharp teeth, reside in Bhaumanarakam; {{F}}3:  M. ३९. 8-9.{{/F}} sons of यातुधान; {{F}}4:  वा. ६९. १२८.{{/F}} description of their forms and features; {{F}}5:  Ib. ७०. ५४-63.{{/F}} mother, स्वसा; {{F}}6:  Vi. I. २१. २५.{{/F}} both दानवस् and Daityas live in पाताल. {{F}}7:  Ib. II. 5-4.{{/F}}

राक्षसस्|raaxasas
 (II)--एत्य्: (see also यक्ष, निशाचर). When out of hunger the first created beings began to swallow water, the राक्षसस् tried to protect the waters; then the hairs of प्रजापति stood on end with anger; out of this came snakes of all sorts; {{F}}1:  Br. II. 8. ३२; वा. 9. ३०-5; Vi. I. 5. ४३.{{/F}} occupy Vajraka hill. {{F}}2:  वा. ३०. ९०; ३१. १२; ३४. ५५; ३९. ३६; १००. १५९; १०१. 3, २८.{{/F}}

राक्षसजित्|raaxasajit
--a son of जाम्बवन्. Br. III. 7. ३०३.

राक्षसमातृस्|raaxasamaatRs
--eight in number: perhaps the seven daughters of खश and नीला; create fear and disease among children (human beings- वा। प्।). Br. III. 7. १५६-61; वा. ६९. १८८.

राक्षसी|raaxasii
--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. १६. [page३-062+ ३३]

राक्षसीवेला|raaxasiivelaa
--when no ceremonies are to be performed; the first three मुहूर्तस् or नालिकस् of the morning, सङ्घव (8-३० to ११ A.M.) of noon, afternoon and evening. M. २२. ८२-83.

राक्षी|raaxii
--a chief doorkeeper in Geyacakraratha. Br. IV. १९. ८८.

राग|raaga
--carries away भूत; leads to सम्सार and its ills; विषयराग, reason for re-birth. वा. १०२. ६७, ६९.

राघव|raaghava
--see राम (s.v.); {{F}}1:  Br. III. 5. ३६.{{/F}} killed ताडका; {{F}}2:  वा. ६७. ७३.{{/F}} his consort was सीता; {{F}}3:  Vi. I. 9. १४४.{{/F}} an अवतार् of विष्णु to kill रावण. {{F}}4:  Ib. IV. १४. ४९.{{/F}}

राघवेश्वरम्|raaghaveshvaram
--a तीर्थ sacred to the पितृस्. M. २२. ६६.

राज|raaja
 (I)--one of the ten branches of the Rohita clan of devas. Br. IV. 1. ८६; वा. १००. ९०.

राज|raaja
 (II)--(see also राजन्) qualifications of: should not retreat from the battle-field; should protect Brahmanas, the poor and the helpless; insist on svadharma of his sub- jects, aid tapasvins, befriend the truthful and avoid the vakras; {{F}}1:  M. २१५. ५६-99; २३८. १२.{{/F}} precautions to be observed; befriend enemy's sub- jects and provide them with jobs; use spies in administra- tion; {{F}}2:  Ib. २२०. 8-४७.{{/F}} prescriptions for personal conduct and successful rule of a king; some व्रतम्स् like the आग्नेय, पार्थिव, etc. {{F}}3:  Ib. २२३. 7f.{{/F}} Avoid the two kinds of discontent,--अन्तह्कोप and बहिह्- कोप; the former brings more ruin it being towards the mem- [page३-063+ ३२] bers of the royal household; the latter towards सामन्तस्. {{F}}4:  Ib. २२६. 3-१२.{{/F}} Collect taxes through faithful servants annually. {{F}}5:  Ib. २१५. ५७.{{/F}} Earn the title of राजऋषि like ययाति; {{F}}6:  Ib. १३. ६२; ४३. २३; ४६. २८.{{/F}} ety. of. {{F}}7:  वा 62. १३४; १०९. ५४.{{/F}}

राजऋषि|raajaRShi
--a title of पुरूरवस्, ययाति and कार्तवीर्य; {{F}}1:  M. १३. ६२; ४३. २३; वा. ९६. १९०.{{/F}} attained by शमिक. {{F}}2:  M. ४६. २८.{{/F}} For some more names see वा। प्। {{F}}3:  वा. ३२, ३८, ५४; ६१. ८०, ८६-88; ९९. १५, १२७.{{/F}}

राजक|raajaka
--son of विशाखयूप, and father of Nandivar- dhana, the Magadha king. भा. XII. 1. 3-4.

राजकृत्यम्|raajakRtyam
--to punish evil doers and to protect the law abiding. M. २११. 9.

राजकेशि|raajakeshi
--a sage. M. १९६. २६.

राजगृअह|raajagRaha
--the capital of Malla whom कृष्ण van- quished; the palace of. Br. III. ७३. १००; IV. १४. ११.

राजगृहम्|raajagRham
--a sacred place in कीकट. वा. १०८. ७३.

राजत|raajata
--a दान; also रौप्याचलम्; the best gift is of १०,000 palams of silver; the giver goes to the world of the moon; then of 5,००० and then 2,५०० palams; anything above २० palams. M. ८३. 6; ९१. 1ff. [page३-064+ ३३]

राजतम्|raajatam
--the silver vessel used by पितृस् in milking the cow-earth; {{F}}1:  M. १०. १८.{{/F}} out of शिव's eye; {{F}}2:  Ib. १५. ३१; १७. २०. २३.{{/F}} best for use in श्राद्ध. {{F}}3:  वा. ७३. ५१; ७४. 1.{{/F}}

राजधर्म|raajadharma
--also क्षत्रधर्म; no sin to kill one in war. M. १०३. २२.

राजन्|raajan
--ety. दण्डधारिन्; crimes escaping his notice are dealt with by Yama. In Kali the king is mostly of the fourth caste and takes the profession of robbery rather than protection. Earth loses its fertility. The wealth and wives of others are coveted; म्लेच्छस् are patronised. Duties-- salutation to cows and Brahmanas, sandhya worship and gifts to the deserving; not to deprive forcibly a Brahmana of his property; {{F}}1:  Br. II. २९. ६३-64; ३१. ४१-156; ३६. १५६; III. २८. १०-74.{{/F}} renowned kings get the title of राजऋषि, gene- rally of the family of Manu, Aila, इक्ष्वाकु. {{F}}2:  Ib. II. ३५. ९०, ९६-102; III. ७१. १९४.{{/F}}

राजनीति|raajaniiti
--six-fold; learnt by राम and कृष्ण. भा. X. ४५. ३४.

राजपथ|raajapatha
--१० dhanus broad; permits of easy move- ment for men, horses, chariots and elephants. वा. 8. ११९.

राजपुत्र|raajaputra
 (I)--a name of Budha, the son of राजसोम and the originator of the science of elephantology. M. २४. 3.

राजपुत्र|raajaputra
 (II)--prince; special teachers are to be appointed to teach him Dharma, Artha and काम s4a1stras, to train him in elephant riding, chariot riding, and in arts and crafts; he must have his bodyguard so that he may not mix with the undesirables and may control his senses; he [page३-065+ ३५] must live in a private residence, for an ill-disciplined prince will root out the family. {{F}}1:  M. २२०. 1-6{{/F}} A possible internal enemy of the king. {{F}}2:  Ib. २२३. 9.{{/F}}

राजपुत्रीयम्|raajaputriiyam
--a work on elephantology by the sage राजपुत्र, identified with Budha. M. २४. 3.

राजभटस्|raajabhaTas
--police officials; {{F}}1:  वा. १०१. १५४.{{/F}} go to hell. {{F}}2:  Br. IV. 2. १५५.{{/F}}

राजमार्गस्|raajamaargas
 (also राजपथस्)--royal roads as fre- quented by पिशाचस्; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 7. ४०४; २७. ११.{{/F}} in the city of श्रीपुरम्; {{F}}2:  M. १३०. 3.{{/F}} in the city of मथुरा; {{F}}3:  Vi. V. १९. १२.{{/F}} lighted by lamps during nights; {{F}}4:  M. १३९. १९.{{/F}} persons commit- ting nuisance in public roads were visited by fines and required to clean them. {{F}}5:  Ib. २२७. १७५.{{/F}}

राजमाष|raajamaaSha
--unfit for श्राद्ध. Vi. III. १६. 7.

राजयक्ष्म|raajayaxma
--smitten by this, Soma was relieved by his father, Atri. Br. III. ६५. ४६-8.

राजयक्ष्मा|raajayaxmaa
--to be worshipped in house-building. M. २५३. ३०, ४२; २६८. २३.

राजरक्षारहस्यस्|raajaraxaarahasyas
--devices for the protection of the king's person; different kinds of mixtures of medicines used for १५ days, one month, etc.; remedies to avert houses being consumed by fire; against snakes by burning their coating; examination of cooked food by giving it to birds or throw- ing it into the fire and then examining the change in colour; [page३-066+ २७] flies would not sit on the poisoned food; its effect on birds and beasts; the same is applicable to drinking water; such protection needed since he is the root of the tree of the people. M. २१९. 1-३४.

राजराज्यम्|raajaraajyam
--the abode of Kubera. M. ८३. ४५.

राजराज|raajaraaja
--the giver of gift; kalpa tree becomes so in the next birth; {{F}}1:  M. १०१. ३०, ५४, ७१; २७७. २१.{{/F}} for the gift of gosahasra. {{F}}2:  Ib. २७८. २५.{{/F}}

राजराट्|raajaraaT
--the special title awarded by ब्रह्मा to Soma. Br. III. ६५. २०; वा. ९०. २०.

राजवर्तप|raajavartapa
--a कश्यप and a त्रयार्षेय. M. १९९. १२.

राजवर्धन|raajavardhana
--son of Dama, and father of Suvrddhi. Vi. IV. 1. ३६-7.

राजवान्|raajavaan
--son of Dyutimat. Vi. I. १०. 5.

राजवृत्ति|raajavRtti
--followed by robbers as the kings themselves begin to rob in the Kali age. वा. ५८. ४२.

राजवेश्म|raajaveshma
--sacred to ललितापीठ. Br. IV. ४४. ९६.

राजशासनम्|raajashaasanam
--for wrong entry in, punished with uttama दण्ड. M. २२७. २०२. [page३-067+ ३४]

राजस|raajasa
--otherwise known as केतुमान्, a लोकपाल; {{F}}1:  Br. II. २१. १५७; M. १२४. ९५.{{/F}} attained heaven by तपस्। {{F}}2:  Ib. १४३. ३८.{{/F}}

राजसिम्ह|raajasimha
--a king of Vidarbha. His daughter was married to Malayadhvaja पाण्ड्य. भा. IV. २८. २८-29.

राजसी|raajasii
--also प्रजाकरी; this quality possessed by मरीचि Kas4yapa. वा. ६६. ८७, १०४, १०५.

राजसीवृत्ति|raajasiivRtti
--intervening both satva and tama; leads to karma and rebirth and hence duhkha or misery due to ear, eye, tongue, body and smell. वा. १०२. ५४, ६२.

राजसूय|raajasuuya
 (I)--the conqueror of cardinal points was fit to perform this: युधिष्ठीर on this, to कृष्ण: Done by Soma who conquered the three worlds; {{F}}1:  भा. X. ७१. 2[1]; ७२-3; IX. १४. 4; वा. ९०. २२.{{/F}} युधिष्ठिर's desire to be a पारमेष्ठी. So ऋत्विक्स् were sent for, including भीष्म, Vidura. Even शूद्रस् were invited. After the sacrifice, on the suggestion of Sahadeva, the first honour was given to कृष्ण. शिशुपाल's protest and vilification of कृष्ण who had his head cut off. In the sacrifice each brother was assigned specific functions--Duryodhana in charge of treasury, भीम cooking, Nakula the supply of provisions, etc. The अवभृत bath at गन्गा accompanied by divine music. Every visitor duly honoured, returned back. Jealousy of Duryodhana at the success of the sacrifice. {{F}}2:  भा. VII. 1. १३;; X. ७०. ४१; Chh. ७४-75.{{/F}} The consecration ceremony of a king done by पृथु, वालि and others. {{F}}3:  Br. II. ३६. ११३; III. 7. २६८; 8. २५; ६३. ११६; ७२. २८; वा. ६२. ९५; ७०. २१.{{/F}} [page३-068+ ३४]

राजसूय|raajasuuya
 (II)--the head of the Veda. वा. ७१. ७७; ८८. ११८. Ib. १०४. ८४; ११२. ६३.

राजसूय|raajasuuya
 (III)--the fifth गान्धार gra1mika. वा. ८६. ४२.

राजसूयम्|raajasuuyam
--the gift of ब्रह्माण्ड पुराण equal to the performance of १००० sacrifices. {{F}}1:  M. ५३. ५७.{{/F}} The fruits of this यज्ञ are equal to fasting and praying to विष्णु on the अक्षयतृतीय day; {{F}}2:  Ib. ६५. 7.{{/F}} a plunge in the प्रयागा is equal to this यज्ञ। {{F}}3:  Ib. १०६. २१.{{/F}} Sacrifice performed by Soma when विष्णु was ब्रह्मा, शिव, the protector, Atri, the hota, भृगु, the अध्वर्यु, ब्रह्मा, the उद्गात, Sanaka and others were the Sadasyas, ten विश्वेदेवस् Camasa1dhvaryavas, and the three worlds दक्षिण; after this sacrifice the nine देवीस्, लक्ष्मी, सिनिवाली, कीर्ती, Vasu, धृती and others left their husbands and sported with Soma who acted as their consort; {{F}}4:  Ib. २३. १९-27; ५८. ५४; २३९. ३७; Vi. IV. 6. 8.{{/F}} the title of Soma after the राजसूय. {{F}}5:  वा. ९०. २६.{{/F}}

राजाज|raajaaja
--a son of शम्भु. Br. III. 5. ४०.

राजाधिदेव|raajaadhideva
--a son of विदूरथ and a hero; had two sons शोणाश्व and श्वेतवाहन equal to gods. M. ४४. ७७-8.

राजाधिदेवी|raajaadhidevii
--a वीरमाता; a sister of Vasudeva; a daughter of शूर and Bhoja and queen of Jayasena, king of अवन्ती; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २४. ३१ and ३९; Br. III. ७१. १५१; M. ४६. 4; Vi. IV. १४. ३१.{{/F}} paternal aunt of कृष्ण and queen of अवन्ती. Her daughter मित्रविन्दा loved by कृष्ण who took her away by force and married her, as her brothers wanted to bestow [page३-069+ ३२] her on Duryodhana; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ५८. ३१.{{/F}} according to the भागवत had two sons Vinda and Anuvinda; {{F}}3:  वा. ९६. १४९.{{/F}} mother of two sons. {{F}}4:  Vi. IV. १४. ४३.{{/F}}

राजान|raajaana
--the first kings of the earth were Priyavrata and उत्तानपाद, sons of Manu; wielders of दण्ड; ety. of. वा. ५७. ५८.

राजिक|raajika
--a pupil of कृत. Br. II. ३५. ५१; Vi. ६१. ४४.

राजीवकोकिलस्|raajiivakokilas
--a Janapada of the केतुमाला continent. वा. ४४. १४.

राजीवल|raajiivala
--a horse of the moon's chariot. वा. ५२. ५३.

राजेयस्|raajeyas
--the collective name for the hundred sons of Raji; the latter won over the Asuras and finally established Indra on the throne and retired for penance; his sons deprived Indra of his power when the latter appealed to बृहस्पति; he increased Indra's strength by rituals and made the राजेयस् adopt the जीनधर्म and hence got outside the pale of the Veda, when Indra easily overcame them and got back his kingdom; beginning of जीन dharma and hetu- वाद. M. २४. ३५-49.

राज्यम्|raajyam
--a kingdom; if a king has no legitimate suc- cessor, it changes hands; ruled by ministry in the king's absence; is concerned with two main things (बाह्य) or foreign affairs and (abhyantara) or home policy; {{F}}1:  Br. III. ५०. २९-51; वा. ८८. ९४; ११२. १४. ४६.{{/F}} of पृथु, described. {{F}}2:  M. 1. ११; १०. १०-35.{{/F}} [page३-070+ २८]

राज्यवर्धन(क)|raajyavardhana(ka)
--son of Dama, and father of सुधृति. भा. IX. 2. २९; Br. III. 8. ३५.

राज्याधिदेव|raajyaadhideva
--son of भजमान. वा. ९६. १३५.

राज्ञी|raaJNii
--one of the three wives of विवस्वान्; she was the daughter of Raivata and had a son Revata. M. ११. 2-3.

राडवीय|raaDaviiya
--a pupil of कृत. Br. II. ३५. ५१.

राडि|raaDi
--a pupil of कृत. Br. II. ३५. ५१.

राणायनीय|raaNaayaniiya
--a composer of साम Veda; {{F}}1:  Br. II. ३५. ४४.{{/F}} a Kauthuka and a disciple of लोकाक्षि. {{F}}2:  वा. ६१. ३७-39.{{/F}}

रात्रि|raatri
 (I)--a R. in क्रौञ्चद्वीप. Br. II. १९. ७५; M. १२२. ८८; वा. ४९. ६९; Vi. II. 4. ५५.

रात्रि|raatri
 (II)--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ४४. ७५.

रात्रि|raatri
 (III)--पारमेश्वर; pralaya or destruction at the end of which recurs the creation of the universe. वा. 5. 2 and 6.

रात्रि|raatri
 (IV)--when the Asuras were born to प्रजापति night came into being; ety.; three यामस् of the night are full of darkness--त्रियामिका; then प्रजापति took another guise and created the devas; आसुरि of tamas quality; {{F}}1:  वा. 9. 6-१५; Br. II. १३. १४.{{/F}} no [page३-071+ ३०] night for the region to the north of Meru and south of लोका- loka as the sun is far removed and the earth is surrounded by the lekha; {{F}}2:  वा. ५०. १०८.{{/F}}  for the पितृस् is सुक्लपक्ष; {{F}}3:  Ib. ५१. ११; ५७. 9.{{/F}} enters water in the morning. {{F}}4:  Ib. ५३. १४.{{/F}}

रात्रिसूक्तम्|raatrisuuktam
--a मन्त्र of the ऋग् Vedins to be recited in tank ritual. M. ५८. ३४; ९३. १३१.

राथम्तर|raathamtara
--the 4th kalpa. M. २९०. 3.

राधा|raadhaa
 (I)--came with कृष्ण to mediate between परशुराम and विनायक; spoke on the non-differentiation of शिव and विष्णु; गणेश was a वैष्णव and परशुराम S4aiva. Br. III. ४२. २१, ४७-8; ४३. २१ and २९; ४४. २९; वा. १०४. ५२.

राधा|raadhaa
 (II)--the goddess enshrined at वृन्दावन. M. १३. ३८.

राधाकान्त|raadhaakaanta
--is कृष्ण. Br. III. ३६. ५६.

राधिक|raadhika
--son of Jayasena, and father of Ayuta. भा. IX. २२. १०.

राम|raama
 (I)--Balabhadra of the यादव race and lord of द्वारका. (बलराम): brother of कृष्ण and सुभद्रा; See Baladeva; eldest son of Vasudeva by रोहिनी; father of two sons; welcomed कृष्ण to द्वारका; asked by कृष्ण to take one of the two heavenly chariots and get ready to fight जरासन्ध. राम blew his conch and began fighting [page३-072+ ४४] under his palmyra ensign; defeated the enemies on all sides. Fastened जरासन्ध with ropes but कृष्ण set him free; when जरासन्ध encamped on the यमुना, was consulted by कृष्ण; fought successfully जरासन्ध a third time and defeated बाण's army; when about to give a death-blow to जरासन्ध, a voice from the welkin said “do not kill जरासन्ध; go back.” Thus जरासन्ध was allowed to go back to his city. {{F}}1:  भा. I. ११. १६; X. ५०. १२-32; [५० (v)  8]; [५१ (v)  ३८-58]; [५२ (v) 1-6]; Br. III. ६१. २५; ७१. १६४-8; M. ४६. ११; वा. ८६. ३०; ९६. १६२; Vi. V. 6. 9; १३. १६.{{/F}} Honoured by the याधव sabha, went with कृष्ण to the Gomanta hill; on the way met and bowed to परशुराम; helped कृष्ण in killing शृगाल Vas4udeva and was welcomed by the citizens of करवीरपुर. Stayed in this city for four months and returned to मथुरा with his brother. Attacked by जरासन्ध's army, fled with कृष्ण to Gomanta, pursued by जरासन्ध; reached द्वारका safe. {{F}}2:  भा. X. [५२ (v)  १३-41]; [५३(v) 1-२२]; ५२. 5-6 [5-7]; 7. १४ [1 and 2].{{/F}} Married रेवती before the advent of Kali and hence very tall in appearance; with his plough he brought down her height to his level. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ५२. १५ [११-12].{{/F}} Heard of कृष्ण going alone to कुण्डिन and of the pre- parations of Caidya to fight him; went with his army to कुण्डिन and was welcomed by its king: Attacked Caidya's party pursuing कृष्ण and रुक्मिणी on that account. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ५३. २०-21 and ३२; Ch. ५४ (whole).{{/F}} Went to हास्तिनपुर with कृष्ण after the reported burning of the पाण्डवस् and कुन्ती: Pursued शतधन्वन् with कृष्ण and finding he had not the स्यमन्त in his person, sent कृष्ण back to द्वारका and himself to मिथिला as Janaka's guest; taught the use of the गदा (mace) to Duryodhana. Did not agree with कृष्ण in returning the jewel to अक्रूर. Left for Videha after Satadhanvan's death. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ५७ (whole) ; ५८. 9 [4 and 5]; ६७ (v) ४२.{{/F}} Attended Aniruddha's marriage at भोजकट where induced by Kalinga and other friends, Rukmin invited राम for a game of dice: in it, राम sometimes lost and sometimes gained. At his loss Kalinga laughed showing his teeth. When Rukmin played false it was referred to [page३-073+ ३८] a mediator who was unfortunately Kalinga and who there- fore maintained that Rukmi was in the right. A voice from the air said: “Rukmi tells an untruth”. Without heeding to this Rukmi insulted राम as a forester and herdsman and new to the art of dice. राम got enraged, took the mace and vanquished Rukmi: next he pulled out the teeth of Kalinga making fun of him all the time: others fled in fear; returned to द्वारका. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ६१. २६-40.{{/F}} His picture was among those drawn by चित्रालेखा: In- vaded बाण's city, fought with कुम्भाण्ड and कूप- कर्ण. Once drove to Vraja and spent two months there. During nights he sported and sang with Gopis on the यमुना drinking वारुणी and playing in the waters: changed the course of the river by his plough: {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ६२. २०; ६३. 3-8.{{/F}} यमुना (s.v.) presented him with clothes, and ornaments with which he shone brighter than ever. {{F}}8:  Ib. X. Ch. ६५ (whole).{{/F}} Desire for more territory. {{F}}9:  Ib. XII. 3. 9.{{/F}} Wanted to give सुभद्रा in marriage to Duryodhana but कृष्ण was for her marriage with Arjuna. The latter went to द्वारका as an ascetic when राम one day invited him for भिक्ष। It was an opportunity for Arjuna and सुभद्रा to see each other. Arjuna carried her away on a festive occasion with कृष्ण's consent. राम's wrath was pacified by कृष्ण. Then he approved of the marriage and sent him presents. {{F}}१०:  Ib. X. ८६. 1-१२, १८.{{/F}} Unable to recover the dead son of the द्वा- रका Bra1hman2a. {{F}}११:  Ib. X. ८९, ३१ and ४१.{{/F}} Founded the city of Govardhana on the upper regions of the गोदावरी in the northern part of the Sahya mountain. {{F}}१२:  Br. II. १६. ४४.{{/F}} The God of Love cursed to be born as the brother of कृष्ण at द्वारका. {{F}}१३:  M. 4. १७-21.{{/F}} [page३-074+ ४७]

राम|raama
 (II)--a son of दशरथ known for his righteous- ness and truth: परिक्षित् compared to him: An अवतार् of Hari born in the इक्ष्वाकु line; killed रावण; His fame equalled that of पृथु. {{F}}1:  भा. I. १२. १९; II. 7. २३-25; IV. २२. ६३; IX. १०. 3; M. १२. ५०-51.{{/F}} King of the कोशल country and brother of लक्ष्मण, Bharata, and शत्रुघ्न: Disfigured सूर्पणका; killed मारीच (सुबाहु?) and other राक्षसस् in the यज्ञ of विश्वामित्र, bent and broke the bow of शिव and married सीता, put down the pride of परशुराम, spent a forest life with his wife in obedience to his father's command, killed Khara, त्रिशिरस् and १४,000 राक्षसस्; performed the funeral rites to जटायु, and Kabandha, killed वालि for the sake of सुग्रीव, put up a bridge across the sea, welcomed by the Lord of the seas; killed रावण and कुम्भकर्ण in their capital, ordered विभीषण to perform funeral rites to his dead kith and kin; recovered सीता; enthroned विभी- षण; left in an aerial chariot to अयोध्या, embraced Bharata, paid respects to Brahmanas, Gurus, elders and was crowned by वसिष्ठ just like Indra. In his period which was the त्रेतायुग, it looked like कृतयुग; sons, कुश and Lava; ruled for १०१० years; {{F}}2:  भा. V. १९. 1; VII. 1. ४४; १०. ३६; IX. १०. 3-५२; X. ४०. २०; XI. 4. २१; Br. III. 7. २०३; 8. ५४; ३७. ३०; ६३. १८५-193; ६४. १६; ७३. ९१; वा. ८८. १९२-4; Vi. IV. 4. ८७-102, १०४.{{/F}} led an exemplary household life, by his loyalty to his wedded wife; performed sacrifices by giv- ing all his kingdom as दक्षिण, retaining only the ornaments and dress, and for सीता, her सौमान्गल्य। The Brahmanas returned the kingdom as they had no use for it and praised him. {{F}}3:  भा. IX. १०. ५३-6; ११. 1-7; वा. ७०. ४८; ८८, १८४, १९१-7.{{/F}} One night he went about to know what people talked of his rule. He heard a person saying that राम was mad after सीता, taking her back though she was at another's house for long. Next day he abandoned her and left her at वाल्- मीकि's abode. Here were born his two sons--कुश and Lava. When सीता entered the bowels of the earth, राम led a life of celibacy for १३,000 years giving joy and happiness to the people of कोशल. Sent his brothers on दिग्विजय and him- self resided at the capital. {{F}}4:  भा. IX. ११. 8-३५.{{/F}} Hearing of the रामचरित of वाल्- मीकि, rids one of कर्मबन्धस्; {{F}}5:  Ib. IX. ११. २३; M. १२. ५०-51.{{/F}} resided on the banks of the कदली river; {{F}}6:  Ib. २२. ५३.{{/F}} the २४थ् in the त्रेतायुग; 7th incarnation [page३-075+ ४१] with वसिष्ठ as Purohita; {{F}}7:  Ib. ४७. २४५; ११४. ३८; वा. ९८. ९२; १०८. १६, २४-5.{{/F}} image of, generally ten तलस् in measurement; {{F}}8:  M. २५९. 1.{{/F}} an earthly paradise created by राम in the upper regions of गोदावरी in Govardhana; {{F}}9:  वा. ४५. ११३.{{/F}} performed श्राद्- dha at Rudrapada and दशरथ took the पिण्ड and went to Rudraloka blessing his son to go to विष्णुलोक; {{F}}१०:  Ib. १११, ६४.{{/F}} an incarna- tion of नारायण. {{F}}११:  Vi. IV. १३. ५३.{{/F}}

राम|raama
 (III) (परशुराम)--a son of Jamadagni and रेणुका; an अम्श of Hari. Heard from his father that Arjuna-Haihaya had taken कामधेनु against his wish, and getting angry went to Haihaya's capital, cut off the king's head and took back the cow. In order to get rid of the sin of killing a king, he went on तीर्थयात्र for a year. {{F}}1:  भा. IX. १५. १३ to the end. Br. III. 1. ९८; ६६. ६३; ६९. ४८; M. ४३. ४०; २८५. 7.{{/F}} In obedience to his father's command he killed his mother and brothers. This pleased the father and by his boon to his son, they all came back to life. During his absence, the sons of Haihaya killed his father, and on his return, found his mother crying over the death of Jamadagni. He took his axe, ran to माहिष्मती, rooted out all the क्षत्रियस् by defeating them twenty-one times; with their blood he made nine pools at स्यमन्तपञ्चक, where he worshipped his father's dead body and distributed the various regions to the priests; ended it with अवभृत in the सरस्वती। {{F}}2:  भा. IX. १६. 1-२३; M. २७३. ६६.{{/F}} He would be a great sage in the forthcoming मन्वन्तर। A sage of the 8th मन्वन्तर। Even today resides in Mahen- dra contemplating on Hari; {{F}}3:  भा. VIII. १३. १५; IX. १६. २५-7.{{/F}} was invited for the राजसूय of युधिष्ठिर and came to see कृष्ण at स्यमन्तपञ्चक. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ७४. 9; ८४. 4.{{/F}} In his early years, with the leave of his parents, he visited his grand parents ऋचीक and सत्यवती; and after some stay there, called on his great grandfather भृगु, who advised [page३-076+ ३४] him to do तपस् in the हिमालयस् in honour of शिव. Engaged in तपस् by standing in water in the winter and on the fire in summer, by means of पद्मासन; शिव in hunter's guise visited him and asked him to quit his place. Suspecting him to be god, राम, appealed to him when शिव showed his true form. Instructed by शिव, he went round the earth on a pilgrimage tour. Helped the Devas in routing the Asuras; continued his तपस् by worshipping शिव as मृग- व्याध. Pleased, the Lord instructed him in the अस्त्र- ग्राम in its four aspects; went to ब्रह्मा for advice before he started on his crusade against the क्षत्रियस्. Advised to meet शिव and to get initiated into कृष्णमन्त्र कवचम्; शिव instructed him with त्रैलोक्य विजयम् मन्त्रम्। On his way back he stayed at पुष्कर and heard a male deer narrating the story of परशुराम and अकृतव्रण to the female deer, adding that his was not the उत्तम भक्ति but the मध्यम। He took the hint from that conversation that he would achieve his end by Agastya's grace. राम repaired to the hermitage of Agastya, followed by the deer. {{F}}5:  Br. III. Chh. २१-35.{{/F}} मूलक afraid of; {{F}}6:  Ib. III. ६३. १७९; ७४. २६२.{{/F}} a ब्राह्मण; {{F}}7:  वा. ९४. ४६; ९९. ४४९.{{/F}} a slayer of the क्षत्रियस्; versed in Dhanurveda; {{F}}8:  Ib. ९१. ९१.{{/F}} equal in prowess to Indra resplend- ent and a mixture of Brahma and क्षत्र; {{F}}9:  Ib. ६५. ९४.{{/F}} consort धरनी. {{F}}१०:  Vi. I. 9. १४३.{{/F}}

