 (I)--born of anger of ब्रह्मा; name explained; ‘the weapon’: places assigned to him; his women; asked to procreate and be a प्रजापति; created beings which would burn the universe; persuaded by ब्रह्मा to stop this, and proceed to तपस्; expression of the तमस्। {{F}}1:  भा. III. १२, 7-२०; XI. 4. 5, ३०. ३८.{{/F}} Claimed the remaining wealth of the Angirasa sacrificers as his own, which नाभाग thought was his. When नाभाग gave it to Rudra, the worshipful god presented him that wealth and disappeared; presented पृथु with a sword दशचन्द्र। {{F}}2:  Ib. IX. 4. 6-११; IV. १५. १७.{{/F}} Taught क्रिया yoga to उमा; ब्रह्मा fled in fear from; {{F}}3:  Ib. XI. २७, 3; I. 7. १८.{{/F}} came with the gods to द्वारका to ask कृष्ण to go back to वैकुण्ठ, and glorified Hari. {{F}}4:  Ib. IV. ch. २४ (whole) ; XI. 6. 1; 7. 1. VI. १७. २६-39.{{/F}} No offerings by दक्ष in his sacrifice, and सती's voluntary death. Rudra created वीरभद्र to cause दक्ष's death. ब्रह्मा pacified Rudra and revived दक्ष and others. {{F}}5:  Ib. IV. chh. 4-7.{{/F}} Rudra to bear the गन्गा; {{F}}6:  Ib. IX. 9. 7-9; X. 7. २९; ३९. ५३.{{/F}} addressed कृष्ण as Hari; {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ६३. ३४-45.{{/F}} worship of, leads to wealth and pleasure. Conferred a boon on वृकासुर and came to grief. {{F}}8:  Ib. X. ch. ८८ (whole).{{/F}} [page३-089+ ४५] The presiding deity of the planet शनैश्चर. कालो- Rudra is शिव; at the end of a Kalpa he assumes the form of a Samvarttaka sun and burns down all the worlds. His own messengers of death; worshipped by काम with शत- रुद्रीय. {{F}}9:  Br. II. २४. ४९; III. 3. १०२ and १०९; २३. ६४; ६५. ३२; IV. 6. ७०; 7. ३८; १०. ८७; ११. ३३; १५. २४; ३०. 8; ३६. १६; ४०. १३ and २७.{{/F}} Enshrined in गोकर्ण. {{F}}१०:  Ib. III. १३. २०.{{/F}} Destroyed the god of Love and married उमा on the advice of the seven sages; marriage rites described. {{F}}११:  M. 4. १२, २२; ११. २९; १३. 9. and १४; १३८. २६; १५४. १९४-245, ४३९-83.{{/F}} उमा's transfer as गौरी. {{F}}१२:  Ib. ch. १५५.{{/F}} आडि, son of Andhaka, who attacked him was killed. {{F}}१३:  Ib. ch. १५६.{{/F}} Agni's entrance into the harem when शिव made him drink his वीर। This was God सुब्रह्मण्य nursed by कृत्तिकस्; {{F}}१४:  Ib. ch. १५८.{{/F}} blessed बाणासुर. {{F}}१५:  Ib. ch. १८८; २२५. १३; २५३. ४२.{{/F}} Icon of; in the form of a १६ year old boy; worshipped before buildings; different postures detailed. {{F}}१६:  Ib. २५९. 3-२६; २६५. ४१; २६६. ४३; २६८. २२.{{/F}}

