 (I)--the region of वायु. भा. X. ८९. ४४. [page३-195+ ४७]

वायव्या|vaayavyaa
 (II)--a mind-born mother. M. १७९. १०.

वायस|vaayasa
 (I)--to be fed with स्राद्ध पिण्ड for long life; {{F}}1:  Br. III. १२. ३३; IV. 2. १७४.{{/F}} the crow as belonging to Indra, वरुण, Yama and निरृति; {{F}}2:  वा. १०१. १७१; १०८. ३१; १११. ४०.{{/F}} one of copper, as gift for the ceremonial connected with tank construction. {{F}}3:  M. ५८. १९.{{/F}}

वायस|vaayasa
 (II)--(see वायव्य): a यामदेव. वा. ३१. 7.

वायु|vaayu
 (I)--a God and father of इला; {{F}}1:  भा. IV. १०. 2; १४. २६.{{/F}} and मुदा clan of Apsarasas: presented पृथु with चामरस्: worshipped through प्राणायम in शाकद्वीप; {{F}}2:  Ib. V. १५. १५; २०. २७.{{/F}} A लोकपाल and father of भीम. Took part in the देवासुर wars and killed the Asuras. Deprived of his force by the Asuras; {{F}}3:  Ib. VIII. 5. १९; १०. २६; ११. 1 and ४२; IX. २२. २७. M. ३१. १२; ४६. 9. २६६. २४; वा. ९९. २४४.{{/F}} set out on a black antelope against कृष्ण taking पारिजात, but returned afraid of him; {{F}}4:  भा. X. [६५ (v)  ४४]: [६६ (v)  २७-32]; M. १४८. ६०-61.{{/F}} his city was visited by Arjuna in search of the dead child of a द्वारका Bra1hman2a; {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ८९. ४४; Br. IV. ३३. ६७.{{/F}} Born of आकाश: the wind-god loved अञ्जना and gave birth to हनुमान्: overlord of the winds, formless creatures and of time. Presiding deity of Bhuvarloka and hence Bhuvas- pati (also मातरिश्व). Addressed by the sages engaged in sacrifice to speak on लोकालोक; {{F}}6:  Ib. II. २०. 1 and 7; २५. 5-१४; III. 7. २३, २२४-5, २९६; 8. १२; IV. 2. २०; १९५-7, २१२, २४५-6.{{/F}} narrates the fourth पाद of the ब्रह्माण्ड पुराण, {{F}}7:  Ib. IV. 1. २२७; 4. ४४.{{/F}} reported to उमा in penance of a lady in her chamber little knowing her to be आदि in disguise; {{F}}8:  M. १५६. ३९.{{/F}} worship of; {{F}}9:  Ib. २३६, 5; २५३. २४; २६५. ३९ and ४१. २६८. १२.{{/F}} Icon of, mounted on a black deer, {{F}}१०:  Ib. २६१. १९; २८९. 6.{{/F}} a स्थान of Rudra; {{F}}११:  Vi. I. 8. 7.{{/F}} father of Manojava and भीम; {{F}}१२:  Ib. I. 8. ११; IV. २०. ४०.{{/F}} कृष्ण's messenger to Indra. {{F}}१३:  Ib. V. २१. १४-17; ३७. १६-28.{{/F}} [page३-196+ ३३]

वायु|vaayu
 (II)--is a transformation of आकाश with the two qualities of शब्द and स्पर्श। Its subtle element is स्पर्श from which came तेजस्; {{F}}1:  M. 3. २४.{{/F}} it is प्राण, अपान and समान; {{F}}2:  Ib. १६६. 5.{{/F}} role of, in sustaining life. {{F}}3:  वा. ३१. ४१-5.{{/F}}

वायु|vaayu
 (III)--a Vasu: a son of Dharma and सुदेवी. M. १७१. ४७.

वायु|vaayu
 (IV)--a son of अनुह्राद; {{F}}1:  वा. ६३. १२; ६७. ७५.{{/F}} the lord of सब्द, आकाश and बल, {{F}}2:  Ib. ७०. १२.{{/F}} the appointed father of वृकोदर; {{F}}3:  Ib. ९९. २४४.{{/F}} present- ed Skanda with the banners of the cuckoo and hen. {{F}}4:  Ib. ७२. ४५.{{/F}}

वायु|vaayu
 (V)--a तिर्थ sacred to, in the सरस्वती. भा. III. 1. २२.

वायु पुराण|vaayu puraaNa
--contents of; originally narrated by ब्रह्मा; or पाशुपत Yoga, origin of Linga, glorification of नीलकण्ठ; one who does not know this पुराण, though learned in all the Vedas and other branches, will not be a man of culture; the whole पुराण is full of the greatness of महेश्वर; {{F}}1:  वा. 1. ४८-205.{{/F}} narrator वायु; {{F}}2:  Ib. २६. 5.{{/F}} (see वायवीयम्) .

वायुलोक|vaayuloka
--burnt by the Pralaya fire. Br. IV. 1. १५३.

वायुस्कन्ध|vaayuskandha
--the residence of Marut गणस्. वा. 1. १३४.

वारण|vaaraNa
--the heavenly animal which came down for Haryanga's help. M. ४८. ९८. [page३-197+ ४०]

वारणशैलेन्द्र|vaaraNashailendra
--शिव in काञ्ची. Br. IV. 5. 7.

वारणावतम्|vaaraNaavatam
--the city of हस्तिनापुर; सत्यभामा goes there to complain to कृष्ण often about the death of her father by शतधन्वा; {{F}}1:  वा. ९६. ६१.{{/F}} here कृष्ण went to perform the last obsequies to the पाण्डवस् who were reported to have been burnt down. {{F}}2:  Br. III. ७१. ६३; Vi. IV. १३. ७०.{{/F}}

वारा|vaaraa
--a शक्ति. Br. IV. ३२. १७.

वाराणसी|vaaraaNasii
--काशी: sacred to Hari; {{F}}1:  भा. VII. १४. ३१; X. ६६. ४०.{{/F}} fit for श्राद्ध offer- ing, and sacred to ललिता; {{F}}2:  Br. III. १३. १०१; IV. ४४. ९३.{{/F}} the capital of दिवोदास devastated by the राक्षस Ks2emaka, resulting in the change of capital to गोमती. The abode of शिव and उमा after their marriage, and hence the name Avimuktam क्षेत्रम्; {{F}}3:  Ib. III. ६७. २६-62.{{/F}} the goddess enshrined here is विशालाक्षी: a place of pilgrimage; {{F}}4:  M. १३. २६; २२. 7.{{/F}} capital of रुद्रशृएण्य of the Yadu race: city where मार्कण्डेय lived. {{F}}5:  Ib. ४३. ११; १०३. १३.{{/F}} Lord became क्षेत्रपाल: the यक्ष Harikes4a per- formed penance here; {{F}}6:  Ib. १८०. 1-5, १५ and ५४.{{/F}} the place of Yogis and Siddhas: death here is release from rebirth; {{F}}7:  Ib. १८०. ७२-79.{{/F}} a siddha क्षेत्र where शिव and His consort live all the three yugas and make Avi- muktam गृहम् in Kaliyuga; {{F}}8:  वा. ७७. ९३; ९२. २७, ५८-59; ९९. ३१५.{{/F}} अवतार् of लान्गलि at, in the २२न्द् dva1para; {{F}}9:  Ib. २३. १९८.{{/F}} cursed by Nikumbha to become deserted for 1,००० years; {{F}}१०:  ९२. २३-28.{{/F}} burnt down by कृष्ण. {{F}}११:  Vi. V. ३४. 3, ३९-41.{{/F}}

वाराणसी माहात्म्यम्|vaaraaNasii maahaatmyam
--शिव addresses पार्वती on, in taking her out and showing the grandeur and majesty of the forest and garden round about काशी; the place of विद्या- [page३-198+ ४१] dharas, Siddhas and चारणस्. Here भगवान् Pin3gala became गणेश्वर and क्षेत्रपाल and distributor of food to the residents in the city. He was originally a यक्ष, son of पूर्णभद्र. He devoted himself to severe austerities and was blessed by शिव to be a गणपति. {{F}}1:  M. ch. १८०.{{/F}} It is अविमुक्त तीर्थ for here शिव is omnipresent and is never absent from there. All sinners who die here become Rudras in time. शिव stands here like a pillar, motionless till the deluge. Every part of the city is holy. {{F}}2:  Ib. ch. १८१.{{/F}} He who remains here for a month gets the benefit of observ- ing the पाशुपत vow. By living permanently one gets true emancipation. By giving up life at the मणिकर्णिका ghat one secures the desired goal. Perpetual life in काशी leads one to union with शिव. {{F}}3:  Ib. ch. १८२.{{/F}} काशी's importance on account of its sacred stream, the Ganges; survives all deluge; शिव addresses पार्- वती on the great glory of the क्षेत्रम् in terms of Parama- yoga, Paramagati and परममोक्ष. It is a place where people of all वर्णस् attain immortality. Gifts of cow and other things in this city are always beneficial. {{F}}4:  Ib. ch. १८३.{{/F}} It is the place where शिव got rid of the curse of ब्रह्मा to roam about with a skull for having cut off the fifth head of the creator. Through the grace of Hari, the skull fell down in काशी and broke into a thousand pieces. {{F}}5:  Ib. ch. १८४.{{/F}} It is the burial ground of all the gods, the ground being the Avimukta temple. It is the seat of ब्रह्मा. But it deludes non- devotees. Here वेदव्यास resided for १२ years observing the vow of silence. At the end of the vow he felt hungry and asked for alms. None was able to feed him. When he was about to curse the city, शिव and पार्वती took the human form and entertained him to his satisfaction. Then व्यास knew of his guests who remarked that a man of choleric temper like himself should not live in that city. But he was permitted to visit it twice a fortnight on अष्टमि and चतुर्दशी days. {{F}}6:  Ib. ch. १८५.{{/F}} [page३-199+ ३०]

वाराह|vaaraaha
 (I)--(विष्णु). An अवतार् of Hari who raised the earth from the waters, see वराह, the form which विष्णु takes in the श्वेतकल्प with four feet, four hands, etc., becomes Samvatsara and assumes the form of यज्ञ; the four yugas are four feet, the क्रतुस् are अङ्गस् or limbs, the four Vedas are the hands ऋतु, सन्धिमुखस्, two अयनस् are the faces and eyes, three पर्वस् are the heads, etc., {{F}}1:  भा. XI. 4. १८; वा. २३. १०३-7; ४८. ४०; ४९. ११; Vi. I. 4. 8, २६.{{/F}} appro- priate to water sports; description of; {{F}}2:  Br. I. 5. ११, ff.{{/F}} helped by माया, wife (छाया-वा। प्।) out of the recovered earth came mountains and seven worlds; creation of human beings; {{F}}3:  Ib. I. 5. १९.{{/F}} where ब्रह्मा is said to assume this form. {{F}}4:  Ib. II. 7. 7-9.{{/F}}

वाराह|vaaraaha
 (II)--a Mt. afraid of हिरण्यकशिपु's arms. M. १६३. ८१.

वाराह|vaaraaha
 (III)--the २६थ् kalpa. M. २९०. 9.

वाराह|vaaraaha
 (IV)--the present kalpa; fourteen Manus be- ginning with स्वायम्भुव; name and features explained. वा. २१. १२, २३, २६ f. Vi. I. 3. २८; II. 1. ४३.

वाराहस्|vaaraahas
--a Janapada of the भद्रा continent. वा. ४३. २२.

वाराह कल्प|vaaraaha kalpa
--in this aeon, Hari took the incarnation of a boar; see वराह. भा. III. ११. ३६.

वाराहम्|vaaraaham
--a महापुराण, comprising २४,000 श्लोकस्; {{F}}1:  भा. XII. 7. २४; १३. 7; Vi. III. 6. २३.{{/F}} narrated by विष्णु to क्षोणि containing the माहात्म्य of [page३-200+ २६] महावाराह; he who gives it with a golden eagle on the Full Moon day of Madhu reaches oneness with विष्णु. {{F}}2:  M. ५३. ३९-41.{{/F}}

वाराहमुखी|vaaraahamukhii
--a शक्ति. Br. IV. २०. ३७.

वाराहि|vaaraahi
--a Pravara (Angiras). M. १९६. १२, १३.

वाराही|vaaraahii
 (I)--a surname of ललिता. Br. IV. १७. १९.

वाराही|vaaraahii
 (II)--a शक्ति; a mind-born mother. {{F}}1:  Br. IV. १९. 7; २०. ३७; M. १७९. ११.{{/F}} Icon of, with buffalo mount. {{F}}2:  Ib. २६१. ३०.{{/F}}

वाराही|vaaraahii
 (III)--a R. of the वराहद्वीपम्. वा. ४८. ३९.

