शर्मिष्ठा|sharmiShThaa
 (I)--a daughter of वृषपर्वन् (hence वार्षपर्वणि-वि। प्।) and wife of ययाति. She once went with her attendants and देवयानी, and became engaged in water sports. शिव and पार्वती passed them when they put on their dress. In doing so शर्मिष्ठा put on देवयानी's dress by mistake and was taken to task by देवयानी who called [page३-391+ ३६] her a slave, arrogating superiority as a Brahmana girl. शर्मिष्ठा grew angry and stripping her of her clothes threw her into a well and returned home; {{F}}1:  भा. VI. 6. ३२; Br. III. 6. २३; ६८. १५; M. 6. २२; २४. ५२; Chh. २७-30; Vi. IV. १०, 4.{{/F}} शुक्र resented the action of the princess and left the palace though the king begged his pardon. शुक्र agreed to stay on condition that शर्मिष्ठा would follow देवयानी wherever she went. It was agreed. She was given to ययाति when देवयानी was married to him. ययाति advised not to share his bed with शर्मिष्ठा. One day after her monthly period शर्मिष्ठा requested him to embrace her, which he did. She became mother of three sons--Druhya, Anu and पूरु. {{F}}2:  भा. IX. १८. 6-३३; M. Chh. ३१-32; वा. ६८. २३; ९३. १६.{{/F}}

