--a grandson of नन्दियश; ruled at पूरिका. Br. III. ७४. १८३.

शिशिर|shishira
 (I)--Mt. on the base of Meru, and on the south of the मानस. भा. V. १६. २६; Br. II. १४. ३८; १९. १५; वा. ३६. २२; ३८. 2; Vi. II. 2. २८.

शिशिर|shishira
 (II)--a pupil of शाकल्य. भा. XII. 6. ५७.

शिशिर|shishira
 (III)--a son of मेधातिथि and the founder of the शिशिरम् kingdom in प्लक्षद्वीप. Br. II. १४. ३६-8; वा. ३३. ३२; Vi. II. 4. 3, 5.

शिशिर|shishira
 (IV)--a क्षत्रिय who became a dvija. Br. III. ६६. ८८.

शिशिर|shishira
 (V)--son of अरिष्टिसेन. Br. III. ६७. 6.

शिशिर|shishira
 (VI)--a son of Dhara. M. 5. २४.

शिशिर|shishira
 (VII)--a कौशिक Brahmis2t2ha. M. १४५. ११३.

शिशिर|shishira
 (VIII)--a mind-born son of ब्रह्मा in the १६थ् Kalpa. वा. २१. ३५. [page३-431+ २६]

शिशिर|shishira
 (IX)--the winter; the first of ऋतुस्. वा. ५३. २६, ११३.

शिशिर|shishira
 (X)--a son of Dharma (Vasu). Vi. I. १५. ११३.

शिशिरायिणी|shishiraayiNii
--a daughter of वृकदेवी. वा. ९६. १८०.

शिशिरावती|shishiraavatii
--one of Vasudeva's wives and mother of four sons. Br. III. ७१. १८३.

शिशु|shishu
 (I)--a son of बलराम. Br. III. ७१. १६६.

शिशु|shishu
 (II)--a son of सारण. वा. ९६. १६४; Vi. IV. १५. २१.

शिशुक|shishuka
--the आन्ध्र king who vanquished शुशर्मा, the कण्व: ruled for २३ years. M. २७३. 2.

शिशुनन्दि|shishunandi
--ruled from किलिकिला. भा. XII. 1. ३२.

शिशुनाक|shishunaaka
--succeeded Nandivardhana eclipsing the fame of all his predecessors and became ruler of Girivraja; killed the Pradyotas and became king at वाराणसी; esta- blished his son at Benares; ruled for ४० years; suc- ceeded by काकवर्ण, क्षेमधर्मा, क्षेमजित्, Vin- dhyasena, भूमिपुत्र, अजातशत्रु, वम्शक, उदासि, Nandivardhana and महानन्दि; all of them ruled for ३६० years; their contemporaries are इक्ष्वाकुस्, पाञ्चलस्, [page३-432+ ३७] काशेयस्, Haihayas, Kalingas, अश्मकस्, Kurus, Maithilas, शूरसेनस् and वीतिहोत्रस्. M. २७२. 6-१७; वा. ९९. ३१४-15.

शिशुनाग|shishunaaga
--the father of काकवर्ण; became ruler after rooting out the Pradyotas; ruled for ४० years at Benares. भा. XII. 1. 5; Br. III. ७४. १२७-8.

शिशुनागस्|shishunaagas
--ten in number commencing with शिशुनाग, and ending with महानन्दि; these ruled for ३६० years. {{F}}1:  भा. XII. 1. 7; Br. III. ७४. १२७-35.{{/F}} These are क्षत्रबन्धुस् and contemporaries of इक्ष्वाकुस्, पाञ्चलस्, कालकस्, Haihayas, Ekalingas, शकस्, Kuravas, Maithilas, सूरसेनस्, वीतिहोत्रस्.^2 (See also शिशुनाक).

शिशुनाभ|shishunaabha
--the father of काकवर्ण. Vi. IV. २४. 9-१०.

शैशनाभस्|shaishanaabhas
--descendants of शिशुनाभ; rule of, for ३६२ years. Vi. IV. २४. १९.

शिशुपाल|shishupaala
--a son of श्रुतश्रवस् and दमघोष; in pre- vious births, हिरण्यकशिपु killed by Narasimha and रावण (दशग्रीव) killed by राम; a hater of Hari but was shown grace by कृष्ण; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. २४. ४०; VII. 1. १७; X. ६०. १८; २९. १३; Br. ७१. १५८-59; वा. ९६. १५७-58.{{/F}} attacked the northern gate of मथुरा and Gomanta when they were besieged by जरासन्ध; {{F}}2:  भा. X. ५०. ११ [7]; ५२. ११ [१५].{{/F}} engaged by भीष्मक for his daughter रुक्मिणी under the influence of Rukmin, his eldest son; defeated by कृष्ण who carried off रुक्मिणी; consoled by his friends that Time was not in his favour he returned to his city. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ५३ (whole); ५४. 9-१७; Vi. V. २६. 3 and 7.{{/F}} Protested against the place of honour being given to कृष्ण when ब्रह्मऋषिस् and राजऋषिस् were available. He vilified him as a cowherd given to drinking and not an observer of वर्णधर्म. While the पाण्डवस् drew their swords, कृष्ण cut off his head. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ७४ (whole).{{/F}} His [page३-433+ ३५] friend was शाल्व who summoned a conference at कुण्डिन to which शिशुपाल went. {{F}}5:  Ib. X. ५७. १९; ७६. 2 [१०]; ७८. [5]; Vi. IV. १४. ४५. ५२.{{/F}} As he died remembering the Lord, he attained मोक्ष; {{F}}6:  भा. VII. १०. ३८; XI. 5. ४८; Br. IV. २९. १२२.{{/F}} (see Caidya). Maitreya asked पराशर how it was that though he was killed by the Lords Nara- simha and राम, हिरण्यकशिपु did not attain salvation but was reborn as शिसुपाल, and how he attained it when killed by कृष्ण; पराशर replied that neither हिरण्यकशिपु nor रावण knew that Narasimha or राम were the अवतार्स् of विष्णु; शिशुपाल knew in his heart of hearts that कृष्ण was God विष्णु and welcomed death at his hands. Hence his salvation. {{F}}7:  Vi. IV. १५. 1-१५.{{/F}}

शिशुमार|shishumaara
 (I)--a प्रजापति; father of Bhrami and father-in-law of Dhruva. भा. IV. १०. ११.

शिशुमार|shishumaara
 (II)--the form of the system of heavenly bodies supposed to be yoga power of Hari. At the end of the tail is Dhruva and on the tail are other gods like Indra, Agni, कश्यप; on its back lies the अजवीथि and on the stomach the Ganges. Similarly all constellations and planets are seen on the different limbs of its body; {{F}}1:  भा. II. 2. २४; V. २३. 4-8; VI. 6. १४; Br. I. 1. ८५. II. २३. ९९; M. १२५. 5-9; १२७. १९; वा. 1. १०१; Vi. II. १२. २९, ३४.{{/F}} described. {{F}}2:  M. १२८. १९-25.{{/F}}

शिशुमार|shishumaara
 (III)--is तारामय; the eternal deity; उत्ता- नपाद is the upper jaw, यज्ञ is the lower lip, Dharma is the head, heart is नारायण, साध्य and अश्विन्स् front feet, वरुण and Aryama is the hind feet, the samvatsara, child; Mitra is अपान; tail is Agni, Mahendra, मरीचि and कश्यप and Dhruva; all the planets are centred in Dhruva. वा. ५२. ९०-9; Vi. II. 9. २३-4. [page३-434+ २८]

शिशुमारपुर|shishumaarapura
--in the third tala or Vitala. वा. ५०. २६.

शिशुमार्ग|shishumaarga
--an Asura with a city in the third Talam. Br. II. २०. २७.

शिष्ट|shiShTa
--a son of Dhruva and धन्या; married सुच्छाया daughter of Agni. M. 4. ३८.

शिष्टस्|shiShTas
--also designated शन्त and साधुस्; those who have conquered the senses; साधु brahmaca1ri, साधु gr2hasta, साधु vaikha1nasa and साधु yati by yoga practice; followers of स्मार्त and श्रौत karmas; put in practice आचार which is eightfold; जितात्मन्स्। Br. II. ३२. १९-53; ३५. १९२.

शिष्टाचार|shiShTaachaara
--characteristics of; eight limbs are gifts, truth, tapas, non-covetousness, learning, sacrifice, honour and modesty (giving birth to a son and sympathy-वा। प्।). Prac- tised by seven sages; the features of the above eight limbs; the शिष्टस् are Manu and the seven sages who promulgate laws relating to त्रयी, वार्ता and दण्डनीति, इज्या and Var- णाश्रम; the आचारस् are besides the two-fold श्रौत and स्मार्त dharma. Br. II. ३२. ३६; ३५. १९२; IV. 3. ४९; M. १४५. ३३-34. ३७, ३९, ४२-52; वा. ५९. ३३-37; १०२. ७०.

शिष्ति|shiShti
--a son of Dhruva; wife सुच्छाया; Ripu and four other sons. Vi. I. १३. 1.

शिसुक|shisuka
--a grandson of नन्दियश, ruled in पुरीका. वा. ९९. ३७०. [page३-435+ ३०]

शीक्षा|shiixaa
--a part of विष्णु. Vi. V. 1. ३७.

शीघ्र(ग)|shiighra(ga)
 (I)--the son of अग्निवर्ण and father of Maru. भा. IX. 2. 5; Br. III. ६३. २१०; वा. ८८. २१०; Vi. IV. 4. १०८.

शीघ्रग|shiighraga
 (II)--a son of सम्पाति. M. 6. ३५.

शीतम्भ|shiitambha
--a hill range on the east of Meru. Vi. II. 2. २७.

शीतम्शु|shiitamshu
--a son of Atri born of his tejas in tapas; fell down on the earth landed by the seven mind-born sons of प्रजापतिस्; ब्रह्मा supplied him with a chariot yoked with a thousand white horses; the lustre spread in २१ ways in the earth; the vegetation became ever green and the nourisher of men; anointed राजराट् by ब्रह्मा in the kingdom of seeds, vegetation, Brahmans and waters; the २७ daughters of दक्ष, known as नक्षत्रस् given in marriage to; performed राज- सूय; for this हिरण्यगर्भ was उद्गात, ब्रह्मा, ब्रह्मी and Sadasya was नारायण Hari; attended by सनत्कुमार and other sages; दक्षिण was three worlds; he was served by nine देवीस् Sini1, कूहू and others; got the title of राज- राजेन्द्र; in his pride seized forcibly the consort तारा of बृहस्पति to censure the sons of Angiras; in spite of request from the devas he did not yield; तारकामय battle helped by शुक्र and Rudra; ब्रह्मा intervened and तारा was re- turned to बृहस्पति; she was pregnant and brought forth a son named Budha; struck by consumption, invoked Atri's help, got rid of the disease and became resplendent and the originator of a great dynasty. वा. ९०. 1-४९. [page३-436+ २९]

शीतवृत्तास्|shiitavRttaas
--एकार्षेयस्. M. २००. 4.

शीतान्त|shiitaanta
--a Mt. to the east of अरुणोद. वा. ३६. १८; ३७. 1; ४२. १६.

शीताम्शु|shiitaamshu
--an attribute of the Moon; taken up from the milk ocean by महेश्वर. Vi. I. 9. ९७.

शीतोदम्|shiitodam
--a lake in the west. वा. ३६. १६.

शीलावति|shiilaavati
--the wood cutter's wife earned this name on account of her charity. Br. IV. 7. ३५.

शीलव्रतम्|shiilavratam
--gives शील and आरोग्य and leads to शिवपद. M. १०१. ३९.

श्रीसर|shriisara
--the holy lake in the valley between the moun- tains शीतान्त and with a महापद्म in the middle where श्री lives. वा. ३७. 5-8.

शुक|shuka
 (I)--a son of व्यास and अरणी and a great yogin; superior to his father as a yogi; seeing him firm in renuncia- tion, व्यास taught him the भागवत; renounced worldly life before his upanayana. Wandered naked from place to place and reached the country of कुरुजान्गलस्. When at हास्तिनापुर he stopped for a few minutes at the threshold of householders to purify their abode. {{F}}1:  भा. I. 2. 2-3; 4. 2-8; 7. 8; M. १५. 8.{{/F}} सूत's salutation to: called on परीक्षित् doing प्रायोपवेश and imparted know- ledge to him, addressed by the king as to the best way of spending his last moments for attaining मोक्ष। Enlightened [page३-437+ ३४] him by the भागवत episodes; {{F}}2:  Ib. I. १२. 3; १९. २५-39; 1. 3; XII. 6. 8.{{/F}} went with कृष्ण to मिथिला, and to स्यमन्तपञ्चक for the solar eclipse. Took part in defending द्वारका against शाल्व. {{F}}3:  Ib. X. ८६. १८; ७६. १४; ८२. 6.{{/F}} On सौर गण as seven for each month. Heard the story of Citraketu from व्यास, नारद and Devala. {{F}}4:  Ib. XII. ११. २७; VI. १४. 9.{{/F}} In the form of a Brahman; one of the twelve who knew the धर्म ordained by Hari. {{F}}5:  Ib. XII. १३. २१; VI. 3. २०.{{/F}} A Madhya- माध्वर्यु; married पीवरी and got by her five sons all योगा- चार्यस् and a daughter कीर्तिमती, a योगिनी; of superior bhakti; (married पीवरी, the mind-born daughter of the बर्हिषद् Manes and had by her a daughter and four sons-म्। प्।) the sons were कृष्ण, Gama, Prabhu, शम्भु and भूरिश्रुत. {{F}}6:  Br. I. 1. १५०; II. ३३. १४; III. 8. ९२-4; १०. ८०-82; ३४. ३८; M. १५. 8; वा. ७०. ८४; ७३. २८; १०८. ४२ and ६०.{{/F}}

शुक|shuka
 (II)--a son of गार्हपत्य agni. Br. II. १२. १२.

शुक|shuka
 (III)--a son of शरभ and father of ऋक्ष. Br. III. 7. २०७.

शुक|shuka
 (IV)--the father-in-law of अणुह. M. ४९. ५७; वा. ९९. १७९.

शुकस्|shukas
--parrots, children of शुकि; {{F}}1:  M. 6. ३१.{{/F}} cry in the presence of poisoned food; {{F}}2:  Ib. २१९. २०.{{/F}} of the Tamra line. {{F}}3:  Vi. I. २१. १६.{{/F}}

शुककन्या|shukakanyaa
--see कृत्वी. भा. IX. २१. २५.

शुकनदी|shukanadii
--a R. of the केतुमाला continent. वा. ४४. १८. [page३-438+ २६]

शुकनास|shukanaasa
--a Janapada of the केतुमाला continent. वा. ४४. १३.

शुकप्रिया|shukapriyaa
--a name of ललिता. Br. IV. १७. ३३ and ४४.

शुकी|shukii
 (I)--loved by अग्नी. भा. IV. २४. ११.

शुकी|shukii
 (II)--a daughter of ताम्रा and कश्यप; married Garutmat and had six sons त्रिशिर, Sumukha, Bala, पृष्ट, त्रिशन्कुनेत्र and Surasa who had in their turn a number of sons and grandsons; {{F}}1:  Br. III. 7. 8-9, ४४६; वा. ६९. ३२८-30.{{/F}} brought forth parrots and owls; gave birth to parrots, owls, and crows (वि। प्।) {{F}}2:  M. 6. ३०-31; Vi. I. २१. १५-16.{{/F}}

शुक्तस्|shuktas
--heat making rays of the sun. वा. ५३. २२.

शुक्तिमत्|shuktimat
--(Kulaparvata) a hill in भारतवर्ष. भा. V. १९. १६; Br. II. १६. १८; वा. ४५. ८९, १०७; Vi. II. 3. 3.

शुक्तिमती|shuktimatii
--a R. from the ऋक्ष hill. Br. II. १६. ३१; वा. ४५. १०१.

शुक्तिमन्ती|shuktimantii
--a R. from the ऋष्यवान्. M. ११४. २६.

शुक्तिमान्|shuktimaan
--a kulaparvata. M. ११४. १७ and ३२.

शुक्र|shukra
 (I)--(alias उशनस्) a son of Kavi (हविर्धान and दिव्या, hence काव्य); married ऊर्जस्वती, and father of [page३-439+ ४९] देवयानी through जयन्ती. {{F}}1:  भा. III. 1. २२; IV. 1. ४५; V. 1. ३५; VI. 7. १८; वा. ६३. २३; ६५. ७४; ९३. ८५; १०१. ३३; Vi. I, १४. 2.{{/F}} The Purohita of हिरण्यकशिपु. Father of शण्ड and Marka, tutors of प्रह्लाद. Took part in प्रह्लाद's coronation. A ब्रह्मऋषि: Heard of the in- sult offered to his daughter by शर्मिष्ठा, the daughter of the ruler वृषपर्वन् and left the capital. The Purohita of वृषपर्वन्, the latter made him stay offering to make his daughter a slave of देवयाणी. In offering the latter to ययाति, he asked him not to share his bed with शर्मिष्ठा, cursed ययाति to become aged for having shared his bed with शर्मिष्ठा, and on an appeal mitigated it by saying that he could exchange his old age with youth of another if he found one to accept the exchange; {{F}}2:  भा. IX. Ch. १८ (whole); VII. 5. 1-2 १०. ३३; Br. III. ६८. १५; M. २५. 4, १६; २७. २६, ३७; ३०. ३०-36; ३२. २३, २६; ३३. 2 and २६.{{/F}} joined Soma in तारकामय war: blessed the Asuras in this war: fought with बृहस्पति in a देवासुर battle. {{F}}3:  भा. IX. १४. 6; VIII. १०. ३३.{{/F}} Brought back to life the unconscious Bali by सञ्जीविनी Vidya. Presented Bali with an unfading garland of flowers; knowing वामन to be Hari, warned Bali from agreeing to his request. Bali would not hear, and शुक्र cursed him to lose all श्री. At the bidding of Hari com- pleted the यज्ञ begun by Bali. {{F}}4:  Ib. VIII. ११. ४७-8; १५. 6; १९. ३०-43; २०. 1-१५; २३. १८; Br. III. ३०. ५४; ६५. ३१; M. १९२. १०; २४६. 1.{{/F}} The third वेदव्यास. Heard the पुराण from वायु and told it to बृहस्पति; {{F}}5:  Br. III. 1. ७६ and ८६; १०. १८; II. ३५. ११७; IV. 4. ५९.{{/F}} wor- shipped स्थानु with severe penance; born in तिष्यनक्षत्र: married mind-born daughter of पितृस् (Somapas) and father of 4 sons, त्वष्ट्रि, Varatri, शण्ड and Marka; {{F}}6:  Ib. I. 1. १२७-9; II. २४. ५०-51 and १३१; ३३. ३२; III. 1. ७५-8; १०. ८६-7; ६८. १५, ८६-7.{{/F}} cursed the Asuras when they lost their empire, and यज्ञ came to the side of Devas. Asura's appeal and शुक्र's penance to शिव. Finding the Asuras having no आचार्य, the Devas attacked them who appealed to शुक्र's mother. विष्णु at the instance of Indra slew her, a woman and a wife of भृगु, for which विष्णु was cursed to be born on earth as man seven times. Indra then set up his daughter जयन्ती to serve शुक्र and earn his goodwill. Pleased with her service, शुक्र agreed to live with her as husband for ten years. After this period, बृहस्पति assumed his form and deluded the Asuras. शुक्र who grew angry cursed the Asuras at which बृहस्पति felt happy and threw off his disguise. They appealed to शुक्र for help once again or threatened to leave for रसातलम्. He managed to get back their kingdom in the epoch of सावर्णि [page३-440+ ४८] when Bali was emperor; {{F}}7:  Ib. III. ७२. ९३-195; ७३. 2, ५८; M. ४७. ८६-111, १७२-202.{{/F}} lives in Bhuvarlokam; आश्रम of, located below the सहस्रशिखर and Kumuda hills; {{F}}8:  Br. IV. 2. ३०; वा. ३८. ६०-2;{{/F}} consecrated भण्ड on the throne; {{F}}9:  Br. IV. १२ 2-6; १७. ५६.{{/F}} revealed अन्गारकव्रत to विऋओचन; {{F}}१०:  M. ६२. 6, २७-40.{{/F}} preached peace between the devas and asuras after seeing the destruction of twelve wars: wanted to excel बृहस्पति in मन्त्र by the grace of शिव and learnt नीति from शिव; {{F}}११:  Ib. ४७. ६१-84.{{/F}} encouraged Asuras by giving them his pupils शण्ड and Marka for assistance. But his curse tells when the pupils desert them. Both were bought off by gods who offered them a status in sacrifices. This resulted in the helplessness of Asuras who entered रसातलम्; {{F}}१२:  Ib. ४७. २१०-233; ४८. ९३; ९३. १४.{{/F}} appointed Purohita of the Asuras; expert in सञ्जीविनी vidya1, revived the dead back to life; {{F}}१३:  Ib. २५. 9.{{/F}} taught Kaca, son of बृहस्पति; {{F}}१४:  Ib. २५. ४७.{{/F}} has ruled that the son of the king who pleases his father best is entitled to the throne; {{F}}१५:  Ib. ३४. २४-5.{{/F}} a ऋषि; {{F}}१६:  Ib. ४७. ६२ and ११४; १२६. ६९; १४५. ९२.{{/F}} a मन्त्रकृत्; {{F}}१७:  Ib. १४५. १०३.{{/F}} asked Bali to treat वामन with choice gift. ^१८ Ib. २४६. 3.

