 3-८६.{{/F}} who are eligible to be fed and those who are not; Grahasta, वानप्रस्थ, Yati and वालखिल्य are eligible; those beyond the आश्रमस् are not eligible; the leavings of श्राद्धस् not to be given to women and शूद्रस् but to sons, {{F}}7:  Ib. III. १५. 3, ३८, ५९.{{/F}} gifts of rice, कमण्डलु, fans, slippers, cloths and gems, silver and gold vessels, fuel, bed, silk, etc., made on the occasion will result in long life, health, wealth, children, cattle, conveyance, etc., {{F}}8:  Ib. III. १६. 1.{{/F}} either it is काम्य or नैमित्तिक and अजस्र; to be done on all the १५ days of the dark half of the month including the अमावास्य and its effects; {{F}}9:  Ib. III. १७-1, १०-20.{{/F}} the श्राद्ध performed under every नक्षत्र and its results as narrated by Yama to शशबिन्दु; {{F}}१०:  Br. १८. 2-१४.{{/F}} हविस् of sesamum, rice, fruits and roots, flesh of animals and birds like fish, deer, hare, parrots, hog, छागल, gavya, aura- bhra, खड्ग, etc.; three Brahmans to be fed representing the trinity; not to feed those addicted to liquor, cattle rear- ing, and are messengers of villages, merchants; also one who picks up quarrels with parents, whose wife is in periods, a thief, one insulting friends, mad, hemophrodite, culpable of child murder, defiler of preceptor's bed, physician, adulterer, seller of Vedic Niyamas, dogs and brahmicides not to be seen in a श्राद्ध; the sprinkling of seasamum is to ward off Asuras and रक्षसस् from taking part; the time is the fore- noon of शुक्लपक्ष and afternoon of कृष्णपक्ष; {{F}}११:  Ib. III. १९. 2.{{/F}} offering of पिण्डस्; thus said बृहस्पति to his son in the श्राद्ध कल्प; {{F}}१२:  २०. १०; IV. 4. ५३.{{/F}} ordained for पितृस्; places for oblations in the absence of fire; articles fit and unfit for; {{F}}१३:  M. १५. ३०-38; २०४. 1.{{/F}} kinds of, and details relat- ing to; {{F}}१४:  {{/F}} साधारण श्राद्ध described; {{F}}१५:  Ib. ch. १७.{{/F}} तीर्थस् for perform- ance of. {{F}}१६:  Ib. ch. २२.{{/F}} [page३-478+ २६]

