सत्राजित|satraajita
--(सत्राजित्-म्। प्।) a son of Nimna (Nighna- ब्र्। and वि। प्।) a friend of God आदित्य; afraid of कृष्ण, be- friended him by bestowing his daughter and the jewel Sya- mantaka on कृष्ण. This jewel was given to him as a present by the Sun god. Wearing it सत्राजित made the citizens of द्वारका blind by its splendour. It was placed in a seperate house to be worshipped as God; refused to part with it when कृष्ण demanded it for the Yadu king. His brother Pra- sena while out a hunting took it to the forest where a lion killed him. जाम्बवन् killed the lion and took the jewel and gave it to his daughter. सत्राजित suspected कृष्ण of killing his brother and depriving him of the jewel. कृष्ण went to the forest, tracked the steps which led to the cave of जाम्बवन्, and after defeating him took his daughter and the jewel to द्वारका. In a public assembly सत्राजित was sent for and the jewel was given to him by कृष्ण. सत्राजित's concern how to befriend कृष्ण. He offered his daughter and the jewel to him. He married the daughter सत्यभामा but returned the jewel to him; {{F}}1:  भा X. ch. ५६ (whole): IX. २४. १३; Br. III. ७१. २१-60; Vi. V. १३. १०, १४.{{/F}} married the ten daughters of Kaikeya who gave birth to १०१ sons. the eldest of whom was भङ्गकार; {{F}}2:  M. ४५. १७, १९.{{/F}} other members of the family, अक्रूर, शतधन्वा and others who wished to marry सत्यभामा became jealous and plotted to kill सत्राजित्; शतधन्वा mur- [page३-521+ २४] dered him while asleep; in order to avenge his death and also to take the jewel, कृष्ण pursued him and killed him. {{F}}3:  Vi. IV. १३. ६७-100.{{/F}}

