सरस्वती|sarasvatii
 (II)--(महानदी) R. in भारतवर्ष of ब्रह्मावर्त, in कुरुक्षेत्र. Here ऊर्वशी enjoyed water sports with her companions when पुरूरवस् found her a second time. {{F}}1:  भा. I. 4. १५; IV. १९. 1; V. १९. १८; IX. १४. ३३. II. 9. ४४; Br. II. १२. १६; वा. ४५. ९५; ५५. ४३; १०८. ५९, ७८; १०९. २१;{{/F}} The ब्रह्मनदी; on its banks व्यास composed the भारत, and his hermitage was on the western bank. Here he heard the भागवत from नारद. {{F}}2:  भा. I. 4. २७; 7. 2.{{/F}} Here परशुराम had his अवभृत bath. {{F}}3:  Ib. IX. १६. २३.{{/F}} On its banks was the अम्बिकावन. {{F}}4:  Ib. X. ३४. 2 and 4.{{/F}} Here sages practised तपस्। At its source पृथु performed a hundred अश्वमेधस्। {{F}}5:  Ib. IV. १४. ३६; १६. २४.{{/F}} Lies on the way from द्वारका to हास्तिनपुर. Flows west at प्रभास; was made to flow back towards a desert where अम्बरीष performed sacrifices. {{F}}6:  Ib. X. ७१. २२; IX. ३०. 6; IX. 4. २२.{{/F}} When the sages per- [page३-554+ ४०] formed यज्ञ on its bank, a question arose as to who was the superior god in the world. भृगु, the son of ब्रह्मा was deputed to find this out. {{F}}7:  Ib. X. ८९. 1-2.{{/F}} Here are eleven places sacred to त्रीत, उशनस्, Manu and others. Vidura had his ablu- tions in all of them. {{F}}8:  भा. III: 1. २१-22.{{/F}} कृष्ण sat under an अश्वत्त tree on its banks preparing to leave off mortal coil and asked Uddhava to go to बदरी. {{F}}9:  Ib. III. 4. 3-8.{{/F}} On its banks Kardama performed austeri- ties for १०,000 years. Its banks filled with hermitages, one was Kardama's. In it देवहूती bathed. {{F}}१०:  Ib. III. २१. 6; २२. २७. २३. २५. २४: 9:{{/F}} Visited by Bala- राम. {{F}}११:  Ib. X. ७८. १८-19.{{/F}} परीक्षित् came to hear Dharma at the place where the R. flows East, complaining to Earth on the advent of Kali. {{F}}१२:  Ib. I. १६. ३७.{{/F}} Defined. {{F}}१३:  VIII. 4. २३-4.{{/F}} From the हिमालयस्; fit for श्राद्ध offerings; {{F}}१४:  Br. II. १६: २४: २७; III. १३. ६९; १४. ८३; Vi. III. १४. १८.{{/F}} a holy river; {{F}}१५:  M. 7. 3.{{/F}} sacred to पितृस्; flows from the slopes of the हेमकूट hill; {{F}}१६:  Ib. २२. २३.{{/F}} flows through कुरुक्षेत्र; {{F}}१७:  Ib. १२१: ६४-5; १८६. १०; २२९. 3.{{/F}} scene of talk between Garga and Atri. {{F}}१८:  Ib. २३९. १८.{{/F}} sacred to देवमात; {{F}}१९:  Ib. १३. ४४;{{/F}} in the chariot of त्रिपुरारि. {{F}}२०:  Ib. ११४. २०; १३३. २४.{{/F}}

