--a Veda imparted to Jaimini, {{F}}1:  भा. I. 4. २१; IX. ११. 2; २१. २८; X. 7. १४; ५३. १२; XI. २७. ३१; XII. 6. ७६; ११. ४७; १२. ६२. वा. ३१. ३३; ६५. २६. Vi. III. 4. 9 and १३.{{/F}} who arranged it under व्यास's guidance; present in वारुणि यज्ञ with विश्वावसुस् and Gandharvas; {{F}}2:  Br. II. ३४. १५; III. 1. २५.{{/F}} gave birth to a number of elephants; {{F}}3:  Ib III. 7. ३३४, ३३९.{{/F}} learnt by the Asuras; {{F}}4:  Ib IV. १२. १७.{{/F}} taught by Jai- mini to his son Sumantu and his grandson सुतवान; the latter's son Sukarma composed सहस्र सम्हिता and taught to his pupils हिरण्यनाभ, Kausalya and पौष्पिञ्जि; ५०० pupils of the latter were the northern chanters of the साम; हिरण्यनाभ's disciples the eastern chanters of the साम; one of his pupils, कृत, taught to his disciples २४ branches [page३-585+ ३५] of the सम्हिता; {{F}}5:  M. ४९. ७६; वा. ९९. १३०. Vi. III. 6. 1-7.{{/F}} part of विष्णु; {{F}}6:  Ib V. 1. ३७.{{/F}} served with other Vedas as a horse of the chariot of त्रिपुरारि. {{F}}7:  M. ८५. 5; १३३. ३१;{{/F}}

