सौभरि|saubhari
 (I)--a ऋग् Vedic sage who got himself trans- formed into a youthful person and requested king मान्- धात्रि for his daughter's hand; when he was asked to select one from the harem, he went in, when all his fifty daughters wanted to have him as their husband. So he agreed; after enjoying worldly pleasure for long, he felt the urge for मुक्ति and retired to the forest, with his wives following and became a वैखानसभिक्षु; lived with them; father of १५० sons; when the sage was dead, all his wives burnt themselves on his funeral pyre; {{F}}1:  भा. IX. 6. ३८-55; Vi. IV. 2. ६९ to end.{{/F}} before his marriage he was engaged in penance. Once immersed under the waters of the यमुना in contemplation of the Lord, he saw a fish in sexual union and felt a desire for home life; on another occasion he noticed गरुड consuming a fish, and cursed on behalf of [page३-704+ ३०] the sages that गरुड's visit to कालिन्दि would be his death. {{F}}2:  Ib. X. १७. 9-११.{{/F}} Knew the yoga power of Hari. {{F}}3:  Ib. II. 7. ४५.{{/F}}

सौभरि|saubhari
 (II)--a pupil of Devamitra. भा. XII. 6. ५६.

सौभरि|saubhari
 (III)--a son of सत्या and कृष्ण. Br. III. ७१. २४७.

सौभरिका|saubharikaa
--a daughter of सत्यभामा. Br. III. ७१. २४८.

