 (I)--praise of: by Arjuna; {{F}}1:  भा. I. 7. २२-26.{{/F}} by कुन्ती; {{F}}2:  Ib. 8. १८-43.{{/F}} by भीष्म; {{F}}3:  Ib. 9. ३२-42.{{/F}} by women of हास्तिनपुर; {{F}}4:  Ib. १०. २१-30.{{/F}} by शुक; {{F}}5:  Ib. II. 4. १२-24; 9. 5-१६.{{/F}} by ब्रह्मा; {{F}}6:  Ib. 9. २४-29.{{/F}} by जीव in embryo; {{F}}7:  Ib. III. १२-21.{{/F}} by देवहूती; {{F}}8:  Ib. ३३. 2-8.{{/F}} by दक्ष and others; {{F}}9:  Ib. IV. 7. २६-47.{{/F}} by सुनीति; {{F}}१०:  Ib. 8. १९-3.{{/F}} by Dhruva; {{F}}११:  Ib. 9. 6-१७.{{/F}} by पृथु; {{F}}१२:  Ib. २०. २३-31.{{/F}} by Pracetasas; {{F}}१३:  Ib. ३०. २२-42.{{/F}} by नारद; {{F}}१४:  Ib. ३१. 9-२२[4].{{/F}} रुद्रगीता in praise of: taught by शिव to Pracetasas; {{F}}१५:  Ib. २४. ३३-79.{{/F}} praise of Hari leads to attain divine knowledge and also to मोक्ष; {{F}}१६:  Ib. VII. 1. 4-5 [1-2]; 7. ३१.{{/F}} praise of, by Manu (स्वायम्भुव), {{F}}१७:  Ib. VIII. 1. 9-१६.{{/F}} by Gajendra; {{F}}१८:  Ib. 3. 2-२९.{{/F}} by ब्रह्मा; {{F}}१९:  Ib. 5. २६-50; 6. 8-१५; १७. २५-28.{{/F}} by शिव; {{F}}२०:  Ib. १२. 4-१३.{{/F}} by Aditi; {{F}}२१:  १७. 8-१०.{{/F}} by Bali in bondage, by प्रह्लाद; {{F}}२३:  Ib. २३. 6-8.{{/F}} and by Satyavrata; {{F}}२४:  Ib. २४. २९-30, ४६-53.{{/F}} by त्रयी and उपनिषदिच् and Yoga literature; {{F}}२५:  Ib. X. 8. ४५.{{/F}} praise of: by गरुड; {{F}}२६:  Ib. X. [५३व् 14-१६].{{/F}} by Mucukunda; {{F}}२७:  Ib. ५१. ४६-58.{{/F}} by जाम्बवत्; {{F}}२८:  Ib. ५६. २६-8.{{/F}} by कृतवर्मन्, and अक्रूर; {{F}}२९:  Ib. ४०. 1-३०; ५७. १२-17.{{/F}} by भूमि, mother of Naraka; {{F}}३०:  Ib. ५९. २५-31.{{/F}} by रुक्मिणी; {{F}}३१:  Ib. ६०. ३४-48.{{/F}} by Indra; {{F}}३२:  [६७ (v) २४-30].{{/F}} by नृग; {{F}}३३:  Ib. ६०. ४४; ६४. १०-29.{{/F}} and by Rudra; {{F}}३४:  Ib. ६३. ३४-45.{{/F}} his deeds recalled by the citizens of मथुरा; {{F}}३५:  Ib. X. ४३. २२-31.{{/F}} praise of; nature of; much in evidence in द्रविड; {{F}}३६:  Ib. XI. 5. ३२-40.{{/F}} by नारद; {{F}}३७:  Ib. X. ३७. 9-२३; ६९. १७-18; ७०. ३७-44.{{/F}} by kings in जरासन्ध's prison, and after their [page३-745+ ३९] release; {{F}}३८:  Ib. ७०. २५-30; ७३. 8-१६.{{/F}} by युधिष्टिर; {{F}}३९:  Ib. ७४. 2-5.{{/F}} by ऋषिस्; {{F}}४०:  Ib. ८४. १६-26.{{/F}} by Vasudeva, देवकी and Bali; {{F}}४१:  Ib. ८५. (whole).{{/F}} by बहुलाश्व; {{F}}४२:  Ib. ८६. ३१-6.{{/F}} by श्रुतदेव; {{F}}४३:  Ib. ८६. ४४-9.{{/F}} by श्रुतिस् (श्रुतिगीति); {{F}}४४:  Ib. ८७. १४-41.{{/F}} by gods; {{F}}४५:  Ib. XI. 6. 7-१९.{{/F}} by ब्रह्मा; {{F}}४६:  Ib. 6. २१-7; X. १४. 1-४०.{{/F}} by Uddhava; {{F}}४७:  Ib. ४२. ४९; 7. १४-18; ११. १३, ३४, ३६; २९. ३७-40.{{/F}} by नलकूबर and मणिग्रीव; {{F}}४८:  Ib. X. १०. २९-38.{{/F}} by कालिय and his wives; {{F}}४९:  Ib. १६. ३३-59.{{/F}} by Gopis (गोपिगीता); {{F}}५०:  Ib. २१. 7-१९; ३१. 1-१९; ३५. 2-२५.{{/F}} by Indra. {{F}}५१:  Ib. २७. 4-१३.{{/F}} ^२२ Ib. २२. 2-११, २१-23.

हरि|hari
 (II)--a name given to विष्णु by स्वायम्भुव Manu for saving three worlds from affliction; {{F}}1:  भा. II. 7. 2.{{/F}} acted as ब्रह्मा in Soma's राजसूय; {{F}}2:  M. २३. २१.{{/F}} अधिदेवत for the planet Budha; {{F}}3:  Ib. ९३. १३; २४६. 4, ३४: २४७. १९; २४८. ३६.{{/F}} does प्रणाम every day to शङ्कर. {{F}}4:  वा. २१. 7; ३५. १३.{{/F}}

हरि|hari
 (III)--a son of ऋषभ and a भागवत: expound- ed to Nimi the nature of a भागवतोत्तम. भा. V. 4. ११; XI. 2. २१, ४५-55.

हरि|hari
 (IV)--an अवतार्: born as son of हरिणी and Hari- medhas: awarded मोक्ष to Gajendra. भा. VIII. 1. ३०.

हरि|hari
 (V)--son of Vasudeva and देवकी to put down adharma. भा. IX. २४. ५५-67. [page३-746+ ३२]

हरि|hari
 (VI)--(Matsya). भा. X. ४०. १७.

हरि|hari
 (VII)--(as horse) killed Madhu and कैटभ. भा. X. ४०. १७.

हरि|hari
 (VIII)--(कूर्म) bore Mandara. भा. X. ४०. १८.

हरि|hari
 (IX)--(वराह) raised the Earth. भा. X. ४०. १८; Br. 5. १५.

हरि|hari
 (X)--Narasimha. भा. X. ४०. १९.

हरि|hari
 (XI)--निर्गुण and apart from प्रकृति: makes his devotees the poorest so as to create in them a spirit of detachment: Blesses and curses: In the garb of a Brahma- चारिन् persuaded वृक to test शिव's boon on himself: भृगु kicked the sleeping Hari in his chest and helped him to get united with लक्ष्मी: भृगु's wonder at it; {{F}}1:  भा. X. Chh. ८८-89.{{/F}} Has root in religious performances of Brahmanas and is himself यज्ञ and source of all Dharma: the २५थ् principle: Helped शिव in regaining his lost glory through Maya: took the form of a cow and with ब्रह्मा as calf drank the immortalising fluid of the well in Tripura; {{F}}2:  Ib. VII. 2. ११; 8. ५२; १०. ५१ and ६२; ११. 7.{{/F}} विभूतिस् of; {{F}}3:  Ib. १६. 9-४०.{{/F}} ब्रह्मा born of his grace and Rudra of his wrath. {{F}}4:  Ib. XII 5. 1.{{/F}}

हरि|hari
 (XII)--अवतार्स् of: पुरुष as ब्रह्मा, विष्णु and Rudra, नरनारायण, Hamsa, Datta, कुमार, ऋषभ, हयग्रीव, Matsya, वराह, कूर्म, नृसिम्ह, वामन, परशुराम and राम. भा. XI. 4 (whole). [page३-747+ ३३]

हरि|hari
 (XIII)--in a group--form of वासुदेव, Sankar- षण, Pradyumna and Aniruddha: as the indwellers of सूर्य: spoken of in nine forms such as time, place and so on. In the form of time, for every month seven attendants lead him; {{F}}1:  भा. XII. ११. २१ and २८, ३१-44.{{/F}} other attendants of. {{F}}2:  Ib. XI. २७. २७-9.{{/F}}

हरि|hari
 (XIV)--a तुषित god in the स्वारोचिष and a साध्य in the चाक्षुष epoch. Br. III. 3. १५.

हरि|hari
 (XV)--a son of Rukmakavaca appointed over Videha with his brother Parigha. Br. III. ७०. २९; M. ४४. २८-9; वा. ९५. २८.

हरि|hari
