हरिकथा|harikathaa
--(also नारायण Katha1) sung in the सभास् of ब्रह्मा and शिव: sacred, never dull and always new; {{F}}1:  भा. X. ६०. ४४; ५२. २०.{{/F}} one way of getting divine knowledge: leads to virtue, nectar itself: purifies men and women; {{F}}2:  Ib. VII. 1. 5 [3]; 7. ३१. X. 1. १३ and १६. XI. 3. 2.{{/F}} fit to listen to, and fit to [page३-748+ ४०] be told and listened to: would never give satiety: by listening to it one gets proper vision and crosses the road of सम्सार. For instance hearing of the अवतार् of वामन leads one to bliss and that of Matsya to world's welfare; {{F}}3:  Ib. I. १५. ३६; १८. 9-१० and १४; V. १२. १६. VIII. २३. ३०; २४. 1-3; X. ९०. २१ [1], २४ and ५०. XI. १४. २६; १९. २०. XI. १४. २६; १९. २०.{{/F}} purifies the worlds and destroys the sins of Kali; {{F}}4:  Ib. XI. ११. २३ and ३५; XII. 8. 6.{{/F}} faith in the कथा im- portant; {{F}}5:  Ib. XI. २०. 8-9, २७; २६. २८-29; २७. ४४.{{/F}} importance of, stated by नृसिम्ह to प्रह्लाद, and by नारद to युधिष्टिर; {{F}}6:  Ib. VII. १०. १२; १४. 3.{{/F}} praise of; {{F}}7:  Ib. II. 1. 5, 2. ३६-37; 3. १४. २५; 4. 8. 2-6, १७; III. १९. ३३-8; २०. 6; ३२. १८-19; X. 1. 4-१६; 7. 1-3; १२. ४१-3; १३. 1. 2; १६. 2-3; ७८. [९६ (v) 2-4]; ८०. 1-4; XI. 5. 4.{{/F}} परीक्षित्'s deep interest in, and नारद singing of; {{F}}8:  Ib. X. 1. १५; I. 5. २६ and २८; 6. ३३.{{/F}} अरिष्तसेन hears it and narrates it to किम्पुरुष; {{F}}9:  Ib. V. १९. 2; VI. 2. २६; 3. ३१.{{/F}} narrated by शुक; {{F}}१०:  Ib. VII. 1. 5.{{/F}} by Gopis on the eve of कृष्ण's departure to मथुरा, and on hearing कृष्ण's message through Uddhava. {{F}}११:  Ib. X. ३९. १९. ३०; ४७. ३७-52.{{/F}}

